1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:11,000
[ 中文翻译：疯狂弥天大幌 ]
合并调校：daidai75
[ translation: loco-whopper ]

2
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,500
《桃色血案》

3
00:01:52,510 --> 00:01:54,110
“铁城”

4
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,900
嗨，托伊伯尔。
Hi, Toybull.

5
00:02:14,530 --> 00:02:17,260
嘿，看到你朋友刚驾车回城了，麦卡锡先生。
Hey, your pal just drove into town, Mr. McCarthy.

6
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:21,210
再给我来一杯，托伊伯尔。
I'll have one more, Toybull.

7
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:25,510
恐怕我得明天才能付你酒钱。
I'm afraid I'll have to pay my bar bill tomorrow.

8
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:27,640
我信得过你，麦卡锡先生。
You're good with me, Mr. McCarthy.

9
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:29,650
谢谢你，托伊伯尔。
Thank you, Toybull.

10
00:02:35,050 --> 00:02:36,610
晚安，托伊伯尔。
Good night, Toybull.

11
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:39,250
晚安，麦卡锡先生。
Good night, Mr. McCarthy.

12
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:58,420
“保罗・比格勒，律师”

13
00:04:42,310 --> 00:04:43,800
我是接线员。
Operator.

14
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,180
接线员，给我接…
Operator, I want...

15
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:49,410
雷鸣湾489号。
489 Thunder Bay.

16
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,820
我想和曼尼昂夫人通话。
I want to speak to Mrs. Manion.

17
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:54,120
曼-尼-昂。
M-A-N-I-O-N.

18
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:56,290
我是保罗・比格勒。
This is Paul Biegler speaking.

19
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,420
铁城700号。
Iron City 700.

20
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:04,630
反正你会看。
You do that.

21
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:07,330
既然你已经偷看了，那么你就…
After you sneak a peek, why, you...

22
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,810
打开你看到的东西吧。
uncork whatever you find.

23
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,320
- 要替你倒点儿吗？
- 荣幸之至。
- Shall I pour?
- Be a privilege.

24
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,020
乐意效劳，先生。
My pleasure, sir.

25
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:33,620
你和这个士兵单打独斗啊。
You fought this soldier by yourself.

26
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:35,900
你一直在独斟独饮，保利。
You've been drinking alone, Paulie.

27
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,060
我不喜欢你那样。
I don't like that.

28
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:41,730
放下你的石头，律师，你自己也
住在玻璃房子里【咱们彼此彼此】。
Drop the stone, counselor.
You live in a glass house.

29
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:47,200
我屋子的窗户很久以前就都被打破了，
所以我想说什么就可以说什么。
My windows have been busted long ago, 
so I can say as I please.

30
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,270
想来根意大利雪茄吗？
Have an Italian cigar?

31
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:52,540
不，谢谢。
No, thanks.

32
00:05:52,650 --> 00:05:56,320
那些发出臭味的植物【抽雪茄】
是你堕落的另一个象征。
Those stinkweeds are another 
sign of your decadence.

33
00:06:00,330 --> 00:06:01,850
保利，这是事实啊。
Paulie, it's a fact.

34
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:05,360
自从米奇・罗德威克将你
挤出地方检察官办公室，
Since Mitch Lodwick beat you out of 
the office of public prosecutor...

35
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:08,260
你就成了个废人。
you haven't been worth salt for peanuts.

36
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:10,530
当然我也理解你的感受。
Not that I don't understand how you feel.

37
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:15,670
一个人如果从他用了很久的办公室里
被挤了出来，
A man gets beat out of an office 
he's held for a long time...

38
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:19,340
那么他会觉得遭到了圈内人的摒弃。
he feels his community has deserted him.

39
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:21,810
他会觉得周围的人对他轻蔑地指指戳戳。
The finger of scorn is pointed at him.

40
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:24,810
只有孤寂的心灵才会理解我的痛苦。
None but the lonely hearts shall know my anguish.

41
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:27,980
保利，你是个出色的律师，
你应该表现得像那么回事。
Paulie, you're a good lawyer.
You ought to make like one.

42
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:31,090
你应该呆在这儿，时刻准备为客户服务，
而不是四处钓钓鱼，或演奏那些…
Be here ready for clients, 
not out fishing and playing that...

43
00:06:31,090 --> 00:06:32,790
唧唧歪歪的爵士乐。
rooty-tooty jazz.

44
00:06:32,890 --> 00:06:34,660
噢，我还是有谋生手段的。
Oh, I'm making a living.

45
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,730
我干些非实质性的活儿――
I run a few abstracts--

46
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:39,820
时不时地给那些闹离婚的男女们提提建议，
how to divorce Jane Doe 
from John Doe every once in a while.

47
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:42,530
或是对那些欠债不还的人给些警告。
Threaten a few deadbeats.

48
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,500
而在夜里，我则坐下来喝一杯波旁威士忌，
And in the evening, 
I sit around and drink bourbon whisky...

49
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:49,560
和帕内尔・埃米特・麦卡锡一起研习法律，
and read law with Parnell Emmitt McCarthy...

50
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,040
他是个了不起的人。
one of the world's great men.

51
00:06:52,150 --> 00:06:54,910
那可是对我的溢美之词，保利。
That was a kind word, Paulie.

52
00:06:55,020 --> 00:06:56,780
你知道…
You know...

53
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:58,780
我以前可能是还不错。
I might have been.

54
00:06:58,890 --> 00:07:03,020
这也是为什么我不愿意看到
你的才华被一些庸才所忽略的原因。
That's one of the reasons I hate to see 
your talent pushed aside by lesser men.

55
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,560
我看着你，仿佛看到了多年以前的自己，
I look at you, and I see myself years ago...

56
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:09,050
那时我也沉醉在那些年久发黄的书籍
所散发出的气味里，
with the same love for the smell 
of the old brown books...

57
00:07:09,060 --> 00:07:12,260
和这样落满灰尘的办公室里。
and the dusty office.

58
00:07:13,070 --> 00:07:15,130
这些是我们的玫瑰，
Here's the rose.

59
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:18,600
我们的百合，我们亲爱的狼犬。
A lily. A sweet lupine.

60
00:07:18,710 --> 00:07:22,040
《美国最高法院报告》。
The United States Supreme Court reports.

61
00:07:23,410 --> 00:07:25,040
那么…
Well...

62
00:07:25,150 --> 00:07:27,710
今晚我们读些什么呢，律师？
what shall we read this evening, counselor?

63
00:07:27,810 --> 00:07:30,680
来点儿大法官霍尔姆斯的报告如何？
How about a little Chief Justice Holmes?

64
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:38,050
让大法官稍等一会儿，我可能有客户。
Keep Chief Justice on hold for a moment.
I might have a client.

65
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,650
- 我在等一个电话。你好！
- 比格勒先生吗？
- Waiting for a call. Hello?
- Mr. Biegler?

66
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,890
- 噢，是的，我是保罗・比格勒。
- 你当事人的电话。
- This is Paul Biegler speaking.
- It's your party.

67
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,230
- 喂？曼尼昂夫人吗？
- 什么？
- Hello? Mrs. Manion?
- What?

68
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:46,960
比格勒先生？
Mr. Biegler?

69
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:49,400
抱歉刚才没能接通你。
你收到我的留言啦？
I'm sorry I missed you a while ago.
Did you get my message?

70
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,990
- 那是谁？叫什么名字？
- 请稍等一会儿。
- Who is that? What is that name?
- Just a minute, please.

71
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:54,630
好像电话不太清楚。别挂掉。
We seem to have a bad connection. Hold on.

72
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:58,110
是个女人，叫曼尼昂。
梅达说她想找我。
It's a woman, name of Manion.
Maida took a message from her.

73
00:07:58,210 --> 00:08:00,080
- 住在雷鸣湾？
- 对，是的。
- In Thunder Bay?
- Uh-huh.

74
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:02,110
要是她想让你替他丈夫出庭，就说“好的”。
If she wants you to represent her husband, say yes.

75
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:05,520
- 可是我还不知道这是怎么回事。
- 当作你已经知道好了，先答应了她再说！
- I don't know what it's all about.
- Pretend you do and say yes.

76
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:06,980
- 喂？
- 比格勒先生？
- Hello?
- Mr. Biegler?

77
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:10,420
噢，是的，现在好多了。
是的，我听得很清楚。
Oh, yes. This is much better now.
Yes, I can hear you fine.

78
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:13,220
整个下午我一直在等你的电话。
I've waited for your call all afternoon.

79
00:08:13,330 --> 00:08:16,230
噢，对不起，我才刚回来。
Yes, well, I just got in a few moments ago,

80
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:18,850
你看到报上登的我丈夫的事儿了？
毛毛，别这样。
You've read about my husband? 
Muffy, please.

81
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:20,330
是的。
Yes.

82
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:23,400
比格勒先生，你读过报上登的
我丈夫的事情吗？毛毛，别这样。
Mr. Biegler, have you read 
about my husband? Muffy, please,

83
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:28,270
唔…嗯，是的，我读了一些。
Well, uh, yes, I have, a little.

84
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:30,670
- 你会为他辩护吗？
- 呃，我不知道。
- Will you defend him?
- I don't know.

85
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:33,940
- 我得再多了解一些情况。
- 你愿意和他谈谈吗？
- I'd have to know more about it.
- Will you talk to him?

86
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:36,950
比格勒先生，他现在被关在县监狱。
明天上午你可以见他吗？
Mr. Biegler, he's in the county jail.
Will you see him in the morning?

87
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:40,880
他非常盼望能见到你，
因为有人竭力向他推荐你。
He's very anxious to see you.
You've been so highly recommended.

88
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:42,720
是吗？
I have?

89
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:45,990
是的，有人向他提到的你，
你愿意见他吗？
Yes, someone told him about you, 
Will you see him?

90
00:08:46,090 --> 00:08:48,890
好的，我想可以。我明天上午去见他。
I suppose I could. I'll see him tomorrow morning.

91
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:53,290
- 你想让我也一起去吗？
- 那太好了。
- Would you want me there too?
- I think that'd be fine.

92
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,660
那就10点钟见吧。
Let's make it about 10:00.

93
00:08:55,770 --> 00:08:58,240
谢谢，太谢谢你了！
Thank you, Thank you so much.

94
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:00,640
嗯，不用那么客气。再见。
Yes, you're quite welcome. Bye.

95
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,330
那么，这究竟是怎么回事？
Now, what's this all about?

96
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:05,470
有个叫巴尼・奎尔的家伙强奸了曼尼昂夫人。
A man named Barney Quill raped Mrs. Manion.

97
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:07,810
她的丈夫，他是陆军中尉――
Her husband, he's a lieutenant in the army--

98
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:10,780
在雷鸣湾有个临时基地，炮兵之类的――
there's a temporary base in Thunder Bay, 
a gunnery or something--

99
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:15,580
这个中尉来到奎尔的旅店，向他连开了五枪，
The lieutenant goes to Quill's place 
and plugs Mr. Quill about five times...

100
00:09:15,690 --> 00:09:18,520
铅头中毒致使奎尔先生当场殒命。
which causes Mr. Quill to promptly die 
of lead poisoning.

101
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:20,720
- 这是何时发生的事？
- 几个晚上之前吧。
- When did this happen?
- A couple of nights ago.

102
00:09:20,730 --> 00:09:23,890
要是你没有外出去某个
鸟不拉屎的死水潭钓鱼的话，
If you hadn't been out fishing 
in some godforsaken backwater...

103
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,500
你早就应该听说了。
you'd have known about it.

104
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:42,670
- 早上好，梅达。
- 噢，你总算回来了。
- Morning, Maida.
- Oh, there it is.

105
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:44,680
- 怎么啦？
- 报纸。
- What?
- The newspaper.

106
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:48,040
我以为他们可能不再送报来了，
因为我们没付账单。
I thought maybe they didn't bring it.
We haven't paid the bill.

107
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:50,910
- 你看到我留的条了吗？
- 是的。我们可能会接这个案子。
- Did you get my note?
- Uh-huh. We may be on the case.

108
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:54,250
在去和曼尼昂中尉谈话前，
我正多读点有关案子的情况。
I'm just reading up on it now
before talking to Lt. Manion.

109
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:56,120
他没回自己家吗？
Doesn't he ever go home?

110
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:59,210
嗯，你是说帕内尔？
我们昨晚呆到很晚。
Oh, you mean Parnell?
We were up late last night.

111
00:10:59,330 --> 00:11:01,090
像是如此。
Is that a fact?

112
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:04,490
我想你最好取消我今天所有的预约。
I think maybe you better cancel 
all my appointments for today.

113
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:08,260
还有什么预约？大家都以为
你搬到林子里去住了。
What appointments? People think 
you've migrated into the woods.

114
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:13,270
如果冰箱里再放些鱼的话，
那么它就会自个儿…
If this refrigerator gets any more
fish in it, it'll swim upstream...

115
00:11:13,370 --> 00:11:15,600
游到上游去产卵了。
and spawn all by itself.

116
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,940
对不起，能稍微打断你一下吗？
May I have your attention for a moment, please?

117
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:24,780
我昨天看了一下你的支票本。
I was going over your checkbook yesterday.

118
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:27,010
我开不出给我的薪水了。
I can't pay me my salary.

119
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,590
你怎么把沃尔克夫妇的离婚诉讼费花光的？
What did you do with the fee 
for the Walkers' divorce?

120
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:32,990
拿去帮着往某个铀矿里掺假啦？
Help salt a uranium mine or something?

121
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:36,820
- 仅买了些生活必需品。
- 比如说那艘舷外马达艇。
- Bought a few bare necessities.
- Like a new outboard motor.

122
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:40,090
我希望我也能被归入必需品之列。
I wish I could be classed as a necessity.

123
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:43,600
- 要烤面包吗？
- 不…不了。我会…呃…
- Aren't you gonna have your toast?
- No, no, I'll, uh--

124
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:47,140
我会打电话给你，告诉你事情的进展情况。
I'll call you, let you know how things are going.

125
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:49,730
小心别让他的“紫心勋章”收买了你。
Don't let him pay you off in Purple Hearts.

126
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:52,440
那些职业当兵的穷得丁当响。
Those professional soldiers never have a dime.

127
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:55,140
我知道的，我以前嫁过一个。
I ought to know. I was married to one.

128
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:17,970
对不起，你是曼尼昂夫人？
Beg your pardon. Are you Mrs. Manion?

129
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:20,370
- 你好。
- 我是保罗・比格勒。
- Hi.
- I'm Paul Biegler.

130
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:22,410
- 我叫劳拉。
- 你好。
- I'm Laura.
- How do you do?

131
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,780
- 这是毛毛。
- 噢，毛毛。
- This is Muff.
- Oh, Muff.

132
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,780
监狱就在那边。
The jail's right here.

133
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:32,470
你挺高哈。
You're tall.

134
00:12:35,660 --> 00:12:38,650
- 你好，保利！
- 嗨，苏罗。
- Hello, Paulie!
- Hi, Sulo.

135
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,660
你在这儿等着，毛毛。
You wait here, Muffy.

136
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,600
- 见到你真高兴，保利。
- 你怎么样？
- Good to see you, Paulie.
- How you feeling?

137
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,460
还行。我想你是来见那个当兵的吧。
Fine. I guess you come for the soldier boy.

138
00:12:50,570 --> 00:12:53,330
没错。我们可不可以
在警官的办公室里进行谈话呢？
Yeah. Do you think it'd be all right 
if we talk in the sheriff's office?

139
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,500
噢，当然可以，保利。我把他带过来。
Oh, sure, Paulie. I'll bring him down.

140
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:09,410
你不介意把眼镜摘掉吧，曼尼昂夫人？
Would you mind taking your glasses off, Mrs. Manion?

141
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:14,530
天哪！那是巴尼・奎尔干的吗？
Did Barney Quill do that to you?

142
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:16,600
是的，远不止这些。
Mm-hmm. More than that.

143
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:18,600
你应该看看，全身上下都有。
You should see. All over.

144
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:23,430
要是你觉得那样更自在一点的话，
你还是戴上吧。
You can put them back on 
if it's more comfortable for you.

145
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:35,480
这位是保利・比格勒。
保利，这就是你要的人。
This is Paulie Biegler.
This is the bucko, Paulie.

146
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:37,910
- 你好。
- 嗨，曼尼。
- Hello, there.
- Hi, Manny.

147
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:39,920
嗨，劳拉。
Hello, Laura.

148
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:47,020
曼尼昂夫人，今天下午2点左右，
你可以去我办公室见我吗？
Mrs. Manion, can you meet me down in
my office about 2:00 this afternoon?

149
00:13:47,130 --> 00:13:49,150
地址是巴恩汉西街305号。
It's 305 West Barnham.

150
00:13:49,260 --> 00:13:51,290
- 当然可以。
- 那好。
- Of course.
- Fine.

151
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,990
你需要什么东西吗，亲爱的？
Is there anything I can get you, hon?

152
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:56,000
不需要什么，亲爱的。
I'm all right, hon.

153
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,330
到里面来。
Right in here.

154
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:14,450
通缉犯，前十名。
Wanted. The big ten.

155
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:17,660
人们评出了最佳服饰女士前十名，
They got the ten best-dressed dames...

156
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:21,190
最佳球队前十名，最佳曲子前十名，
the ten top teams, the ten top tunes...

157
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:23,020
而这里是最高通缉犯前十名。
and now the ten most wanted.

158
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:27,400
嗯，别这么说，那也是一种美国梦。
那些家伙也算是成功了。
Don't knock it. That's the American dream.
Those boys made the grade.

159
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:30,800
你曾经是…
You were the...

160
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:32,930
这个地区的检察官，是吗？
district attorney around here, weren't you?

161
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,100
嗯哼，干了十年。
Ten years.

162
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:37,230
那么你干辩护律师有什么经验呢？
What's your experience as a defense lawyer?

163
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:41,140
- 不算很多。
- 我怎么知道你能应付我的案子？
- Not very much.
- How do I know you can handle my case?

164
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:44,150
我想你当然不知道。
I guess you don't know.

165
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,220
何不妨我们谈谈呢？
Shall we talk about it?

166
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,750
只能这样了。
I suppose so.

167
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:52,490
行了，中尉。别这么灰心丧气。
Come on, Lieutenant. Don't be so bored.

168
00:14:52,590 --> 00:14:55,960
你知道，也许没有哪个律师
能够应付你的案子，
It might very well be that no lawyer 
can handle your case...

169
00:14:56,060 --> 00:14:58,260
如果你的目标是想完全逃脱罪责的话。
if you mean getting you off scot-free.

170
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:01,560
你大概忘了巴尼・奎尔强奸了我的妻子。
You seemed to be forgetting 
Barney Quill raped my wife.

171
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:03,760
不成文的【道德】法律是站在我这一边的。
I have the unwritten law on my side.

172
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:06,630
不成文法只是一个神话，中尉。
The unwritten law's a myth, Lieutenant.

173
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:09,440
根本没有什么不成文法这回事儿。
There is no such thing as the unwritten law.

174
00:15:09,540 --> 00:15:12,510
任何人只要犯了谋杀罪，
而且这种说法得到了证实，
And anyone who commits a murder 
on the theory that it does exist...

175
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:15,710
那么他就会被关入州监狱，
在里面吃喝拉撒，
has just bought himself room and board 
in the state penitentiary.

176
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:17,540
也许得终身服刑。
Maybe for life.

177
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:22,650
了解了这些，也许我们接着可以…
Now, with that in mind, 
perhaps we can proceed with a...

178
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:25,220
从一些问答开始――
few questions and answers that--

179
00:15:25,330 --> 00:15:28,490
也就是…呃…
能借你打火机用一下吗？
That, uh--
Can I borrow your lighter?

180
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:35,860
我们可以开始一些个问答，
那也许会有助于你的辩护。
We can proceed with a few questions and 
answers that might help your defense.

181
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:40,640
当然也有可能没什么用。
But it probably won't be.

182
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:44,940
是啊，打火机不错。
Yes. Nice lighter.

183
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:50,750
- 好吧。
- 你多大了？
- Okay.
- How old are you?

184
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:53,320
- 二十八岁。
- 服役多少年了？
- Twenty-eight.
- How long have you been in the service?

185
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:55,410
50年参的军。
Since '50.

186
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:58,080
- 参加过战斗吗？
- 韩战。
- You see any action?
- Korea.

187
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,560
- 授过勋吗？
- 很多。
- Have any decorations?
- Plenty.

188
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:04,220
- 这是你的第一次婚姻？
- 不是。
- Is this your first marriage?
- No.

189
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:07,360
这不是在证人席上，
你不必只回答“是”或“不是”。
You're not on the witness stand.
You don't have to answer yes or no.

190
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:10,530
多给我讲一点你们的婚姻状况。
Just give me the matrimonial rundown.

191
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:14,830
- 有必要吗？
- 有没有必要得由我说了算。
- Is this necessary?
- I'll be the judge of that.

192
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:18,130
我的第一个妻子和我离了婚。
My first wife divorced me.

193
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,970
说我虐待了她。
Charged cruelty.

194
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:24,810
其实只是些在床上吃吃饼干之类的事，
你知道，都是些鸡毛蒜皮的小事儿。
Eating crackers in bed.
You know, the usual stuff.

195
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,440
事实的真相是…
Truth was...

196
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:29,080
我在朝鲜时她有了另一个家伙。
she found another guy when I was in Korea.

197
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:34,690
四年前我在佐治亚州遇见了劳拉。
I met Laura four years ago in Georgia.

198
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:37,320
在她离婚后我们就马上结婚了。
We were married right after her divorce.

199
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,900
你认识她丈夫吗？
Did you know the husband?

200
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:44,270
- 他是我手下的。
- 你是说你们是伙伴？
- He was in my outfit down there.
- You mean, you were buddies?

201
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:47,770
好吧，我不接着问了，
可能显得有些不合时宜。
I'll withdraw the question.
It's a little old-fashioned.

202
00:16:47,870 --> 00:16:51,400
你们两个的婚姻中
有没有孩子来自于哪一方呢？
Have there been any children 
by or from any of these marriages?

203
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:54,710
- 没有。
- 对将来有什么打算吗？
- No.
- Any present prospects?

204
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:57,080
没什么特别的，直到出了巴尼・奎尔这件事。
Not unless Barney Quill started something.

205
00:16:57,180 --> 00:16:59,340
你用什么枪打的奎尔？
What kind of a gun did you use?

206
00:16:59,450 --> 00:17:02,790
战争后留下的，是把鲁格尔手枪。
现在在警察这儿。
War souvenir. A Luger.
The police have it now.

207
00:17:02,890 --> 00:17:06,020
我想你读过报纸上登的
有关你案子的那些事吧？
I suppose you've read the newspapers, 
the stories about your case.

208
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:09,820
- 读过一些。
- 那它们是不是基本属实呢？
- Some of them.
- Are they substantially correct?

209
00:17:09,930 --> 00:17:13,020
- 是的。
- 那么你并没有看见奎尔强奸并殴打你的妻子？
- Yes.
- And you didn't see Quill rape and beat your wife?

210
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:15,190
是的，没有。
No. No.

211
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,630
当她回来后…
When she got back...

212
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:19,710
回到我们的车房后，她告诉我所发生的事。
to the trailer, she told me what had happened.

213
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:22,600
在你去奎尔的酒吧并杀死他之前，
那有多长时间？
And how long was it before you went 
over to Quill's and killed him?

214
00:17:22,710 --> 00:17:24,570
我不知道精确的时间，可能有一小时吧。
I don't know exactly. Maybe an hour.

215
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:27,110
那么长时间，嗯？
That long, huh?

216
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:30,670
报纸上说你妻子自愿接受测谎仪测试。
The newspapers say that your wife 
volunteered to take a lie detector test.

217
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:34,180
- 这你知道吗？
- 我也是从报纸上读到的，她也是这样跟我说的。
- Do you know anything about this?
- Only what I read and what she told me.

218
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:36,810
你知道测谎仪的测试结果吗？
Do you know how the lie detector test turned out?

219
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:38,320
他们没告诉她。
They didn't tell her.

220
00:17:38,420 --> 00:17:41,790
- 什么事，苏罗？
- 监狱里的中饭好了。
- Yes, Sulo?
- We got lunch served for the jail.

221
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:45,690
- 你想和我们一起吃吗？
- 你姐姐还在监狱里做饭？
- You want to eat with us?
- Your sister still cook for the jail?

222
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,700
噢，是的，她还在做。
Oh, sure. She cooks.

223
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,960
那么请转达我对她的问候，苏罗。
Well, you give her my compliments, Sulo.

224
00:17:52,070 --> 00:17:54,040
我在市里还有个午餐约会。
I've got a luncheon date downtown.

225
00:17:54,140 --> 00:17:56,230
- 走好，比格勒先生。
- 午饭后我会回来。
- Nice going, Mr. Biegler.
- I'll be back after lunch.

226
00:17:56,340 --> 00:18:00,800
你瞧，如果刚才有所冒犯的话，请你原谅。
Look, I'm sorry if I offended you a while ago.

227
00:18:00,910 --> 00:18:03,850
不，你没有。
No, you're not.

228
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:06,250
行了，伙计。
Come on, bucko.

229
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,910
谢谢。
Thank you.

230
00:18:09,390 --> 00:18:11,290
把盐递给我，保利。
Pass the salt, Paulie.

231
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:15,520
谢谢。
Thank you.

232
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,290
你有没有给中尉好好地上一课呢？
Did you give the lieutenant the well known lecture?

233
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:24,030
如果你是问我有没有教他编个谎，回答是“没有”。
If you mean, did I coach him into a phony story, no.

234
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:26,930
也许你太单纯了，保罗，
Maybe you're too pure, Paul.

235
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:30,810
对法律中所固有的缺陷来说，你太单纯了。
Too pure for the natural impurities of the law.

236
00:18:30,910 --> 00:18:34,940
要么你就给中尉个机会，
让他另外请人替他辩护；
Could be that you owe the lieutenant 
the chance to find a defense.

237
00:18:35,050 --> 00:18:37,710
要么你就稍微点拨他一下，给他指条道，
Could also be that you might guide him 
a little, show him the way...

238
00:18:37,820 --> 00:18:39,980
让他自己决定何去何从。
and let him decide if he wants to take it.

239
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:42,610
- 要盐吗？
- 不，我还没剥完。
- Want some salt?
- No, I'm not ready.

240
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:45,120
总之，我不是做这家伙律师的合适人选。
Anyway, I'm not the right lawyer for this fellow.

241
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:47,490
他有点傲慢，有点敌意……
He's insolent, hostile--

242
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:52,120
你没必要喜欢上他，替他辩护就成。
You don't have to love him. Just defend him.

243
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:54,260
怎么回事儿？你不缺钱啦？
What's the matter? Don't you need a fee?

244
00:18:55,970 --> 00:18:59,230
你知道吗？我倒是认为
你可能有点害怕了。
You know something? I think 
you might be a little bit afraid.

245
00:18:59,340 --> 00:19:03,170
- 害怕什么？
- 害怕你可能会栽在这上面。
- Afraid of what?
- That you might get licked.

246
00:19:06,550 --> 00:19:10,210
你知道比费城律师【精明的律师】
更加狡猾的是谁吗？
You know, there's only one thing more 
devious than a Philadelphia lawyer...

247
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:12,410
那就是爱尔兰律师【麦卡锡是爱尔兰姓】。
and that's an Irish lawyer.

248
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:14,040
把盐给我。
Pass the salt.

249
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:18,790
放下来，放下来。
Put it down.

250
00:19:26,130 --> 00:19:30,160
- 嗨，你好。
- 我通常只对叫我保罗的人打招呼。
- Hello there.
- I usually answer to the name Paul.

251
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,170
你还有别的笑话吗？
You gonna have some more jokes?

252
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:34,300
除非你想成为滑稽演员。
Not unless you want to be the comic.

253
00:19:34,410 --> 00:19:38,100
噢，我给你带了些烟卷。
Oh, I brought you some cigarettes.

254
00:19:38,210 --> 00:19:40,110
- 哦，谢谢了！
- 讲和了？
- Oh, thanks.
- Peace?

255
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:43,200
- 当然。
- 那好，很好。那么中尉…
- Sure.
- Fine, fine. Now, Lieutenant...

256
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:46,620
有四种方式我可以替谋杀案辩护：
there are four ways I can defend murder.

257
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:50,310
第一，那不是谋杀，
那是自杀或者事故；
Number one, it wasn't murder.
It was suicide or accidental.

258
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:53,420
第二，不是你干的；
第三，可以证明你的合法性，
Number two, you didn't do it.
Number three, you were legally justified...

259
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:55,690
比如说为了保护你的家人或是正当防卫；
like the protection of your home or self-defense.

260
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:59,700
第四，你有杀人的理由。
Number four, the killing was excusable.

261
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:02,500
那么我符合这美好前景的哪一条呢？
Where do I fit in to this rosy picture?

262
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:06,870
我先来告诉你你不符合哪一条吧：
其实前三条你都不符合。
I'll tell you where you don't fit in.
You don't fit in any of the first three.

263
00:20:06,970 --> 00:20:10,880
为什么？为什么不能证明
我杀死强奸我妻子的人是合法的？
Why? Why wouldn't I be legally justified 
in killing the man who raped my wife?

264
00:20:10,980 --> 00:20:12,640
时间因素。
Time element.

265
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:15,080
如果你是当场抓住他的，
那么也许可以证明你开枪合法，
If you'd caught him in the act, 
the shooting might have been justified...

266
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:18,150
但是你并没有当场抓住他，
而且你有时间叫警察，
but you didn't catch him in the act, 
and you had time to bring the police...

267
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:19,910
这你也没做。
and you didn't do that either.

268
00:20:20,020 --> 00:20:22,920
你会因谋杀而被判有罪――
预谋的、报复性的谋杀罪。
You're guilty of murder--
premeditated and with vengeance.

269
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:25,220
在任何法庭，这都是一级谋杀罪。
That's first-degree murder in any court of law.

270
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:28,890
- 你是不是想让我服罪？
- 如果我建议你认罪，我会告诉你的。
- Are you telling me to plead guilty?
- When I advise a cop out, you'll know.

271
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,660
- 认罪？
- 就是服罪并请求宽恕。
- Cop out?
- That's plead guilty and ask for mercy.

272
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:35,170
如果你这不是在建议我认罪，
那么你是在建议我干嘛？
If you're not telling me to cop out, 
what are you telling me to do?

273
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:37,170
我没建议你干任何事情。
I'm not telling you to do anything.

274
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:40,360
我只是想让你了解下法律上是怎么说的。
I just want you to understand the letter of the law.

275
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:45,770
- 那你就继续。
- 继续什么？
- Go on.
- Go on with what?

276
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:50,740
继续你想说的啊。
Whatever it is you're getting at.

277
00:20:54,550 --> 00:20:57,350
你知道，你很聪明，中尉。
You know, you're very bright, Lieutenant.

278
00:20:57,460 --> 00:21:02,420
那就让我们看看你究竟能有多聪明。
Now let's see how really bright you can be.

279
00:21:04,730 --> 00:21:08,390
好吧，那我就加把劲。
Well, I'm working at it.

280
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,770
好的，听着，因为你妻子遭到强奸，
All right. Now, because your wife was raped...

281
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:14,270
在法庭上，会形成有利于你的氛围。
you'll have a favorable atmosphere in the courtroom.

282
00:21:14,370 --> 00:21:17,170
如果所有情况都属实的话，
你会受到同情。
The sympathy will be with you 
if all the facts are true.

283
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:21,870
你所需要的是某种法律上的借口，
这样陪审团就会站在你的角度上同情你。
What you need is a legal peg so the jury 
can hang their sympathy in your behalf.

284
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,480
你明白我的意思吗？
You follow me?

285
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:28,420
那么你的合法借口是什么呢，中尉？
What's your legal excuse, Lieutenant?

286
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:32,920
你杀死巴尼・奎尔的合法借口是什么？
What's your legal excuse for killing Barney Quill?

287
00:21:35,030 --> 00:21:37,290
没有正当理由哈？
Not justification?

288
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,830
没有正当理由。
Not justification.

289
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:45,470
借口。
Excuse.

290
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:50,610
正当的借口。
Just excuse.

291
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:07,090
有什么借口呢？
What excuses are there?

292
00:22:07,190 --> 00:22:09,860
我怎么知道？是你把奎尔干掉的。
How should I know?
You're the one that plugged Quill.

293
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:14,800
- 我当时可能【气】疯了。
- 什么意思？
- I must've been mad.
- How's that?

294
00:22:15,630 --> 00:22:17,530
我说我当时可能【气】疯了。
I said I must've been mad.

295
00:22:21,670 --> 00:22:24,300
不，恶劣情绪不能作为借口。
No, bad temper's no excuse.

296
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:29,450
我是说，我可能发疯了。
I mean, I must've been crazy.

297
00:22:34,190 --> 00:22:36,520
这样是不是有点希望了？
Am I getting warmer?

298
00:22:41,260 --> 00:22:44,090
好吧，我们回头再见。
Okay. See you around.

299
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,960
这样是不是有点希望了？
Am I getting warmer?

300
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:49,000
在我和你妻子谈过以后，咱们再聊吧。
I'll tell you that after I talk to your wife.

301
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:52,830
与此同时，你好好回想一下
你当时怎样个发疯法。
In the meantime, see if you can 
remember just how crazy you were.

302
00:23:00,110 --> 00:23:02,140
曼尼昂夫人来了吗？
Is Mrs. Manion here yet?

303
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:04,440
她已经等了很长时间了。
She's been waiting quite a while.

304
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:07,750
她把你的所有唱片集都过了一遍，
从迪克西兰【南方爵士乐】到布鲁贝克【爵士乐作曲家】。
She's been through all your albums, 
from Dixieland to Brubeck.

305
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:09,480
你认为她怎么样？
What do you think of her?

306
00:23:09,590 --> 00:23:13,320
很温柔、易相处，是那种男人
喜欢占、而且去占她便宜的…
Soft. Easy. The kind men like 
to take advantage of...

307
00:23:13,430 --> 00:23:15,150
女人。
and do.

308
00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:17,200
你拿到钱啦？
Did you get any money?

309
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:19,390
- 钱。
- 噢，没有。
- Money.
- Oh. Oh, no.

310
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:22,630
我还没决定是否接这个案子。
I haven't decided to take the case yet.

311
00:23:22,740 --> 00:23:25,230
你知道，有时你真令我感到意外。
You know, you surprise me sometimes.

312
00:23:25,340 --> 00:23:28,240
为什么？我一直是这样的。
Why? I've been around.

313
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:44,650
我…呃…
I, uh...

314
00:23:46,430 --> 00:23:48,330
希望你不介意。
hope you don't mind.

315
00:23:48,430 --> 00:23:50,220
我想我们最好谈谈。
I think we'd better talk.

316
00:23:50,330 --> 00:23:52,590
你好像是个有趣的律师。
You're a funny kind of a lawyer.

317
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,070
我是说这音乐。
The music, I mean.

318
00:23:55,170 --> 00:23:57,140
律师就不能喜欢音乐了吗？
Aren't lawyers supposed to like music?

319
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,800
唔，不是这种音乐。
Well, not that kind of music.

320
00:23:59,910 --> 00:24:03,710
哦，那我就承认好了，
我是个有趣的律师。
Oh. I guess that settles it.
I'm a funny kind of lawyer.

321
00:24:03,810 --> 00:24:05,640
你老家在哪里，曼尼昂夫人？
Where's your home, Mrs. Manion?

322
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:08,370
你在哪儿上的学？
你在哪儿长大的？
Where did you go to school?
Where did you live when you were young?

323
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:11,750
没有什么特别固定的地方，
我们总是四处搬迁。
No place in particular.
We sort of moved around.

324
00:24:11,850 --> 00:24:15,180
我父亲是流动工人，流动建筑工人，
主要是建造水坝。
My father was a construction boomer.
Building dams, mostly.

325
00:24:16,420 --> 00:24:17,890
你可以喊我劳拉。
You can call me Laura.

326
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:21,230
那么你家人还健在吗，劳拉？
Is your family still alive, Laura?

327
00:24:21,330 --> 00:24:22,660
不在了。
No.

328
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:25,030
我不知道，我应该有香烟的，
不知道放哪儿了。
I don't know. I have some 
cigarettes around here someplace.

329
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,290
- 你想抽烟吗？
- 不，我是想给你找一根。
- Do you want a cigarette?
- No, I want to offer you one.

330
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,800
- 你可以帮我点上。
- 噢，当然。
- You could light it for me.
- Oh, yes.

331
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:34,540
给你。
Here.

332
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:36,730
和你丈夫的一样哈。
That's just like your husband's.

333
00:24:39,550 --> 00:24:41,710
他给了我这个因为我喜欢他用的那种。
He gave me this because I liked the one he had.

334
00:24:41,810 --> 00:24:44,480
他就是这样，总是送我礼物。
He's like that. 
He gives me presents all the time.

335
00:24:44,580 --> 00:24:47,910
- 你们婚姻很幸福？
- 是的。
- Do you have a happy marriage?
- Yes.

336
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:51,790
那么你的第一次婚姻出了什么问题？
What went wrong with the first marriage?

337
00:24:51,890 --> 00:24:55,020
唔，问题出在我喜欢上了曼尼。
Well, what when wrong is when I went for Manny.

338
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:57,100
哇喔，你可够坦诚的。
Well, that's honest enough.

339
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:00,890
当然不只是因为这个。
就像我刚才说的，我习惯了四处为家，可是…
It was more than just that.
Like I said, I grew up on the move, and...

340
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,560
杰克――就是我的第一个丈夫――
杰克不喜欢搬家。
Jack-- that was my first husband--
Jack didn't like to move.

341
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:06,930
甚至有好的机会，他都不愿意迁居。
He wouldn't even take a transfer 
when he had the chance.

342
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:09,010
我感到很无聊。
I was really bored.

343
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:12,670
曼尼喜欢动。只要有机会，
我们就一直东奔西走。
Manny likes to go. We're always going 
whenever we get the chance.

344
00:25:12,780 --> 00:25:15,800
我们到过许多地方。
我感到口渴。
We've been all over.
I'm thirsty.

345
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:17,970
要水呢，还是来杯啤酒？
Water, or would a beer do?

346
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:20,750
我想啤酒最好了。
I think a beer would do fine.

347
00:25:20,850 --> 00:25:23,050
梅达，给我拿瓶啤酒来，行吗？
Maida, bring me a bottle of beer, will you?

348
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:27,390
- 你结婚了吗？
- 没有。
- Are you married?
- No.

349
00:25:28,630 --> 00:25:30,890
不错啊。
That's nice.

350
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:33,790
你没结婚，一个人守着
这么大的房子干什么呢？
What do you do alone in this house 
if you aren't married?

351
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:36,630
唔，这是祖上留下来的住宅，
我是这个家族的最后一位。
Well, it's a family home, 
and I'm the last of the family.

352
00:25:36,740 --> 00:25:38,640
- 给你啤酒。
- 谢谢。
- There you are.
- Thank you.

353
00:25:40,170 --> 00:25:42,570
- 你不来一杯吗？
- 不，现在不喝。
- Aren't you having one?
- No, not right now.

354
00:25:44,340 --> 00:25:46,240
给你。
There you are.

355
00:25:46,350 --> 00:25:49,470
能不能用那个烟灰缸给毛毛也来点儿？
他喜欢喝啤酒。
Could Muff have a little 
in that ashtray? He loves beer.

356
00:25:49,580 --> 00:25:52,210
你想给你的小狗喝啤酒？
You want a beer for the dog?

357
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,290
好吧，给你。
Well, here we are.

358
00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:01,590
喝完他就该睡了。
He'll go to sleep now.

359
00:26:04,930 --> 00:26:07,360
- 他是不是很乖巧？
- 是的。
- Isn't he cute?
- Yeah.

360
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:09,430
怎么样？你准备好了吗？
How about it? Are you ready?

361
00:26:11,270 --> 00:26:14,500
我的意思是，你准备好
告诉我案子的情况了吗？
I mean, are you ready 
to tell me the story?

362
00:26:14,610 --> 00:26:16,510
我知道你什么意思。
I know what you mean.

363
00:26:17,980 --> 00:26:21,210
好吧，那么你就把和州警谈过的
所有事情都和我谈谈吧，
Now, suppose you tell me everything 
you told the state police...

364
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:24,250
还有你没有告诉州警的所有事情。
plus everything you didn't tell the state police.

365
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:29,590
- 从何谈起？
- 你什么时候离开家去奎尔的酒吧的？
- Where should I begin?
- When did you leave for Quill's bar?

366
00:26:29,690 --> 00:26:33,150
吃完晚饭后就去了，
我想大约在8点半左右。
Right after dinner. 
About 8:30, I guess.

367
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:35,590
曼尼从射击场回家时已经很晚了，
Manny was late getting home 
from the firing range...

368
00:26:35,690 --> 00:26:38,460
于是我们一起吃了晚饭，
然后他就倒头睡了。
so we had dinner, 
he laid down and went to sleep.

369
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:41,360
我几乎一整天都闷在车房内，所以我就…
I hadn't been out of the trailer all day, so...

370
00:26:41,470 --> 00:26:44,160
我带上毛毛和一只便携灯，走路去了酒吧。
I took Muff and a flashlight 
and walked over to the bar.

371
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:47,100
我要了一杯酒，玩了会儿弹球机。
I bought a drink and played the pinball machine.

372
00:26:47,210 --> 00:26:50,700
- 酒吧里人很多吗？
- 唔…不多。
- Many people in the bar?
- Mm-mm. Not many.

373
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:53,400
巴尼走了过来，让我和他比赛游戏。
Barney came over and challenged me to a game.

374
00:26:53,510 --> 00:26:56,680
- 输了就喝酒，你知道？
- 你和巴尼很熟吗？
- For drinks, you know?
- How well did you know Barney?

375
00:26:56,780 --> 00:27:00,450
唔，酒吧是他开的，
曼尼和我有时会去，仅此而已。
Well, he owned this bar where 
Manny and I went sometimes, that's all.

376
00:27:00,550 --> 00:27:02,520
他有没有向你调过情呢？
Had he ever made a pass at you?

377
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:04,920
没有，从没有这样的事。
No. Nothing like that at all.

378
00:27:05,020 --> 00:27:07,620
那晚他喝了很多吗？
Was he drinking heavily that night?

379
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:11,530
看上去没有，至少他和我玩球时看不出来。
Didn't seem to be. At least 
not when we were playing pinball.

380
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:14,390
你在那儿就一直和他在一起吗？
Were you with him the whole time you were there?

381
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,560
不，还有其他人也在玩。
No, there were other people playing too.

382
00:27:16,670 --> 00:27:19,160
你是什么时候离开酒吧的？
And what time did you leave the bar?

383
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:22,670
嗯，我想大约在11点左右。
Oh, about 11:00, I guess.

384
00:27:22,780 --> 00:27:25,970
我从边门离开的。
毛毛带着便携灯，
I left by the side door.
Muff was carrying the flashlight.

385
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:28,100
他用嘴巴夹着。他太乖了，
He carries it in his mouth. He's so cute...

386
00:27:28,210 --> 00:27:29,910
走在前面用便携灯开路。
running along ahead with the light shining.

387
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:33,010
- 他清醒吗？
- 毛毛？当然他很清醒。
- Was he sober?
- Muff? Of course he was sober.

388
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:34,810
噢，你这是开玩笑，是吗？
Oh, you're joking now, aren't you?

389
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:38,190
是的，我是开玩笑。请继续。
Yes, I'm joking. Go on.

390
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:40,820
这时，巴尼不知从哪儿冒了出来，
Well, Barney came from somewhere.

391
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,690
不是从我离开的那道门。
Not the door I left by.

392
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,590
他说他和我同路，可以开车送我回家。
And he said he was going my way 
and he could drive me home.

393
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:49,630
他说夜里经常有野熊出没，
我不应该独自走回家。
He said the bears had been prowling 
around, and I oughtn't to walk home.

394
00:27:49,740 --> 00:27:52,030
野熊在夜里从林子里出来觅食。
The bears come out of the woods at night to scavenge.

395
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:54,110
但是它们不会伤害到谁，不是吗？
They're harmless enough, aren't they?

396
00:27:54,210 --> 00:27:56,770
是的，要是在白天我也不会感到害怕，
Yeah, I suppose I wouldn't have been 
afraid in the daylight...

397
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:59,070
但是夜里就不一样了，你知道。
but the dark isn't the same.

398
00:27:59,180 --> 00:28:02,170
是的，我理解。
于是你就坐进了巴尼的车里……
Yes, I know. I know.
Now, you got into Barney's car--

399
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,580
我坐了进去，他开着车，
直接回了停放车房的公园。
I got in and he drove 
straight to the trailer park.

400
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:07,780
- 他没提什么事吗？
- 没有，没说什么。
- He made overtures?
- No, nothing.

401
00:28:07,890 --> 00:28:10,880
当我们到达公园时，
自动大门已经关上了。
When we got to the trailer park, 
the auto gate was closed.

402
00:28:10,990 --> 00:28:14,620
莱蒙先生大概会在11点
或稍晚一点关上大门。
Mr. Lemon closes it about 11:00 
or a little after.

403
00:28:14,730 --> 00:28:17,290
于是我就谢了巴尼，想从车里出来，
So I thanked Barney and started 
to get out of the car...

404
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:20,230
但是他说我没必要走一段路，
but he said that there wasn't 
any need for me to walk...

405
00:28:20,330 --> 00:28:23,130
他可以从另一条道送我进公园。
that he could drive me 
into the park on another road.

406
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,400
我不知道还有另一条道，但是…
I didn't know there was another road, but...

407
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:28,340
没容我回答愿不愿意，他就接着开了。
he drove on before I could say yes or no.

408
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:31,000
- 你害怕了吗？
- 没有。
- Were you alarmed?
- No.

409
00:28:31,110 --> 00:28:33,140
我通常不害怕男人。
I'm not usually afraid of men.

410
00:28:33,250 --> 00:28:36,810
不管怎么说，他没碰过我，
甚至一路上他都没说什么。
And anyway, he hadn't touched me 
or even said anything out of the way.

411
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:40,650
唔，女人是不是都有某种天生的直觉，
Well, doesn't a woman sort of instinctively know...

412
00:28:40,750 --> 00:28:42,310
会感受到不怀好意的男人？
when a fellow's on the make?

413
00:28:42,420 --> 00:28:45,390
噢，当然，我经常碰到这样的男人。
Oh, sure, but that's only usual with me.

414
00:28:45,490 --> 00:28:48,950
我是说，各种各样的男人，
从我还是孩子时就见过。
With men, I mean. Almost all men.
Ever since I was a kid.

415
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:51,500
比如说你，你也有兴趣……
You, for instance. You're interested...

416
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,500
但是没有理由要害怕你。
but there's no reason to be afraid of you.

417
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,620
巴尼也给我这样的感觉。
It was like that with Barney.

418
00:28:55,730 --> 00:28:57,900
噢，曼尼昂夫人，请相信我，
我对你一点也没有……
Well, Mrs. Manion, believe me,
I'm not in the least--

419
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,200
叫我劳拉。
Call me Laura.

420
00:29:01,710 --> 00:29:06,580
劳拉，我的兴趣仅限于
帮助你的丈夫，没有别的。
Laura, I'm only interested 
in helping your husband. Nothing more.

421
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:09,150
我不是说你想怎么样。
I don't mean you'd try anything.

422
00:29:09,250 --> 00:29:13,010
我只是说你…你看我的样子。
I just mean it's--it's the way 
you look at me.

423
00:29:14,690 --> 00:29:17,020
唔，不看着你那倒是很难。
It would be very difficult 
not to look at you.

424
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:19,920
哦，你是说我的穿着吗？
你不喜欢吗？
Oh, the way I dress, you mean?
You don't like it?

425
00:29:20,030 --> 00:29:22,790
噢，我喜欢，很喜欢。
Oh, I love it. I just love it.

426
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:26,960
噢，我们还是言归正传吧。
Now, we'd better keep moving 
along with this thing.

427
00:29:27,070 --> 00:29:31,020
那么，那晚你穿的什么？
Now, how were you dressed that night?

428
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:33,870
噢，像这样的一件厚运动衫和一条裙子。
Oh, in a sweater like this and a skirt.

429
00:29:33,970 --> 00:29:36,410
其它的呢…还有什么？
And the rest-- what about that?

430
00:29:36,510 --> 00:29:40,810
内衣吗？我穿了连身薄衬衣、短衬裤和胸罩。
Underneath? I had on a slip and panties and a bra.

431
00:29:40,910 --> 00:29:43,640
- 没系腰带？
- 我不需要腰带。
- No girdle?
- I don't need a girdle.

432
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:45,610
你认为我需要系腰带吗？
Do you think I do?

433
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:49,780
我不知道，我哪知道。
我怎么会知……
I don't know. I don't know.
How should I--

434
00:29:49,890 --> 00:29:53,120
听着，我只关心一些事实，
Look, I'm only concerned with a few facts...

435
00:29:53,130 --> 00:29:55,620
那些可能有助于我
替你丈夫进行辩护的事实。
that might be of help to me 
in the defense of your husband.

436
00:29:55,730 --> 00:29:58,320
- 仅此而已。
- 那好，我不系腰带。
- That's all.
- Well, I don't wear one.

437
00:29:58,430 --> 00:30:01,020
好的，没系腰带，好的。
Okay. No girdle. Okay.

438
00:30:01,130 --> 00:30:02,430
行了，接着说。
All right. Go on.

439
00:30:02,530 --> 00:30:06,270
然后他就离开了大路，
拐进了林中的小径，
Well, he turned off the highway 
into a lane in the woods...

440
00:30:06,370 --> 00:30:08,640
他把车停了下来，关上了灯。
and he stopped the car and turned off the lights.

441
00:30:08,740 --> 00:30:11,370
然后他就抓住我，对我说：
And then he grabbed me, and he said...

442
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,710
“我想要强奸你。”他就是这样说的。
"I'm going to rape you," just like that.

443
00:30:13,810 --> 00:30:16,780
- 他用的这些词吗？
- 原文复述。
- Did he use those words?
- Exactly those words.

444
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:19,320
毛毛叫了起来，
于是他把他扔出了窗子。
Muff began to bark, 
so he threw him out the window.

445
00:30:19,420 --> 00:30:22,880
我可以听见小毛毛在车外呜呜直叫。
I could hear little Muffy whining 
outside the car all through it.

446
00:30:22,990 --> 00:30:26,520
巴尼开始试图占有我，
And Barney began to try to get at me...

447
00:30:26,630 --> 00:30:29,790
我奋力想把他挡开，但是他太强壮了。
and I fought him off as best I could, 
but he was terribly strong.

448
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:32,190
你喊叫了吗？你呼救了吗？
Did you cry out? Did you scream?

449
00:30:32,300 --> 00:30:34,990
在林子里面，喊叫也没什么用处。
Didn't seem to be much use 
out there in the woods.

450
00:30:35,100 --> 00:30:37,530
他开始冲着我大骂，比如…
He began to shout names at me, like...

451
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:39,970
“军中荡妇”之类的。
"Army slut" and other names.

452
00:30:40,070 --> 00:30:42,630
然后他仰着身子，用拳头猛打我。
And then he drew back 
and hit me with his fist.

453
00:30:42,740 --> 00:30:45,470
他又打了几下，我就不再挣扎了。
He hit me again, and I didn't fight anymore.

454
00:30:45,580 --> 00:30:49,410
我可能已经失去了一半意识，但是…
I must have been only half-conscious, but...

455
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:53,210
我知道他扯掉了我的内裤，
做了他想做的事。
I know that he tore my panties off 
and did what he wanted.

456
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:56,410
但是报纸上说医生检查过你，
Now, the newspaper said 
that a doctor examined you...

457
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,490
说他们并不认为你受到过强奸。
and said that he didn't think you'd been raped.

458
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:02,360
我不管医生怎么说。
女人不会把这样的事情弄错的。
I don't care what the doctor thought.
A woman doesn't mistake these things.

459
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:05,450
好吧，好吧。请继续。
All right. All right. Now, go ahead.

460
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:08,800
然后，我…
Well, I--

461
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:11,930
我不确定接着发生了什么，
我肯定晕过去了。但是…
I don't know exactly what happened then.
I must've fainted. But...

462
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:14,230
接下来我所记得的事是，
车子又动了起来。
the next thing I remember, 
the car was moving.

463
00:31:14,340 --> 00:31:17,140
巴尼开得很快，
Barney was driving very fast...

464
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:19,370
他喘着粗气，
and he was breathing hard...

465
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:22,910
丑陋的喘气声。
an ugly, gasping sound.

466
00:31:23,020 --> 00:31:25,510
我们又上了通往公园的主路，
We were on the main road to the trailer park...

467
00:31:25,620 --> 00:31:28,420
他在大门旁疾转车身，停了下来。
and he swung in by the gate and stopped.

468
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:32,890
我打开车门想下车，
毛毛衔着便携灯先跳了下去。
I opened the door to get out.
Muffy jumped out first with a flashlight.

469
00:31:32,990 --> 00:31:34,520
嗯，等一下，
Now, wait a minute.

470
00:31:34,630 --> 00:31:37,560
我想你刚才说过在林子里
他把毛毛扔出了车外。
I thought you said he'd thrown Muff 
out of the car back in the woods.

471
00:31:37,660 --> 00:31:40,100
噢，是的，但是我们回到那儿时
毛毛也在车上。
Well, he did, but Muff was in the car 
when we got back.

472
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:42,220
他可能让毛毛回到了车上。
我记不太清了。
He must've let him back in.
I don't remember.

473
00:31:42,330 --> 00:31:45,830
好吧。你打开了车门，
毛毛先下了车。然后呢？
All right. You opened the door,
and Muff got out first. All right.

474
00:31:45,940 --> 00:31:47,730
我刚想下车，
Before I could get out...

475
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:50,210
巴尼一把抓住了我，
说他要把我所有的衣服撕掉，
Barney grabbed me and said he was gonna 
tear all my clothes off...

476
00:31:50,310 --> 00:31:51,900
并又开始向我袭击。
and attacked me again.

477
00:31:52,010 --> 00:31:55,340
我挣脱开他逃了出来。
我看见毛毛穿过了篱笆上的一个开口，
I got away and ran. I could see Muff 
through an opening in the fence.

478
00:31:55,450 --> 00:31:58,580
他衔着便携灯，来来回回地奔跑着。
He was scooting back and forth with a flashlight.

479
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:02,850
巴尼从背后抓住了我，我摔倒在地。
Barney caught me from behind, 
and I fell to the ground.

480
00:32:02,950 --> 00:32:05,790
他压在我上面，又开始用拳头打我。
He fell on top of me and began 
to beat me again with his fists.

481
00:32:05,890 --> 00:32:07,720
我想他可能会杀了我。
I thought he was going to kill me.

482
00:32:07,830 --> 00:32:12,420
我大声尖叫，不知怎的
我又站了起来开始猛跑。
I screamed and somehow got 
to my feet again and ran.

483
00:32:12,530 --> 00:32:14,430
我跑过篱笆门，
I went through the opening in the fence...

484
00:32:14,530 --> 00:32:17,560
跟着毛毛，他一直带着便携灯跑在我前面。
and followed Muffy, who was running 
along ahead with the flashlight.

485
00:32:17,670 --> 00:32:20,600
我跟着便携灯的灯光，
直到来到我们的车房跟前。
And I kept following the light 
until he led me to our trailer.

486
00:32:20,710 --> 00:32:22,770
那么你再没见过巴尼了吗？
And you didn't see Barney again?

487
00:32:22,870 --> 00:32:25,370
无论死活，我再也没见过他。
Never laid eyes on him again, dead or alive.

488
00:32:26,710 --> 00:32:28,510
好吧，我…呃…
Well, I, uh--

489
00:32:28,610 --> 00:32:30,640
我想暂且到此为止吧。
I think that's enough for now.

490
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:33,950
我有的是时间，只要你愿意。
I've got lots of time. All you want.

491
00:32:35,550 --> 00:32:37,890
- 我怎样才能联系到你？
- 我仍然住在雷鸣湾，
- Where can I reach you?
- I'm still in Thunder Bay...

492
00:32:37,990 --> 00:32:40,150
但是上午我可以开车进城来。
but I can drive down again in the morning.

493
00:32:43,730 --> 00:32:46,860
- 还有什么要补充吗？
- 没有。
- Was there something else?
- No.

494
00:32:59,240 --> 00:33:02,480
- 谢谢你允许我放那些唱片。
- 噢，不用客气。
- Thanks for letting me play the records.
- Oh, you're very welcome.

495
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:04,480
非常感谢，再见。
Thanks a lot. Bye.

496
00:33:07,490 --> 00:33:10,460
- 那是谁？
- 案子里的女人。
- Who's that?
- The lady in the case.

497
00:33:14,390 --> 00:33:16,920
- 你不想接这个案子，哈？
- 唔，我不知道。
- You're not going to take the case?
- I don't know.

498
00:33:17,030 --> 00:33:20,000
那得看明天曼尼昂会跟我说些什么。
That depends on what Manion
has to tell me tomorrow.

499
00:33:20,100 --> 00:33:22,530
他正绞尽脑汁呢。
He's thinking things out.

500
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:24,690
噢，是啊，这样就对了。
Oh, well, that's more like it.

501
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:28,800
听着，要是我接了这个案子，
我想你也加入进来。
Now, if I take the case, 
I want you in it.

502
00:33:28,910 --> 00:33:31,310
我？加入一起凶杀大案？
Me, in a big murder case?

503
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:37,710
噢，保利，让这样一个泡在威士忌里的
酒鬼插手案子，会毁了你的。
The sight of this whisky-drinking man 
at the lawyer's table would ruin you.

504
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:40,250
我需要你。
I need you.

505
00:33:40,350 --> 00:33:41,820
你真心的吗？
You mean that?

506
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,950
他不真心就不会邀请你了。
Why else would he say it?

507
00:33:45,420 --> 00:33:48,520
我很高兴在庭外和你一起工作，但是…
I'd be glad to work with you 
outside of the courtroom, but...

508
00:33:48,630 --> 00:33:51,490
- 不能在法庭内。
- 随你的便。
- not in the courtroom.
- Suit yourself about that.

509
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:54,530
不管怎样，我都指望着依靠你了。
Either way, I'm gonna have 
to be able to depend on you.

510
00:33:56,570 --> 00:33:58,470
你会把酒戒了吗？
Will you lay off the booze?

511
00:34:04,010 --> 00:34:06,140
我不知道。
I don't know.

512
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:08,240
我不知道能否做到，保利。
I don't know about that, Paulie.

513
00:34:08,350 --> 00:34:10,370
你为什么不知道？
Why don't you know?

514
00:34:12,820 --> 00:34:15,480
你认为我戒不了酒？
Do you think I couldn't lay off the booze?

515
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:18,490
试过没有？
Ever tried it?

516
00:34:20,590 --> 00:34:22,360
试试看。
Try it.

517
00:34:26,470 --> 00:34:29,730
我从未接触过谋杀大案，
I never been on a big murder case.

518
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:32,460
这辈子没碰到过一次。
Not once in all my life.

519
00:34:32,570 --> 00:34:34,800
全看你的了，帕内尔。
It's up to you, Parn.

520
00:34:41,550 --> 00:34:43,950
今晚你会过来吗？
Will you be around tonight?

521
00:34:44,050 --> 00:34:47,350
是的。是的，我会过来。
Yeah. Yeah, I'll be around.

522
00:34:56,530 --> 00:34:59,120
你知道，梅达，亲爱的，
You know, Maida, darling...

523
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:02,170
我做得到，
I might manage it.

524
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:05,581
我又会成为一个货真价实的律师。
I might manage to be a real lawyer again.

525
00:35:06,700 --> 00:35:09,200
至少先做一阵子再说。
For a little while, anyway.

526
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,410
我努力回想着，
I tried remembering.

527
00:35:14,510 --> 00:35:18,280
但仍有些细节我记不起来了。
There were still some pieces missing.

528
00:35:18,380 --> 00:35:21,610
我记得…
I remember...

529
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:25,080
我拿着枪去了奎尔的酒吧，
going to Quill's bar with a gun...

530
00:35:25,190 --> 00:35:28,550
我记得吧台后面奎尔的那张脸，
and I remember Quill's face behind the bar...

531
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:33,190
但是其它的事情我就记不起来了，
甚至都不知道怎样回的家。
but I don't remember anything else, 
not even going home.

532
00:35:33,190 --> 00:35:37,530
你不记得怎样开的枪吗？
打了五枪，那么大噪音可很难忘啊。
Don't you remember firing the gun?
Five shots, that's a lot of noise to forget.

533
00:35:37,630 --> 00:35:41,470
是的，我记得听见了枪声，
但是那好像跟我没有关系似的。
Yeah, I remember hearing shots, 
but they don't seem connected with me.

534
00:35:41,570 --> 00:35:46,600
它们听上去很遥远，
像是另外一个人开的枪。
They seemed far away, like 
somebody else was doing the shooting.

535
00:35:51,150 --> 00:35:55,450
曼尼昂中尉，我决定接手你的案子。
Lt. Manion, I'll take your case.

536
00:35:55,550 --> 00:35:57,810
噢，谢谢。谢谢你，比格勒先生。
Oh, thanks. Thanks, Mr. Biegler.

537
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:01,080
好的。那么现在我们来聊聊费用问题。
All right. Now, there's 
the little matter of the fee.

538
00:36:01,190 --> 00:36:03,320
三千美元，还是相当公道的吧，是吗？
Three thousand dollars.
That's reasonable enough, isn't it?

539
00:36:03,420 --> 00:36:07,020
噢，没问题，非常公道。但是我得
以后再付给你，现在我一文不名。
Oh, sure. More than reasonable. I'll 
have to pay later. Right now I'm broke.

540
00:36:07,130 --> 00:36:09,720
- 你什么？
- 我身无分文，一无所有。
- You're what?
- I'm broke. I'm flat busted.

541
00:36:09,830 --> 00:36:11,820
别说三千美元，就是三个美元我也拿不出来。
I don't have three dollars, much less 3,000.

542
00:36:11,930 --> 00:36:16,030
- 你可以筹集一点吗？
- 噢，可以的，一旦我出了监狱。
- Can you raise it?
- Oh, yes, as soon as I get out of jail.

543
00:36:16,140 --> 00:36:19,400
下个星期的发薪日，
But next week's payday.

544
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:22,310
我可以先付你150美元，
I'll be able to give you $150...

545
00:36:22,410 --> 00:36:25,270
如果你能把我弄出去，
我会给你打个剩余款项的期票。
and if you get me off, I'll give you 
a promissory note for the rest.

546
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:29,050
好吧，你知道要是我先得不到
一半费用的话，我就会撒手不管了？
All right, now suppose I don't go along
with you unless you pay me half the fee?

547
00:36:30,450 --> 00:36:33,220
呃，那我就去找法庭指定的律师好了。
Well, I'll have to take a lawyer the court appoints.

548
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:37,020
我有了辩护借口，对吗？精神错乱。
I got my defense now, right? Insanity.

549
00:36:37,130 --> 00:36:39,820
我想我先四处想想办法，
把你保出去再说。
I think I'll stick around, 
make damn sure you get off.

550
00:36:39,930 --> 00:36:43,020
- 该如何做呢？
- 我们需要个精神病专家。
- Where do we start?
- We're going to need a psychiatrist.

551
00:36:44,470 --> 00:36:48,700
你我都没什么钱，
你认为军队会帮你一把吗？
Neither of us has any money. Do you 
think the army'll stir one up for you?

552
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:51,140
我认识个五角大楼的上校，我给他写封信。
I know a colonel in the Pentagon.
I'll write a letter.

553
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,800
很好，马上写。苏罗！
Good. Do that. Sulo.

554
00:36:58,580 --> 00:37:00,240
你现在去哪儿？
Where are you going now?

555
00:37:00,350 --> 00:37:02,750
我现在先去见你的妻子。
I'm going to see your wife, for one thing.

556
00:37:02,850 --> 00:37:04,940
怎么？你昨天不是见过她了吗？
Why? Didn't you see her yesterday?

557
00:37:05,050 --> 00:37:07,020
没错，见过。
That's right. I did.

558
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:09,280
她是个漂亮女人，你的妻子。
She's a very pretty woman, your wife.

559
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:12,460
时间长了当丈夫的也会熟视无睹。
A man gets used to the way his wife looks.

560
00:37:12,560 --> 00:37:15,290
我想是的。回头见。
I guess he does. I'll see you.

561
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:27,000
“检察官”

562
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:35,110
请进！保利，请进来！
Come on in, Paulie. Come on in.

563
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:38,010
自从你从这儿搬出去以后
就没回来过，不是吗？
You haven't been in here 
since you vacated, have you?

564
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:40,550
老地方都认不出来了吧，嗯？
Hardly recognize the old place, huh?

565
00:37:40,660 --> 00:37:43,320
玛丽帮我装修的，
她刚好学完她的室内装饰课。
Mary did it for me. She just finished 
her decorators' course.

566
00:37:43,420 --> 00:37:45,620
聪明的姑娘，非常聪明的姑娘。
瞧瞧这个。
Smart girl. Very smart girl.
Look at this.

567
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:48,420
- 根据毕加索真迹印刷的画。
- 噢，真不错。
- A real, genuine Picasso print.
- That's very nice.

568
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:51,730
这个，试试这把椅子。
你动都不用动。
And here. Try this chair.
It sort of does things for you.

569
00:37:51,830 --> 00:37:53,390
坐下去。
Sit right down.

570
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:57,430
感觉很棒，是吗？
他们说对神经有好处。
Great, isn't it?
Good for the nerves, they say.

571
00:37:57,540 --> 00:37:59,870
- 怎么把它关掉？
- 这儿。
- How do you shut it off?
- Here.

572
00:37:59,970 --> 00:38:01,970
起来吧。感觉爽多啦？
Here we are. Feel better?

573
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,980
感觉快被震散了。
I feel all shook up.

574
00:38:06,650 --> 00:38:10,380
米奇，我来是为了跟你打个招呼，
我现在全权接手了曼尼昂的案子。
Mitch, I just dropped in to tell you
I've got both feet in the Manion case.

575
00:38:10,490 --> 00:38:12,610
- 你会让他认罪宽刑，是吗？
- 不。
- You're going to cop out, aren't you?
- No.

576
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:14,920
那你可犯错了，保罗，
一开庭就会结案的。
That's a mistake. 
It's open and shut.

577
00:38:15,020 --> 00:38:16,620
唔，也许吧。我们走着瞧好了。
Well, maybe. We'll see.

578
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,920
梅特兰法官还在医院里，
也许你也同意…
Judge Maitland's still in the hospital.
Maybe you'd like to agree...

579
00:38:19,030 --> 00:38:21,050
延期开庭等他回来。
to a continuance until he gets back.

580
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:23,130
如果现在就审理这个案子，
上面就会胡乱指派个法官，
If we go with the case now, 
we'll have to try before...

581
00:38:23,230 --> 00:38:25,460
我们就不得不由他来主持庭审。
some grab-bag judge they'll send in.

582
00:38:25,570 --> 00:38:27,930
- 就我而言，我希望是梅特兰法官。
- 是的，我也是。
- Me, I'd rather have Maitland.
- So would I.

583
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:31,100
但是那也意味着在开庭之前，
我的委托人得在监狱里…
But that'd also mean my client 
would lie around in jail...

584
00:38:31,210 --> 00:38:33,610
再耗上两到三个月。
for another two, three months before the trial.

585
00:38:33,710 --> 00:38:37,340
因此，要是你能收回谋杀指控，
改成一般杀人指控，
Now, if you'll drop the charge 
down to manslaughter...

586
00:38:37,450 --> 00:38:40,540
那么我就可以将他保释出来，
否则的话我不同意延期审理。
so I can get him out on bail,
we'll agree to a continuance.

587
00:38:40,550 --> 00:38:43,010
如果你仍然是地方检察官，你不会这样做吧。
You wouldn't do that if you were still D.A.

588
00:38:43,020 --> 00:38:45,180
我不知道，也许会。
I don't know. I might.

589
00:38:45,290 --> 00:38:48,250
我会的，因为那台万能的测谎仪
对他妻子进行了测试，
I might, since a big, fat 
lie detector test on his wife...

590
00:38:48,260 --> 00:38:50,620
结果证实了强奸的说法。
is giving proof to the rape story.

591
00:38:50,730 --> 00:38:53,220
- 陪审团会站在他一边的。
- 你怎么知道测谎仪的结…
- He'd have the jury with him.
- How did you know what the lie--

592
00:38:54,260 --> 00:38:56,030
- 你诈我的，是吗？
- 是的，你上当了。
- I bit, didn't I?
- Yeah, you did.

593
00:38:56,130 --> 00:38:58,760
不管怎么说，测谎仪的测试结果
是不能作为可接受的证据的。
Anyway, the result of a lie detector 
test isn't admissible evidence.

594
00:38:58,870 --> 00:39:02,360
- 你不能用它。
- 是不能用，但是它具有道德上的分量。
- You can't use it.
- No, but it carries moral weight.

595
00:39:03,940 --> 00:39:06,030
米奇，我要是你，
我不会太喜欢坐那把椅子。
Mitch, I wouldn't sit 
in that chair too much.

596
00:39:06,140 --> 00:39:08,230
它会把人的脑瓜颠松的。
It could shake a fellow's brains loose.

597
00:39:08,340 --> 00:39:10,330
我们回头再见。
I'll see you later.

598
00:39:19,420 --> 00:39:21,350
他记得你，保罗，他喜欢你。
He remembers you, Paul. He likes you.

599
00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:23,550
他喜欢我冰箱里的啤酒。
He likes the beer in my icebox.

600
00:39:23,660 --> 00:39:25,950
今天这身行头又有何贵干呢？
要去猎杀野牛？
What's the occasion today.
A buffalo hunt?

601
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:28,900
这些都是在亚利桑那时买的，
我们曾在那儿驻防。
I bought these in Arizona 
when we were stationed there.

602
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,020
穿着潇洒吗？我觉着穿着很潇洒。
Aren't they smart? I think they're very smart.

603
00:39:31,130 --> 00:39:33,190
这儿，坐到我车里去。
Here, we can sit in my car.

604
00:39:40,340 --> 00:39:42,100
给你。
Here you are.

605
00:39:43,510 --> 00:39:44,980
到后面去，毛毛。
Here you go, Muff.

606
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:47,270
我又想起了几件事。
Several things have occurred to me.

607
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:49,480
那些，呃…
The, uh--

608
00:39:49,580 --> 00:39:53,020
那些被巴尼・奎尔撕烂的内衣…
The undergarments Barney Quill tore off--

609
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:55,490
现在在哪儿？在警察那儿？
Who has them now? The police?

610
00:39:55,590 --> 00:39:57,560
你是说我的内裤吗？
You mean my panties?

611
00:39:57,660 --> 00:39:59,720
好吧。你的内裤呢？
All right. Your panties.

612
00:39:59,830 --> 00:40:01,660
后来我也没再见到过。
I haven't seen them since.

613
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,490
我把撕烂的裙子和运动衫交给了警察，然后…
I gave the torn skirt and sweater 
to the police, and then...

614
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:07,230
和他们一道，回到那条深入林子的小径，
去寻找我的内裤，
I went with them up that lane into
the woods to look for the panties...

615
00:40:07,340 --> 00:40:09,960
但是我们什么也没找到，除了我的眼镜。
but we couldn't find anything but my glasses.

616
00:40:10,070 --> 00:40:13,730
你的眼镜？你是说发生这一切的时候，
你一直戴着眼镜？
Your glasses? You mean you were 
wearing glasses through all that?

617
00:40:13,740 --> 00:40:16,470
不，眼镜在盒子里，我拿在手上。
No, I had them in a case in my hand.

618
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:19,380
我阅读时戴，还有玩弹球机之类的也戴着。
I wear them for reading, 
playing pinball, things like that.

619
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:21,910
我想是在挣扎着下车时丢掉的。
I must have tried to get 
out of the car and dropped them.

620
00:40:23,950 --> 00:40:26,220
你可能有兴趣知道…
You might be interested to know...

621
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:29,780
你的测谎结果对你有利。
that your lie detector test 
turned out in your favor.

622
00:40:29,890 --> 00:40:32,520
当然对我有利，
我早该告诉你会是这样的结果。
Of course it did.
I could've told you it would.

623
00:40:32,630 --> 00:40:35,600
- 你一点都不担心吗？
- 不担心。
- You weren't worried about it?
- No.

624
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:37,930
我为什么要担心？
Why should I be?

625
00:40:38,030 --> 00:40:41,470
你想不想担心什么事情呢？
Would you like to have something to worry about?

626
00:40:41,570 --> 00:40:42,830
问得真可笑。
Silly.

627
00:40:42,940 --> 00:40:46,070
譬如说你丈夫正透过
他牢房的窗户望着我们？
Like your husband watching us 
from his cell window?

628
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,870
好了。
All right.

629
00:40:50,980 --> 00:40:53,780
好了，看到就看到了吧。
All right, let's have it.

630
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:57,010
- 他向你说什么了吗？
- 说了很多。
- Did he say something to you?
- Just enough.

631
00:40:57,120 --> 00:41:01,020
- 你怕他吗？
- 是的。
- Are you afraid of him?
- Yes.

632
00:41:01,580 --> 00:41:04,710
这就是为什么你自愿接受
测谎仪的测试吗？为了给他看？
Is that why you volunteered 
for a lie detector test? For him?

633
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:09,120
- 是的。
- 他有妒忌的理由吗？
- Yeah.
- Does he have reason to be jealous?

634
00:41:10,230 --> 00:41:12,220
在我们结婚之前，他就经常妒忌。
He was jealous even before we were married.

635
00:41:12,330 --> 00:41:14,800
我应该早就料到会变成这样的。
I should've known how it would be.

636
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:17,770
有意思的是，他还喜欢拿我炫耀。
It's funny, though. He likes to show me off.

637
00:41:17,870 --> 00:41:20,100
他喜欢我打扮得漂漂亮亮。
He likes me to dress the way I do.

638
00:41:20,210 --> 00:41:23,770
可是要是男人的目光都集中到我身上，
他又会变得很愤怒。
And then he gets furious 
if a man pays any attention to me.

639
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:26,040
我曾想过要离开他，但是我做不到。
I've tried to leave him, but I can't.

640
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:28,410
他一乞求，我就让步了。
He begs, I give in.

641
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:33,080
好了，如果你以为我忘了
刚才的提问，我没有忘。
Now, if you think I've forgotten 
my question, I haven't.

642
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:36,160
- 可我忘了。
- 好吧，
- I have.
- All right.

643
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:38,560
那我再问一遍：
Then I'll ask it again.

644
00:41:38,660 --> 00:41:41,720
你丈夫有没有嫉妒的任何理由呢？
Does your husband have any reason to be jealous?

645
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:44,820
没有。
No.

646
00:41:44,930 --> 00:41:47,700
一次也没有，从来没有。
Not once. Not ever.

647
00:42:15,910 --> 00:42:18,730
“雷鸣湾旅店”

648
00:43:08,960 --> 00:43:15,020
“巴尼・奎尔赢得
上半岛【密歇根】手枪比武赛”

649
00:43:59,390 --> 00:44:01,880
“通向大厅”

650
00:44:05,840 --> 00:44:07,770
嗨，喜欢这地方，是吗？
Hi. Like the place all right?

651
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:10,240
我正在看这些照片。
I was just looking at these pictures.

652
00:44:10,340 --> 00:44:13,840
- 那是巴尼・奎尔，是吗？
- 是的，巴尼・奎尔。
- That was Barney Quill, wasn't it?
- That's right. Barney Quill.

653
00:44:13,950 --> 00:44:16,380
- 我是保罗・比格勒，我是……
- 我知道你是谁。
- I'm Paul Biegler. I'm--
- I know who you are.

654
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:18,580
我在铁城见过你。
I've seen you around Iron City.

655
00:44:18,690 --> 00:44:20,550
你还没告诉我你的名字。
You didn't tell me your name.

656
00:44:20,660 --> 00:44:23,060
帕盖特。我们5点才开门。
Paquette. We don't open till 5:00.

657
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:24,680
没关系，我可以等。
That's all right. I can wait.

658
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,420
我还没发疟疾。
I don't have the shakes yet.

659
00:44:27,530 --> 00:44:30,120
那天晚上你在这儿干活，对吗？
You were on the job that night, weren't you...

660
00:44:30,230 --> 00:44:32,260
巴尼・奎尔被杀的那个晚上。
the night Barney Quill was killed.

661
00:44:32,370 --> 00:44:34,660
就像报上登的那样，我在场。
Like the newspaper said, I was present.

662
00:44:34,770 --> 00:44:38,170
你是那个在外面阻止曼尼昂中尉的人。
You were the fellow who stopped Lt. Manion outside.

663
00:44:38,270 --> 00:44:40,170
是的。
That's right.

664
00:44:40,270 --> 00:44:43,400
他用枪指着我说：
“你也想吃几颗吗，小子？”
He pointed the gun at me and said, 
"You want some too, buster?"

665
00:44:43,510 --> 00:44:46,910
你回答说“不”，因为你的名字不叫“小子”。
And you said no, because your name isn't buster.

666
00:44:47,010 --> 00:44:51,540
- 那有什么可笑的吗，比格勒先生？
- 不，我不是这个意思，对不起。
- Wasn't anything funny about it.
- No, there wasn't. I'm sorry.

667
00:44:51,650 --> 00:44:55,110
当巴尼・奎尔被杀时，
你在哪儿，帕盖特先生？
Where were you when Barney Quill 
was killed, Mr. Paquette?

668
00:44:58,260 --> 00:45:00,920
我想你不愿意聊那天晚上的事，是吗？
I gather you don't want 
to talk about that night, huh?

669
00:45:01,030 --> 00:45:03,260
没错，我不想再谈起它。
That's right. I don't want to talk about it.

670
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:06,800
但是在法庭上你还是得跟我谈，
为什么不现在就谈谈呢？
You'll have to talk to me 
about it in court. Why not now?

671
00:45:06,900 --> 00:45:09,770
因为我现在可以不谈，
这个理由够充分吗？
'Cause I don't have to now. 
Reason enough, okay?

672
00:45:09,870 --> 00:45:11,900
那好吧。
Okay.

673
00:45:13,740 --> 00:45:16,770
天哪，这个老巴尼看上去
像是个蛮主，是吗？
Boy, old Barney, he was kind of
a rugged character, wasn't he?

674
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:21,110
曾是职业拳击手，满身肌肉，
喜欢玩枪，还有……
Ex-prizefighter, muscle man,
fancy with guns, and--

675
00:45:21,220 --> 00:45:23,550
他付清了债务，开了这家清白的旅店。
He paid his debts. Ran a clean place.

676
00:45:23,650 --> 00:45:26,350
- 对我来说，我喜欢他。
- 这地方现在归你啦？
- Me, I liked him.
- You run the place now?

677
00:45:26,450 --> 00:45:30,150
不，我只是在这儿干活。
现在由玛丽掌管。
No, I just work here.
Mary's running things.

678
00:45:30,260 --> 00:45:32,490
玛丽？她是巴尼的妻子吗？
Mary? Was that Barney's wife?

679
00:45:32,590 --> 00:45:35,620
不，他没有妻子。玛丽帮他经营。
No, he didn't have a wife. Mary was his manager.

680
00:45:35,730 --> 00:45:39,670
噢，是吗。我想知道谁继承了这地方。
Oh. All right.
I wonder who's gonna inherit the place?

681
00:45:39,770 --> 00:45:43,200
- 我想是玛丽吧。
- 嗯，又是玛丽。
- Mary, I guess.
- Mary again.

682
00:45:43,300 --> 00:45:45,200
那有什么不对劲吗？
What's the matter with that?

683
00:45:45,310 --> 00:45:48,330
你的意思是玛丽有什么不对劲吗？
我可不知道玛丽有什么不对劲。
You mean, what's the matter with Mary?
I don't know what's the matter with her.

684
00:45:48,440 --> 00:45:50,540
她叫玛丽什么？
Mary what?

685
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:52,310
皮兰特，玛丽・皮兰特。
Pilant. Mary Pilant.

686
00:45:52,410 --> 00:45:56,440
她就在后面的小间里。
我们不应该在这里聊我们的顾客。
She's in the back booth.
We don't talk about our customers here.

687
00:45:56,550 --> 00:45:58,980
但是我们要聊的话，我们不聊……
But if we did--which we don't--

688
00:46:00,790 --> 00:46:03,090
那就是她，她就是玛丽・皮兰特。
That's her. That's Mary Pilant.

689
00:46:12,370 --> 00:46:16,700
- 你认识曼尼昂中尉的妻子吗？
- 当然认识，我也认识中尉本人。
- Do you know Lt. Manion's wife?
- Sure. I know the lieutenant too.

690
00:46:16,800 --> 00:46:19,670
他是个好的长官，她人也不错。
He's a good officer. She's all right too.

691
00:46:19,770 --> 00:46:22,040
很友善，好孩子。
Friendly. Good kid.

692
00:46:22,140 --> 00:46:24,080
你知道什么？住嘴！
What do you know about it? Knock it off.

693
00:46:24,180 --> 00:46:27,080
我又没说什么。她是个迷人的女子。
这样说有什么不对吗？
I didn't mean anything. She's a dish.
What's the matter with that?

694
00:46:27,180 --> 00:46:30,210
你想给这位律师留下错误的印象吗？
Do you want this lawyer to get wrong ideas?

695
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:32,910
中尉会有多少机会呢，麦卡锡先生？
What chance has the lieutenant got, Mr. McCarthy?

696
00:46:33,020 --> 00:46:38,120
我要说机会很大，如果有多几个
你这样的了解他的证人的话。
Pretty good, I'd say, with a couple 
of character witnesses like you.

697
00:46:38,230 --> 00:46:41,350
我很愿意帮他，我当然愿意。
但是我们马上要搬走了。
I'd like to help him out. I sure would.
But we're moving out.

698
00:46:41,460 --> 00:46:43,520
整个部队，去柏林。
The whole outfit. Berlin.

699
00:46:45,370 --> 00:46:48,930
告诉我，那个旅店里的女孩是谁？
Tell me, who is this babe at the hotel?

700
00:46:49,040 --> 00:46:53,340
她叫玛丽・皮兰特，
她是奎尔的私人财产。
Name's Mary Pilant.
She was Quill's private property.

701
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:09,600
- 你想要个桌子吗，先生？
- 是的。
- Would you like a table, sir?
- Yes, please.

702
00:47:15,110 --> 00:47:18,480
- 你是一个人吗？
- 我在等另外两位。
- Will you be alone?
- I'll be joined by two others.

703
00:47:18,580 --> 00:47:21,950
- 要把你帽子挂起来吗？
- 噢，谢谢，非常感谢。
- May I take your hat?
- Thank you very much.

704
00:47:29,630 --> 00:47:33,220
- 指甲修得怎样？
- 你想要知道谁我都可以告诉你。
- How was the manicure?
- Ask me any questions about anybody.

705
00:47:33,330 --> 00:47:38,300
- 我探到了所有消息。
- 那你跟我说说有个叫玛丽・皮兰特的女人吧。
- I've got all the dope.
- Can you tell me about Mary Pilant?

706
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:42,230
小菜一碟。玛丽・皮兰特可能是也可能不是…
Easy. Mary Pilant may or may not have been...

707
00:47:42,330 --> 00:47:44,530
已故的巴尼・奎尔的情人。
the mistress of the late B. Quill.

708
00:47:44,640 --> 00:47:47,230
指甲修剪师支持情人的说法，
The manicurist is in favor 
of the mistress theory...

709
00:47:47,240 --> 00:47:49,210
而美发师却反对这种说法。
but the hairdresser's against it.

710
00:47:49,310 --> 00:47:53,940
但是，他们都一致同意
那俩人的关系的确有点不明不白。
However, they both agree that some sort 
of hanky-panky must have been going on.

711
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:56,170
- 等会儿再说。
- 要菜单吗？
- To be continued.
- Menu?

712
00:47:56,270 --> 00:47:58,000
谢谢。
Thank you.

713
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,890
- 她很漂亮哈？
- 是啊，很漂亮。
- Pretty, huh?
- Yes, very pretty.

714
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:03,860
继续，接着说。
What? What?

715
00:48:03,970 --> 00:48:06,330
唔…是这样，有一种说法是…
Anyway, there's one story that says that...

716
00:48:06,440 --> 00:48:09,410
那一晚巴尼攻击曼尼昂夫人，
从某种意义上来说…
Barney's wild night with 
Mrs. Manion was somehow...

717
00:48:09,510 --> 00:48:11,500
是由玛丽・皮兰特引起的。
triggered by Mary Pilant.

718
00:48:11,610 --> 00:48:15,480
似乎她当时和一个当兵的在一起，
到处闲逛，引得巴尼怒不可遏。
Seems she'd been running around with 
some soldier, and Barney blew his stack.

719
00:48:15,580 --> 00:48:18,980
- 巴尼把自己灌得烂醉，最后就爆发了。
- 玛丽・皮兰特是本地人吗？
- He got tanked up and exploded.
- Is Mary Pilant local?

720
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:21,420
不，她是加拿大人，巴尼带她来这儿的，
No, she's a Canadian.
Barney brought her in here...

721
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:25,150
可能是为了装点门面，
她留了下来接着帮他打理生意。
to sort of dress up the place, 
and she stayed on to manage it for him.

722
00:48:25,260 --> 00:48:27,850
- 看起来她干得不赖。
- 岂止不赖，
- Looks like she's done all right.
- Better than all right.

723
00:48:27,960 --> 00:48:30,690
- 旅店快是她的了。
- 哦？
- She's in for the estate.
- Oh?

724
00:48:30,790 --> 00:48:33,190
她看上去不像个坏人，不是吗？
She doesn't look like a bad sort, does she?

725
00:48:33,300 --> 00:48:35,360
嗯？哪里？
Hmm? Where?

726
00:48:35,470 --> 00:48:38,770
你什么意思，“哪里”？
那个拿着菜单的美人就是。
What do you mean, "where"?
The pretty one with the menus.

727
00:48:38,870 --> 00:48:40,500
就是这儿的那个姑娘吗？
This girl right here?

728
00:48:46,780 --> 00:48:48,800
唔，皮兰特小姐，我可以自我介绍一下吗？
Miss Pilant, may I introduce myself?

729
00:48:48,910 --> 00:48:51,140
我是保罗・比格勒，曼尼昂中尉的律师，
I'm Paul Biegler, attorney for Lt. Manion...

730
00:48:51,250 --> 00:48:53,580
这位是拉特利奇小姐，
这位是麦卡锡先生，都是我的同事。
and this is Miss Rutledge 
and Mr. McCarthy, my associates.

731
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:56,410
- 你好！
- 我想你能不能和我们坐一分钟呢？
- How do you do.
- Could you sit with us for a minute?

732
00:48:56,520 --> 00:48:58,550
- 好的，我可以坐一会儿。
- 谢谢。
- Yes, I can take a minute.
- Thank you.

733
00:49:00,890 --> 00:49:04,190
我想向你了解一些事情，
如果你不介意的话。
I'd like to ask you a few things, 
if you don't mind.

734
00:49:04,290 --> 00:49:06,490
什么样的事情，比格勒先生？
What sort of things, Mr. Biegler?

735
00:49:06,600 --> 00:49:10,260
嗯，比如说你的雇主
奎尔先生是一个怎样的人。
Well, like what kind of a man
your employer was, Mr. Quill.

736
00:49:10,370 --> 00:49:13,200
- 一个非常好的人。
- 如果那是事实的话，那你如何解释…
- A very nice man.
- If that's true, how do you explain...

737
00:49:13,300 --> 00:49:15,570
发生在曼尼昂中尉妻子身上的事儿？
what happened with Lt. Manion's wife?

738
00:49:15,670 --> 00:49:18,570
我压根不知道在曼尼昂中尉妻子身上
发生了什么事，
I don't know what happened 
with Lt. Manion's wife...

739
00:49:18,680 --> 00:49:21,140
所以我也真的没有什么
可以解释的了，不是吗？
so there really isn't anything 
for me to explain, is there?

740
00:49:21,250 --> 00:49:24,680
你对已故的奎尔先生的忠诚
非常令人动容，皮兰特小姐。
Your loyalty to the dead Mr. Quill 
is very touching, Miss Pilant.

741
00:49:24,780 --> 00:49:27,180
巴尼在这儿可以说是
人见人爱，比格勒先生。
Barney was well liked here 
by everyone, Mr. Biegler.

742
00:49:27,180 --> 00:49:30,620
噢，那么一定是人人都很有雅量，
可以无视他犯的小小过失，
It's very generous of everyone 
to overlook his faults...

743
00:49:30,620 --> 00:49:32,720
比如说强奸他人妻子之类的事。
like raping other men's wives.

744
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:35,220
原谅我失陪了。
If you'll pardon me.

745
00:49:35,330 --> 00:49:37,890
你们选好了的话，
服务小姐会过来听你们点菜。
The waitress will take your order 
when you're ready.

746
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:40,050
很高兴认识你们，比格勒先生，
Nice to have met you, Mr. Biegler...

747
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:42,390
麦卡锡先生，拉特利奇夫人。
Mr. McCarthy, Mrs. Rutledge.

748
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:47,330
你刚喝了杜松子酒，中尉。
You just drew gin, Lieutenant.

749
00:49:49,910 --> 00:49:51,810
- 二十。
- 曼尼昂？
- Twenty.
- Manion?

750
00:49:55,650 --> 00:49:57,810
- 有什么消息吗，中尉？
- 是的。
- Any word, Lieutenant?
- Yeah.

751
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:00,610
这是华盛顿来的。
This, from Washington.

752
00:50:00,720 --> 00:50:03,520
他们同意派个医生过来替我作证，
但是有个条件：
They'll let a doctor come and testify, 
but there's a string on it.

753
00:50:03,620 --> 00:50:07,720
他们想让我去底特律的
一家军队医院先做检查。
They want me to go to an army hospital
in Detroit for an examination.

754
00:50:07,830 --> 00:50:11,590
他们不明白你正在监狱里吗？
而且以你的控罪不能保释？
Doesn't the army understand that you're
in jail on a non-bailable offense?

755
00:50:11,700 --> 00:50:13,660
军队只能帮这么多忙了。
That's it, as far as the army's concerned.

756
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:16,530
我不知道该怎么做，我会想想办法的。
I don't know how I can get around this.
I'll try and think of something.

757
00:50:16,630 --> 00:50:19,970
我说，我妻子已经两天没来看我了。
你见到她了吗？
Look, my wife hasn't been here 
in two days. Have you seen her?

758
00:50:20,070 --> 00:50:23,300
- 没有，最近没见过。
- 她究竟去哪儿了？
- No, not for a while.
- Where the hell is she?

759
00:50:23,410 --> 00:50:25,340
你还是多担心担心其它事情吧，中尉。
You've got other things to worry about, Lieutenant.

760
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:28,140
我会和你妻子联系，转告她你想见她。
I'll get in touch with your wife.
I'll tell her you miss her.

761
00:50:28,250 --> 00:50:30,150
是的，请转告她。
Yeah, you tell her that.

762
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:34,080
- 谢谢，苏罗。
- 没事，保利。
- Thanks, Sulo.
- Okay, Paulie.

763
00:50:37,920 --> 00:50:40,290
我理解你的感觉，中尉。
I know just how you feel, Lieutenant.

764
00:50:40,390 --> 00:50:44,120
要是我有那样的尤物在外面的话，
我也会抓狂的。
I'd be tearing my hair out too 
if I had something like that outside.

765
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:48,030
什么样的尤物在外面？
Something like what outside?

766
00:50:48,130 --> 00:50:52,660
你知道我的意思，那种放荡无羁的尤物。
You know what I mean. Something like 
that running around on the loose.

767
00:50:58,980 --> 00:51:01,270
怎么啦，小子们，谁弄的动静？
Now, what's the big noise, buckos?

768
00:51:02,410 --> 00:51:06,610
是我，笨伯。我的肘撞在这该死的铁杠上了。
It's me, dummy. I hit my elbow 
on this lousy iron bar.

769
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:10,590
那是不是要给你些酒精搽搽呢？
You want some rubbing alcohol maybe?

770
00:51:10,690 --> 00:51:12,780
给点波旁威士忌就行了。
A little bourbon might help.

771
00:51:13,890 --> 00:51:16,360
闭嘴，小子们，闭嘴！
Knock it off, buckos.

772
00:51:16,460 --> 00:51:18,490
我们把牌玩完吧，中尉。
Let's finish the game, Lieutenant.

773
00:51:20,140 --> 00:51:22,770
“醉眼乐队”

774
00:51:49,160 --> 00:51:51,890
嘿，你可真是个疯狂的律师。
Hey, what a crazy lawyer we got.

775
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:55,260
你好，保利。他们就是这样叫你的吧？保利？
Hiya, Paulie. That's what 
they call you, isn't it? Paulie?

776
00:51:55,370 --> 00:51:58,330
疯狂的律师，疯狂的名字。
That's a crazy name for a crazy lawyer.

777
00:52:07,480 --> 00:52:11,570
- 谢谢你让我和你一起弹，“醉眼”。
- 嗨，你不是就想颠儿了吧？
- Thanks for letting me sit in, Pie-Eye.
- Hey, you're not splitting the scene?

778
00:52:11,680 --> 00:52:13,980
- 我是说你想走了吗？
- 不 ，我过会儿回来。
- I mean, you're not cuttin' out?
- No, I'll be back.

779
00:52:34,140 --> 00:52:37,010
嗨，保利。伙计们，这位是曼尼的律师。 
Hi, Paulie. Fellows, this is Manny's lawyer.

780
00:52:37,110 --> 00:52:38,570
- 嗨，你好！
- 不想坐下吗？
- Hi. How are you?
- Sit down, won't you?

781
00:52:38,680 --> 00:52:41,040
抱歉，现在不行。曼尼昂夫人，
I'm sorry, I can't right now. Mrs. Manion...

782
00:52:41,150 --> 00:52:43,380
我可以到外面和你谈会儿吗？
may I talk to you for a moment outside?

783
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:47,080
曼尼昂夫人？我还以为
我们早就不用这么正式了。
Mrs. Manion? I thought we dropped 
the formalities a long time ago.

784
00:52:47,180 --> 00:52:50,020
我想或许我们还是重新
变得正式一点好，这很重要。
I think maybe we'd better pick 'em 
up again. It's important.

785
00:52:50,120 --> 00:52:52,450
- 好吧，我跟你走。
- 好吧，这边来。
- All right. I'll go with you.
- All right. Come on.

786
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:54,750
嘿，你还会回来，对吗？
Hey. You're coming back, aren't you?

787
00:52:54,860 --> 00:52:56,760
你说呢？
What do you think?

788
00:53:06,100 --> 00:53:08,330
回头见，“醉眼”。
See you later, Pie-Eye.

789
00:53:08,440 --> 00:53:09,910
好的。
Okay.

790
00:53:17,410 --> 00:53:21,040
- 你收到我的电话留言啦？
- 是的，但是我很忙。
- Did you get my phone message?
- Yeah, but I got busy.

791
00:53:21,150 --> 00:53:23,180
为什么你没去看你丈夫？
Why haven't you been to see your husband?

792
00:53:23,290 --> 00:53:25,190
不明白为什么要每天去看他。
I don't see why I have to see him every day.

793
00:53:25,290 --> 00:53:27,480
我认为你每天都去是个不错的主意。
I think it would be a very good idea if you did.

794
00:53:27,590 --> 00:53:29,960
好吧，我会每天去看他。行了吧？
All right, I'll see him every day. Okay?

795
00:53:30,060 --> 00:53:33,050
- 不，还不行。你的车在哪儿？
- 我跟他们一起来的。
- No, not okay. Where's your car?
- I came with them.

796
00:53:33,160 --> 00:53:36,220
- 我的车就在那儿，跟我来。
- 慢着，我朋友还在里面呢！
- Mine's right over here. Come on.
- Wait. I've got friends inside.

797
00:53:36,330 --> 00:53:39,770
- 什么朋友不朋友的，你现在就回家去。
- 你以为你是谁？
- Friends or not, you're going home.
- Who do you think you are?

798
00:53:39,870 --> 00:53:42,530
我是那位想帮你丈夫
打赢官司的律师，记起来了？
I'm the lawyer trying to beat a rap 
for your husband, remember?

799
00:53:42,640 --> 00:53:45,770
- 那又怎么……
- 你听好了！你听好了！
- What's that got to do with--
- You listen to me.

800
00:53:45,880 --> 00:53:48,540
在结案之前，你必须是一个温顺的小娇妻，
Until this trial's over, you're 
going to be a meek little housewife...

801
00:53:48,650 --> 00:53:50,550
戴一副角质架的眼镜；
with horn-rimmed spectacles...

802
00:53:50,650 --> 00:53:53,280
你必须远离这些男人和路边酒馆，
and you're going to stay away 
from men and juke joints...

803
00:53:53,380 --> 00:53:55,680
不再喝酒和玩弹球游戏；
and booze and pinball machines...

804
00:53:55,790 --> 00:53:59,750
你必须穿着裙服和低跟的鞋子，
你必须束着腰带。
and you're going to wear a skirt
and low-heeled shoes and a girdle.

805
00:53:59,860 --> 00:54:02,190
特别是要束腰带。
你看，劳拉……
And especially a girdle.
Look, Laura...

806
00:54:02,290 --> 00:54:05,130
相信我，我通常并不讨厌女士们
富于魅力的摇曳身姿，
believe me, I don't usually 
complain of an attractive jiggle...

807
00:54:05,230 --> 00:54:08,320
但是你最好还是将你的摇曳身姿
留给你丈夫去观赏吧，
but you save that jiggle 
for your husband to look at...

808
00:54:08,430 --> 00:54:10,290
要是我能尽快把他弄出监狱的话。
if and when I get him out of jail.

809
00:54:10,300 --> 00:54:12,100
行了，我们走吧。
Come on. Let's go.

810
00:54:13,370 --> 00:54:17,530
我很抱歉，真的很抱歉。
再怎么样，我也不想毁掉曼尼的机会。
I'm sorry. I really am. I wouldn't 
hurt Manny's chances for anything.

811
00:54:17,640 --> 00:54:19,540
走吧。
Come on.

812
00:54:57,920 --> 00:55:00,010
这里是巴尼殴打你的地方吗？
Is this about where Barney knocked you down?

813
00:55:00,120 --> 00:55:02,350
是的，就在这里。
Yeah, right over here.

814
00:55:02,450 --> 00:55:04,610
那儿的篱笆上有道门，
毛毛咬着便携灯…
Over there's the opening in the fence 
where Muffy was running...

815
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:06,990
在那儿跑进跑出。
back and forth with the flashlight.

816
00:55:09,830 --> 00:55:11,890
你们的车房在哪儿？
Where's your trailer?

817
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:13,900
在那边山上。
Up there on the hill.

818
00:55:20,170 --> 00:55:22,600
这是我最喜欢的地方。
This is my favorite place.

819
00:55:26,980 --> 00:55:31,070
有时我会等曼尼熟睡后
一个人走出来，就这样坐着。
Sometimes when Manny was sleeping 
I'd come out here and just sit.

820
00:55:31,180 --> 00:55:35,280
我不得不从车房里出来，
我受不了被关在里面的感觉。
I had to get out of that trailer.
I couldn't stand being cooped up.

821
00:55:37,790 --> 00:55:42,520
我…我感到孤独，包罗，非常孤独。
I'm-- I'm lonely, Paul. I'm awful lonely.

822
00:55:42,630 --> 00:55:46,360
要是不孤独的话我也不会
去路边酒馆了，你知道。
I wouldn't have gone to that roadhouse 
if it weren't for that, you know.

823
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:50,330
也许你应该开始准备着习惯孤独了。
Maybe you were getting in 
some good practice being lonely.

824
00:55:50,430 --> 00:55:52,830
你的意思是也许曼尼出不了狱？
You mean you think maybe Manny won't get off?

825
00:55:52,940 --> 00:55:55,960
那得取决于陪审团，
你永远也说不准他们会如何裁决。
That'll be up to the jury, 
and you can never tell about them.

826
00:55:56,070 --> 00:55:59,100
如果他出不了狱，还有一种方式可以了结这一切。
If he didn't, it'd be one way to end it.

827
00:55:59,210 --> 00:56:01,400
不，我不是这个意思。我…
No, I don't mean that.

828
00:56:01,510 --> 00:56:04,970
有时我也会这样想，
但是我真的不愿意这样做。
I may think it sometimes, 
but I don't really want it.

829
00:56:18,700 --> 00:56:21,630
你好，亲爱的，你想我了吗？
Hello, sweetie. Did you miss me?

830
00:56:21,730 --> 00:56:23,960
当然你想我了。
Of course you missed me.

831
00:56:26,400 --> 00:56:28,670
你想进去吗，保罗？
You wanna come in, Paul?

832
00:56:28,770 --> 00:56:31,210
如果你愿意，你可以进去，你知道。
You can if you want to, you know.

833
00:56:32,410 --> 00:56:34,740
不了，谢谢，劳拉。
No thank you, Laura.

834
00:56:34,850 --> 00:56:38,210
对不起，我刚才不得不扫了你的兴在那儿。
I'm sorry I had to spoil your fun 
over at that place.

835
00:56:40,250 --> 00:56:41,950
晚安，劳拉。
Good night, Laura.

836
00:56:42,050 --> 00:56:43,610
晚安。
Good night.

837
00:57:11,350 --> 00:57:13,510
注意，注意，注意！
Hear ye, hear ye, hear ye.

838
00:57:13,620 --> 00:57:18,610
铁峭壁县巡回法庭现在开庭。
The circuit court for the county 
of Iron Cliffs is now in session.

839
00:57:18,720 --> 00:57:20,620
你们可以坐下。
You can be seated.

840
00:57:25,960 --> 00:57:29,960
你们有些人可能不认识我，
我的名字是威弗。
For those of you I haven't met, 
my name is Weaver.

841
00:57:30,070 --> 00:57:32,700
我从本州南面过来，将临时主持本庭，
I'm from downstate,
and I'm sitting temporarily...

842
00:57:32,800 --> 00:57:37,140
因为你们杰出的梅特兰法官
正身患重疾有待康复。
while your good Judge Maitland
is recovering from a severe illness.

843
00:57:37,240 --> 00:57:40,430
我想没有必要作宏篇大论
来介绍我的办案方式，
There's no need to dwell 
at length upon my methods.

844
00:57:40,440 --> 00:57:43,240
因为所有法官都大同小异。
One judge is quite like another.

845
00:57:43,350 --> 00:57:47,080
也许细微的差别在于
他们消化力（领悟力）的强弱，
The only difference is maybe 
in the state of their digestions...

846
00:57:47,180 --> 00:57:50,590
或者是不是很容易在法官席上昏昏欲睡。
or their proclivities for sleeping on the bench.

847
00:57:50,690 --> 00:57:54,070
就我而言，我可以消化掉铁铸的猪。
For myself, I can digest pig iron.

848
00:57:54,070 --> 00:57:56,560
当然，也许我时不时地会打个盹，
And while I might appear to doze occasionally...

849
00:57:56,560 --> 00:57:59,120
但是，你们会发现我也很容易被弄醒，
you'll find that I'm easily awakened...

850
00:57:59,230 --> 00:58:02,670
特别是被一个好律师的精妙的
particularly if shaken gently by a good lawyer...

851
00:58:02,770 --> 00:58:05,430
法律观点轻轻摇醒。
with a nice point of law.

852
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:08,800
现在我们来看一下待判决的刑事诉讼表。
We will now take up the criminal docket.

853
00:58:08,910 --> 00:58:13,000
案子一：对克拉伦斯・马迪根提起的公诉――
Case number one--
The People v. Clarence Madigan--

854
00:58:13,110 --> 00:58:16,050
在夜间强行侵入他人住宅。
breaking and entering in the nighttime.

855
00:58:16,150 --> 00:58:19,050
被告起立上前？
Will the defendant rise and come forward?

856
00:58:19,150 --> 00:58:21,050
是我，法官大人。
That's me, Your Honor.

857
00:58:29,530 --> 00:58:31,620
密歇根州，铁峭壁县法庭：
State of Michigan, court of Iron Cliffs...

858
00:58:31,730 --> 00:58:35,600
我，米切尔・罗德威克，地方检察官，
前来铁峭壁县法庭…
I, Mitchell Lodwick, prosecuting 
attorney, come into Iron Cliffs...

859
00:58:35,700 --> 00:58:38,730
指证克拉伦斯・马迪根，
and give the court to understand
that one Clarence Madigan...

860
00:58:38,840 --> 00:58:42,330
别名“一口闷”・马迪根、
别名“老烟枪”・马迪根，
alias "One-Shot" Madigan,
alias "Smoky" Madigan...

861
00:58:42,440 --> 00:58:44,740
确实强行侵入了卡斯帕・卡茨的住宅，
did break and enter the dwelling house 
of Casper Katz...

862
00:58:44,840 --> 00:58:47,670
并在前述的建筑物内，犯下了盗窃罪。
and did there commit the felony 
of larceny on said premises.

863
00:58:49,150 --> 00:58:51,550
马迪根先生有辩护律师吗？
Does Mr. Madigan have an attorney?

864
00:58:51,650 --> 00:58:55,480
噢，没有。一个人得有钱才能
买得起律师的时间啊。
No. A man's gotta have money to ask 
them fellas the time of day.

865
00:58:55,590 --> 00:58:57,490
马迪根先生，如果你没有钱，
Mr. Madigan, if you're impoverished...

866
00:58:57,590 --> 00:59:00,720
我有义务给你指派个律师。
it's my duty to appoint an attorney 
on your behalf.

867
00:59:00,820 --> 00:59:02,880
我想没必要麻烦了，法官大人。
I wouldn't bother, Your Honor.

868
00:59:02,990 --> 00:59:06,290
我偷了威士忌，罪责难逃。
I stole the whisky. I'm guilty as hell.

869
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:08,760
是一整箱贵重的波旁威士忌，法官大人。
It was a full case of expensive bourbon, Your Honor.

870
00:59:08,870 --> 00:59:10,560
你把这些威士忌卖掉了吗？
Did you sell this whisky?

871
00:59:10,670 --> 00:59:12,160
噢，不，我喝掉了。
No. I drank it.

872
00:59:12,170 --> 00:59:14,070
- 都喝掉啦？
- 你不信吗，法官？
- All of it?
- You bet, Judge.

873
00:59:14,080 --> 00:59:17,830
你知不知道你因犯此罪而不得不接受惩罚？
Are you aware that it will be 
necessary to punish you for this crime?

874
00:59:17,840 --> 00:59:19,410
我罪有应得，法官大人。
It was worth it.

875
00:59:19,510 --> 00:59:22,440
好吧，我接受你的服罪，马迪根先生。
Well, I'll accept your plea of guilty, Mr. Madigan.

876
00:59:22,550 --> 00:59:25,270
判决会过后下达。
现在你可以回到位子上去了。
You'll be sentenced later. 
You may now return to your place.

877
00:59:25,280 --> 00:59:27,180
谢谢，法官大人。
Thanks, Your Honor.

878
00:59:28,920 --> 00:59:31,390
案子二：
Case number two--

879
00:59:31,490 --> 00:59:33,890
对弗雷德里克・曼尼昂的公诉，
The People v. Frederick Manion,

880
00:59:33,990 --> 00:59:36,190
罪名是――蓄意杀人。
The charge-- murder.

881
00:59:36,290 --> 00:59:40,920
我是保罗・比格勒，被告律师。
我的正式材料已交法庭归档。
Paul Biegler for the defendant.
My formal appearance is already on file.

882
00:59:41,030 --> 00:59:43,520
这些人当中哪一位是你的委托人呢，比格勒先生？
Which of these men is your client, Mr. Biegler?

883
00:59:43,630 --> 00:59:45,190
一个都不是。
None of them.

884
00:59:45,300 --> 00:59:48,600
庭警，你能把在押人带上来吗？
Sheriff, will you produce the prisoner?

885
00:59:48,710 --> 00:59:52,610
呃…我，恐怕我做不到，法官大人。
Well, I-- I'm afraid I can't do that, Your Honor.

886
00:59:52,710 --> 00:59:55,680
是不是有谁可以给我解释一下，
我可没有未卜先知的本领。
Perhaps someone should explain.
I'm not clairvoyant.

887
00:59:55,780 --> 01:00:00,050
被告现在正在底特律
接受精神病医生的检查，法官大人。
The defendant is in Detroit 
being examined by a psychiatrist.

888
01:00:00,070 --> 01:00:02,180
在允许被告离开他的司法属地之前，
Shouldn't the court have been consulted...

889
01:00:02,190 --> 01:00:05,220
是不是应该征得法庭的同意呢？
before the defendant 
was allowed to leave its jurisdiction?

890
01:00:05,220 --> 01:00:08,250
法官大人，在这起案子里，
我们涉及到军方。
Your Honor, we're dealing 
with the army in this matter.

891
01:00:08,360 --> 01:00:11,490
他们说这是唯一的时机
可以提供给我们他们的精神病专家。
This is the only crack they would 
give us at one of their psychiatrists.

892
01:00:11,600 --> 01:00:16,290
法庭当时没有参与，而且情况紧急，
我们得马上带被告去见精神病医生。
The court was not present. It was urgent 
we get the defendant to a psychiatrist.

893
01:00:16,400 --> 01:00:18,700
那么公诉人对此有什么意见呢？
What does the attorney for the people say to this?

894
01:00:18,800 --> 01:00:20,530
就我所知，这没有问题。
It was done with my knowledge.

895
01:00:20,640 --> 01:00:25,570
我总是听说这儿――我们美丽半岛的
上半州――是一个奇怪的地方。
I've always heard this Upper Pennisula 
of our fair state was a queer place.

896
01:00:25,680 --> 01:00:29,780
如果允许被控一级谋杀罪的嫌疑犯
逍遥外出在这儿是家常便饭的话，
If it's customary here to allow a man 
charged with first degree murder...

897
01:00:29,780 --> 01:00:34,510
那么我作为一个外来者，
似乎并不合适向你们指出…
to wander about at will, I don't suppose 
it behooves an outsider to point out...

898
01:00:34,520 --> 01:00:38,540
没有那条法律规定
会支持这样奇怪的自由。
that the law makes no provision 
for such quaint liberalism.

899
01:00:38,660 --> 01:00:43,350
法官大人，被告在随行警官的监管之下，
今天下午返回。
The defendant is in the care of a deputy
and will be returned this afternoon.

900
01:00:43,460 --> 01:00:47,060
我们将在被告回来之后，正式传讯他。
We'll formally arraign the defendant on his return.

901
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:50,660
为了记录的需要，你能否给我提一下
他会以什么理由抗辩呢？
For the sake of the docket, 
can you give me a clue to his plea?

902
01:00:50,770 --> 01:00:53,960
被告愿意放弃听取犯罪指控，
并对被控罪名不进行答辩。
The defendant will waive reading 
of the information and stand mute.

903
01:00:54,070 --> 01:00:56,500
以“无罪”抗辩记录在案。
A plea of "not guilty" will be entered.

904
01:00:56,610 --> 01:01:01,310
弗雷德里克・曼尼昂之案将列于
待判决的刑事诉讼表的第一例。
The case of Frederick Manion will be
placed first on the trial docket.

905
01:01:12,120 --> 01:01:14,560
你能抓紧点吗，保利？
要是有人告诉那个法官…
Can you hurry it up, Paulie?
If somebody tells that judge...

906
01:01:14,660 --> 01:01:18,420
在押人在火车站四处闲荡，
他会给我颜色瞧的。
the prisoner was lounging around the 
rail station, he'll give me the works.

907
01:01:18,530 --> 01:01:21,430
只需个把分钟。到这边来。
This will just take a minute. Come on over here.

908
01:01:25,200 --> 01:01:27,900
那么中尉，检查结果怎么样呢？
Well, Lieutenant, how'd things turn out?

909
01:01:28,000 --> 01:01:30,470
- 我有临时性精神错乱。
- 他这样跟你说的？
- I was temporarily insane.
- Did he tell you that?

910
01:01:30,570 --> 01:01:33,630
是的。他说会给你写封信。
Yeah. Says he's gonna write you a letter.

911
01:01:33,740 --> 01:01:36,680
我自己也记了点。
I took some notes on my own.

912
01:01:36,780 --> 01:01:38,770
医生的名字是史密斯。
The doctor's name is Smith.

913
01:01:38,880 --> 01:01:42,840
我希望是“安纳托利・路德维希・史密斯”，
或者是“路德维希・冯・史密斯”，
Anatole Ludwig Smith or 
Ludwig von Smith, I hope.

914
01:01:42,950 --> 01:01:45,280
那样的名字容易唬住陪审团。
A name like that would impress the jury.

915
01:01:45,390 --> 01:01:48,820
可惜只是平白的“马修・史密斯”。
他说当我向奎尔开枪时，
Just plain Matthew Smith.
He said that when I shot Quill...

916
01:01:48,930 --> 01:01:53,790
- 我患有“习惯性分裂反应”症。
- “习惯性分裂反应”。
- I was suffering from "dissociative reaction".
- "dissociative reaction".

917
01:01:54,030 --> 01:01:57,160
- 听上去很不错，是吗，搭档？
- 是啊，用听得懂的英语解释一下呢？
- Sounds pretty good, doesn't it?
- What does it mean?

918
01:01:57,170 --> 01:02:01,660
意思是“我当时产生了无法抑制的
枪击奎尔的冲动。”
It means "I had an irresistible 
impulse to shoot Quill."

919
01:02:04,770 --> 01:02:06,260
这下行了，是不是？
That's okay, isn't it?

920
01:02:06,380 --> 01:02:10,640
他有没有说你在枪击奎尔时，
是否丧失了分辨是非的能力？
What did he say about your knowing 
the difference between right and wrong?

921
01:02:10,750 --> 01:02:14,340
我想他没有说。怎么，这很重要吗？
I don't think he said anything.
Why, is that important?

922
01:02:14,450 --> 01:02:17,680
我们最好别让警官再等了。
你还是走吧。
We'd better not keep 
the sheriff waiting. You'd better go.

923
01:02:23,560 --> 01:02:25,460
谢谢你，警官。
Thank you, Sheriff.

924
01:02:36,840 --> 01:02:41,170
你有否听说过密歇根州的法庭
曾将“无法抑制的冲动”接受成精神错乱？
Ever heard of a Michigan court accepting
"irresistible impulse" as insanity?

925
01:02:41,280 --> 01:02:44,370
没有。或许我们改成“正当防卫”更好一些。
No. Maybe we'd better switch to self-defense.

926
01:02:44,480 --> 01:02:47,540
这样的话即使米奇・罗德威克
也会让我们丢尽脸面。
Even Mitch Lodwick would make 
a monkey out of us then.

927
01:02:47,650 --> 01:02:50,740
- 该死的草莓苏打水。
- 要花生吗？
- Damn strawberry soda.
- Want a peanut?

928
01:02:50,850 --> 01:02:51,620
不，谢谢。
No thanks.

929
01:02:52,720 --> 01:02:55,020
嗯，明天是星期六。
Well, tomorrow's Saturday.

930
01:02:55,130 --> 01:02:59,290
开庭之前我们只有一个周末了。
你想什么时候开始工作呢？
We just have a weekend before the trial.
When do you want to start working?

931
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:01,630
明天上午，一大早。
Tomorrow morning, early.

932
01:03:57,150 --> 01:03:59,590
- 保利。
- 嘿，听听这个，帕内尔。
- Paulie.
- Hey, listen to this, Parn.

933
01:03:59,690 --> 01:04:02,850
你先慢着。我才找到这个：
Never mind that. Just find...

934
01:04:02,960 --> 01:04:08,190
对德费（62岁）的公诉案，
密歇根案宗，486页，1886年。
People v. Durfee, 62, 
Michigan, 486, Year 1886.

935
01:04:08,300 --> 01:04:11,700
就是这个！我手里的《全美诉讼报告》
也有此案。听着：
That's it. I have it right here 
in the A.L.R. Listen.

936
01:04:11,800 --> 01:04:14,830
“大多数州都接受‘是非判断’的测试，
尽管这并不被认为…
"The right and wrong test, 
though deemed unscientific...

937
01:04:14,940 --> 01:04:16,840
是一种科学的方法，除非…”
is adhered to by most states but--"

938
01:04:16,940 --> 01:04:20,030
注意这个“除非”，
“除非被控犯罪的人…
Now listen to this "but"--
"but the fact that one accused...

939
01:04:20,140 --> 01:04:23,270
确实有能力知道…
of committing a crime 
may have been able to comprehend...

940
01:04:23,380 --> 01:04:26,180
他的行为所导致后果的性质，
the nature and the consequences of this act...

941
01:04:26,280 --> 01:04:28,720
即他明确知道那是错误的行为。
and to know that it was wrong.

942
01:04:28,820 --> 01:04:32,580
- 然而，…”
- 可爱永恒的“然而”。
- Nevertheless--"
- Sweet enduring word "Nevertheless."

943
01:04:32,690 --> 01:04:35,920
“然而，如果那是由于某种…
"Nevertheless, if he was forced to its execution...

944
01:04:36,030 --> 01:04:41,160
无力控制的冲动…无力控制的冲动
所强行导致的行为，
by an impulse-- by an impulse 
which he was powerless to control...

945
01:04:41,260 --> 01:04:43,860
那么他就可以免于受到惩罚。”
he will be excused from punishment."

946
01:04:43,970 --> 01:04:47,600
密歇根州最高法院确实接受过
“无法抑制的冲动”的说法。
The Michigan Supreme Court 
did accept irresistible impulse.

947
01:04:47,700 --> 01:04:49,230
这就是先例。
This is precedent.

948
01:04:49,340 --> 01:04:51,830
天哪，我想我们确实有了些依据。
Boy, I think we've got a hold of something here.

949
01:04:51,940 --> 01:04:54,410
亲爱的1886年的老德费。
Good old Durfee, 1886.

950
01:04:54,510 --> 01:04:57,280
你的苏打水怎么样？给我点纸。
How about that? Give me a pad.

951
01:04:57,380 --> 01:05:01,040
现在这草莓苏打水也开始变味了，
喝着像是真正的波旁威士忌。
This strawberry soda is beginning 
to taste like real bourbon whisky.

952
01:05:01,150 --> 01:05:04,850
是啊，那也别喝醉了，
我们还有一帮子陪审团要说服呢，
Well, don't get drunk yet.
We've got to convince a jury...

953
01:05:04,850 --> 01:05:08,210
要让他们相信我们的委托人确实
产生了“无法抑制的冲动”。
that our client was irresistibly impulsed.

954
01:05:08,220 --> 01:05:10,520
记住这点。
Remember that.

955
01:05:10,530 --> 01:05:14,790
陪审团的女士们和先生们，
在开始之前，
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury, 
before we proceed further...

956
01:05:14,900 --> 01:05:18,830
我有必要核查一下你们作为…
it will be necessary for me 
to examine you on your qualifications...

957
01:05:18,940 --> 01:05:20,990
陪审员的资格。
to sit as jurors.

958
01:05:21,100 --> 01:05:23,600
请记住你们都宣过誓。
Will you please remember 
that you are under oath?

959
01:05:23,710 --> 01:05:26,110
你们都是合法公民吗？
Are all of you citizens?

960
01:05:26,210 --> 01:05:28,870
如果不是请举手。
Will you please raise your hand if you are not?

961
01:05:41,860 --> 01:05:46,760
你们当中有治安法官或执法人员吗？
Are there any justices of the peace 
or law enforcement officers among you?

962
01:05:46,860 --> 01:05:48,850
没有。
No.

963
01:05:48,970 --> 01:05:51,700
你们当中有没有人和任何执法人员…
Are any of you related by blood or marriage...

964
01:05:51,800 --> 01:05:55,290
- 有血缘或婚姻上的关系？
- 没有。
- to any law enforcement officer?
- No.

965
01:05:55,870 --> 01:05:59,870
资格检查就到此了。
下面我来检查陪审团的合法性。
So much for qualifications.
I will now examine for cause.

966
01:05:59,980 --> 01:06:02,210
你们当中有没有任何人
和公诉人米切尔・罗德威克…
Do any of you have any business pending...

967
01:06:02,310 --> 01:06:05,910
- 有任何未决的纠纷？
- 没有。
- with the prosecuting attorney, Mitchell Lodwick?
- No.

968
01:06:06,180 --> 01:06:10,120
你们当中有没有任何人
和被告辩护律师保罗・比格勒…
Do any of you have any business 
pending with Paul Biegler...

969
01:06:10,220 --> 01:06:12,810
- 有任何未决的纠纷？
- 没有。
- attorney for the defense?
- No.

970
01:06:12,920 --> 01:06:15,450
你们当中有没有任何人认识被告，
Are any of you acquainted with the defendant...

971
01:06:15,560 --> 01:06:17,870
- 他现在正坐在比格勒先生左边？
- 没有。
- sitting there on Mr. Biegler's left?
- No.

972
01:06:17,980 --> 01:06:20,530
“这家伙是州检查总长办公室的，
我见过他的表现。千万留神！”

973
01:06:20,540 --> 01:06:23,500
请被告的妻子，劳拉・曼尼昂站起来好吗？
Will Mrs. Laura Manion, 
the defendant's wife, please stand?

974
01:06:24,570 --> 01:06:27,170
- 你们当中有没有任何人认识曼尼昂夫人？
- 没有。
- Do any of you know Mrs. Manion?
- No.

975
01:06:27,640 --> 01:06:31,000
谢谢，曼尼昂夫人，你可以坐下了。
Thank you, Mrs. Manion. You may be seated.

976
01:06:31,510 --> 01:06:33,870
辩护律师可以对陪审团的合法性提出质询。
Counsel may challenge the jury for cause.

977
01:06:33,980 --> 01:06:39,470
大人，在辩方质询之前，
我可以向法庭介绍克劳德・丹瑟吗？
Before counsel's challenge, may I 
introduce Claude Dancer to the court?

978
01:06:39,580 --> 01:06:42,680
来自州府兰辛的丹瑟先生
是州检查总长助理。
Mr. Dancer is an assistant 
attorney general from Lansing.

979
01:06:42,790 --> 01:06:45,580
鉴于这起案子的奇特性质，
Because of the peculiar nature of this case...

980
01:06:45,690 --> 01:06:49,420
我请求了检查总长
指派丹瑟先生参与起诉过程。
I requested the attorney general to let 
Mr. Dancer sit in with the prosecution.

981
01:06:49,530 --> 01:06:52,390
久闻你的大名，丹瑟先生。
Your reputation precedes you, Mr. Dancer.

982
01:06:52,500 --> 01:06:54,460
你的参与是本庭的荣誉。
It's a privilege to have you in my court.

983
01:06:54,560 --> 01:06:57,590
谢谢，我想对我也必有收益。
Thank you. I'm sure it'll be instructive.

984
01:06:57,700 --> 01:07:00,190
陪审团当中有没有任何人和州检查总长办公室
Do any of you have any business pending...

985
01:07:00,300 --> 01:07:03,500
- 有任何未决的纠纷？
- 没有。
- before the attorney general's office?
- No.

986
01:07:05,210 --> 01:07:08,040
我得就我以前贬损上半州和…
I must apologize for my disparaging remarks...

987
01:07:08,140 --> 01:07:10,910
这儿的习惯的评论做出道歉。
about the Upper Pennisula and its customs.

988
01:07:10,910 --> 01:07:16,420
我很少碰到谋杀案的陪审团用不到半天时间
就可以选定并宣誓就职的情况。
I've seldom seen a murder jury selected 
and sworn in less than half a day.

989
01:07:16,420 --> 01:07:19,450
你们完全赢得了我的心，先生们。
You have won my heart completely, gentlemen.

990
01:07:19,560 --> 01:07:22,850
丹瑟先生，你要求休庭，
你有什么问题吗？
Mr. Dancer, you asked for the recess.
What's your problem?

991
01:07:22,960 --> 01:07:25,790
我只是想提一个小小的建议。
It was a little suggestion I wanted to make.

992
01:07:25,900 --> 01:07:29,460
- 愿意洗耳恭听。
- 既然辩方以精神错乱作为抗辩理由，
- By all means.
- Since the defense plea is insanity...

993
01:07:29,570 --> 01:07:31,900
控方已经雇了一个精神病医生，
the prosecution has retained a psychiatrist.

994
01:07:32,000 --> 01:07:35,060
因为根据法律，我们有权要求
用我们自己的医生…
Under the statute, we have a right 
to petition for a mental exam...

995
01:07:35,170 --> 01:07:37,160
为被告作精神检查。
of the defendant by our own doctor.

996
01:07:37,270 --> 01:07:41,300
- 你熟悉这条法律吗，比格勒先生？
- 呃…呃，知道一些吧。
- Are you familiar with that statute?
- Uh-huh. Moderately.

997
01:07:41,410 --> 01:07:44,340
我想要是为此提出正式的书面申请的话，
只会耽搁正事，
I think it would only delay things 
to file a formal petition...

998
01:07:44,350 --> 01:07:49,020
因此为什么我们不可以坐在一起，
只是非正式地请求法官大人…
so why don't we informally agree 
to ask His Honor for an adjournment...

999
01:07:49,020 --> 01:07:52,350
暂缓个一到两天，
好让我们的医生看一下被告。
only a day or so, and our doctor
can visit with the defendant.

1000
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:55,020
我想这样对谁都省事儿。
你认为呢，比格勒先生？
It would save everyone time.
Don't you think so?

1001
01:07:55,120 --> 01:07:57,120
- 是的，我想是这样。
- 很好。
- I'm sure it will.
- Good.

1002
01:07:57,130 --> 01:08:01,390
但是假如你非要提出正式的书面申请，
Suppose you just go ahead 
and file that formal petition anyway.

1003
01:08:01,500 --> 01:08:05,590
当然你现在有点晚了，是吗？
也许法官大人可以对你网开一面。
Of course, you're a little late.
Maybe His Honor will overlook that.

1004
01:08:05,700 --> 01:08:10,160
那么，我就会让陪审团认为，
你其实认为我们的精神错乱辩护是有些道理的。
Then I'd like the jury to see that you 
think our insanity plea has some merit.

1005
01:08:10,270 --> 01:08:13,400
其实的确没有必要让我们的医生
为你的委托人作检查。
There really won't be any need 
for our doctor to examine your client.

1006
01:08:13,510 --> 01:08:15,410
当然，我那只是想遵循通常的程序而已。
Naturally, I was only following the usual procedure.

1007
01:08:15,510 --> 01:08:16,940
当然，我也会全力支持。
Naturally, I'm all for it.

1008
01:08:17,050 --> 01:08:20,170
- 那么你是否要提出书面申请呢，丹瑟先生？
- 是的，大人……
- Do you wish to file the petition?
- Yes, Your Honor--

1009
01:08:20,280 --> 01:08:23,180
- 不必了。
- 噢，是的，的确没有必要了。
- That won't be necessary.
- That's right.

1010
01:08:23,290 --> 01:08:27,980
小规模战斗结束，
我们开始加入大规模的战场吧。
Skirmish over. Shall we join now 
on the field of battle?

1011
01:08:31,030 --> 01:08:35,190
奎尔的身上留有五处枪伤。
The body of Quill had sustained five gunshot wounds.

1012
01:08:35,300 --> 01:08:38,270
其中一颗子弹穿透心脏。
One of the bullets had passed through the heart.

1013
01:08:38,370 --> 01:08:41,800
依我之见，他几乎即刻殒命，
Death, in my opinion, was almost instantaneous...

1014
01:08:41,900 --> 01:08:44,030
由这一枪直接导致。
and was directly caused by this wound.

1015
01:08:44,140 --> 01:08:47,300
拉希德医生，可以给我详尽的报告吗？
Dr. Raschid, may I have your detailed report?

1016
01:08:47,410 --> 01:08:48,570
当然。
Certainly.

1017
01:08:48,680 --> 01:08:52,340
我请求这份报告作为公诉方的
一号呈堂证物，记入本案。
I ask that this report be marked 
People's Exhibit One for identification.

1018
01:08:52,450 --> 01:08:54,510
接受并记入本案。
So received and marked.

1019
01:08:54,620 --> 01:08:57,710
公诉方给辩护方一份报告的副本。
The people hand the defense a copy of the report.

1020
01:08:57,820 --> 01:09:00,020
辩护人可以交叉质询了。
Counsel may cross-examine.

1021
01:09:00,120 --> 01:09:03,990
拉希德医生，你的主要目的是确认死亡原因，
Dr. Raschid, your primary purpose 
was to ascertain the cause of death.

1022
01:09:04,090 --> 01:09:06,190
- 是吗？
- 是的。
- Was it not?
- Yes.

1023
01:09:06,300 --> 01:09:09,460
但是我在你的这份报告里
读到你检查过死者，
And yet I read in your report here
that you checked to determine...

1024
01:09:09,570 --> 01:09:14,090
以确定他是否产生过精子。
whether spermatogenesis was occurring 
in the body of the deceased.

1025
01:09:14,200 --> 01:09:15,800
反对，法官大人。
Objection.

1026
01:09:15,910 --> 01:09:19,240
公诉方传唤这位证人
只是为了确认死亡原因。
The people call this witness 
only to show the cause of death.

1027
01:09:19,340 --> 01:09:21,970
法官大人，这份报告是
作为一个整体成为证物的，
Your Honor, the entire report
was offered as evidence...

1028
01:09:22,080 --> 01:09:25,050
报告中包含有精子产生的内容。
and the report contains this information 
about spermatogenesis.

1029
01:09:25,150 --> 01:09:26,310
反对无效，罗德威克先生。
Overruled, Mr. Lodwick.

1030
01:09:26,420 --> 01:09:28,610
证人请回答。
The witness may answer.

1031
01:09:28,720 --> 01:09:31,850
是的，我为死者做了那项检查。
Yes, I made that examination on the deceased.

1032
01:09:31,950 --> 01:09:34,920
那么能不能告诉法庭你的发现呢？
And now would you tell the court your findings.

1033
01:09:35,020 --> 01:09:37,960
死者死亡之前，产生过精子。
Spermatogenesis was occurring at the time of death.

1034
01:09:38,060 --> 01:09:41,720
换句话说，死者生前并不是不育的，
In other words, the deceased in life was not sterile.

1035
01:09:41,830 --> 01:09:43,890
- 他可以产生后代。
- 是这样的。
- He could produce children.
- That is correct.

1036
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:46,940
那么医生，如果一个女人声称
她和某位男子…
Now, Doctor, if a woman says 
that she has had intercourse...

1037
01:09:47,040 --> 01:09:50,530
发生过性关系，
而这名男子又被证明具有生殖能力，
with a certain man 
and the man is proved fertile...

1038
01:09:50,640 --> 01:09:53,270
那么即使在这个女子的体内
没有发现性行为的证据，
even though no evidence 
is found in the woman's body...

1039
01:09:53,380 --> 01:09:55,740
一个律师――就说某个公诉人吧――
could a lawyer--say a prosecuting attorney--

1040
01:09:55,850 --> 01:09:59,340
他能不能以此作为这名女子撒谎的证据呢？
could he use this as evidence 
that the woman is lying?

1041
01:09:59,450 --> 01:10:03,850
法官大人，我反对这样的质问方式。
Your Honor, I object to this line of questioning.

1042
01:10:03,950 --> 01:10:08,520
我们在此并不关心某男某女是否发生过关系。
We're not concerned with if there has 
been relations with a man and a woman.

1043
01:10:08,530 --> 01:10:12,120
法官大人，既然精子产生的检查已经做了，
As long as an examination 
for spermatogenesis has been made...

1044
01:10:12,230 --> 01:10:14,220
至少我们也有权知道为什么要做吧。
at least we're entitled to know why.

1045
01:10:14,330 --> 01:10:15,760
反对无效，请回答。
Overruled. You may answer.

1046
01:10:15,870 --> 01:10:18,660
是的，控方可以用那个结果，
Yes, prosecution could use that...

1047
01:10:18,770 --> 01:10:22,170
尽管那并不能确凿地证明她撒了谎。
though it certainly would not be 
conclusive that she was lying.

1048
01:10:22,270 --> 01:10:23,740
为什么不能？
Why not?

1049
01:10:23,840 --> 01:10:27,140
可以有多种原因导致她身上没有留下证据：
There could be several reasons 
why the test on her was negative.

1050
01:10:27,240 --> 01:10:30,270
用了避孕工具，
The use of a contraceptive...

1051
01:10:30,380 --> 01:10:34,150
或者可能是男方没有完成性行为。
or possibly there was no completion 
on the part of the man.

1052
01:10:34,250 --> 01:10:37,780
关于尸检，有没有人要求你做检查来确定…
Now this postmortem, 
were you also asked to determine...

1053
01:10:37,890 --> 01:10:41,320
死者在他死之前不久是否达到过性高潮？
if the deceased had reached a 
sexual climax shortly before his death?

1054
01:10:41,420 --> 01:10:43,950
- 没有，先生。
- 那么你能不能做这样的检查呢？
- No, sir.
- Could you have made this determination?

1055
01:10:44,060 --> 01:10:45,580
噢，能的。
Oh, yes.

1056
01:10:45,700 --> 01:10:48,260
所以你只被要求做那样一种检查，
So, you were only asked to make such an examination...

1057
01:10:48,270 --> 01:10:51,830
那种可能会对控方有利的检查，
而对辩方有利的检查一概不做。
that might be useful to the prosecution, 
none that might help the defense?

1058
01:10:51,830 --> 01:10:53,760
我反对，法官大人。
I object, Your Honor.

1059
01:10:53,870 --> 01:10:55,600
这个问题具有挑衅性。
The question is argumentative.

1060
01:10:55,710 --> 01:11:00,110
辩方律师企图攻击公诉方代表的意图。
Counsel is trying to impugn the intent 
of the representatives of the people.

1061
01:11:00,210 --> 01:11:03,410
比格勒先生，你应该意识到
这个问题是不适当的。
Mr. Biegler, you must be aware 
that the question is improper.

1062
01:11:03,510 --> 01:11:06,170
我撤回这个问题并就此道歉。
I withdraw the question and apologize.

1063
01:11:06,280 --> 01:11:08,610
这个问题及回答将从法庭记录里删除，
The question and answer will be stricken...

1064
01:11:08,720 --> 01:11:12,880
陪审团将忽略这个问题及其回答。
and the jury will disregard 
both the question and the answer.

1065
01:11:12,990 --> 01:11:14,220
我问完了。
That's all.

1066
01:11:14,320 --> 01:11:16,120
我不用再质询证人了。
No redirect.

1067
01:11:16,230 --> 01:11:19,390
公诉方现在传唤劳埃德・伯克。
The people now call Lloyd Burke.

1068
01:11:19,500 --> 01:11:21,900
请证人举步上前。
Will the witness step forward, please?

1069
01:11:25,670 --> 01:11:29,830
陪审团怎么可能忽略已经听到的内容？
How can a jury disregard what it's already heard?

1070
01:11:29,940 --> 01:11:31,840
- 他们不能，中尉。
- 你能不能在上帝面前…
- They can't, Lieutenant.
- Do you solemnly swear...

1071
01:11:31,940 --> 01:11:33,930
庄严宣誓，你即将作出的证词…
the testimony you shall give shall be the truth...

1072
01:11:34,110 --> 01:11:37,310
将是事实，完全是事实，
除了事实没有别的？
the whole truth and nothing 
but the truth, so help you God?

1073
01:11:37,410 --> 01:11:40,280
- 我宣誓。
- 请坐下。
- I do.
- Sit down, please.

1074
01:11:40,380 --> 01:11:44,580
- 请陈述你的职业，伯克先生。
- 我是广告摄影师。
- Will you state your profession?
- I'm a commercial photographer.

1075
01:11:44,690 --> 01:11:47,160
你是不是受到警察的邀约，
Were you called upon by the police...

1076
01:11:47,260 --> 01:11:50,950
在死者伯纳德・奎尔的遗体
搬离死亡现场…
to take photographs of the body 
of the deceased Bernard Quill...

1077
01:11:51,060 --> 01:11:54,000
之前和之后，为他拍摄遗体照片？
before and after he was removed
from the scene of death?

1078
01:11:54,100 --> 01:11:55,360
是的，先生。
Yes, sir.

1079
01:11:55,460 --> 01:11:58,520
这些死者的照片是你拍的吗？
Were these photographs of the deceased made by you?

1080
01:12:02,970 --> 01:12:04,530
是的。
They were.

1081
01:12:04,640 --> 01:12:09,480
书记官请记下这些照片，
作为公诉方的呈堂证物282-D。
The recorder will please mark 
these People's Exhibit 282-D.

1082
01:12:09,580 --> 01:12:13,140
可将照片提交辩方检查。
Photos are tendered to the defense for examination.

1083
01:12:13,250 --> 01:12:16,420
公诉方提议照片被法庭接受为证物。
请辩方询问证人。
And the people move their admission 
as evidence. Your witness.

1084
01:12:16,420 --> 01:12:18,320
没有问题，没有异议。
No questions. No objections.

1085
01:12:18,320 --> 01:12:21,150
保罗，那天晚上他也拍了我的照片。
Paul, he took pictures of me that night too.

1086
01:12:21,160 --> 01:12:22,520
请等一下，伯克先生。
Just a minute, Mr. Burke.

1087
01:12:24,400 --> 01:12:31,200
伯克先生，这些照片作为证物提交给法庭，
那么那天晚上你是否只拍了这些照片呢？
These photos offered as evidence, are
they the only ones you took that night?

1088
01:12:31,300 --> 01:12:33,390
唔…呃…不。
Why, no.

1089
01:12:33,500 --> 01:12:35,470
我想其它照片你洗不出来，是这样吗？
I suppose the others didn't turn out?

1090
01:12:35,570 --> 01:12:38,300
我拍的照都可以洗出来。
All my pictures turn out.

1091
01:12:38,410 --> 01:12:41,100
噢，当然。我求你原谅。
Of course. I beg your pardon.

1092
01:12:41,210 --> 01:12:44,040
那么你有没有把其它照片交给警方呢？
Did you give the other pictures to the police?

1093
01:12:44,150 --> 01:12:45,610
是的，我交了。
I did.

1094
01:12:45,720 --> 01:12:47,640
那么伯克先生，那些是什么照片呢？
What were they?

1095
01:12:47,650 --> 01:12:50,850
是无关的照片吗？也许是月亮的照片？
Were they side shots or a shot of the moon perhaps...

1096
01:12:50,950 --> 01:12:53,680
或者是一头黑熊在雷鸣湾的垃圾箱内的刨食照？
or a black bear scavenging the Thunder Bay dump?

1097
01:12:53,790 --> 01:12:57,620
我反对，法官大人。
我看不出其它的照片与本案有关。
I object. I can't see how 
other photographs are relevant.

1098
01:12:57,730 --> 01:13:02,630
引入照片是为了显示死者由于暴力而致死。
The photos were introduced to show 
the deceased met with a violent death.

1099
01:13:02,730 --> 01:13:06,190
法官大人，我想任何与这起案子
有联系的照片，都应该与本案有关。
I should think any photo pertaining 
to the case would be relevant.

1100
01:13:06,300 --> 01:13:09,200
你说得有道理，比格勒先生，请继续。
The point is good, Mr. Biegler. Continue.

1101
01:13:09,310 --> 01:13:12,040
那些其它的照片拍的什么呢，伯克先生？
What were these other photographs of?

1102
01:13:12,940 --> 01:13:14,530
曼尼昂中尉的妻子。
Lieutenant Manion's wife.

1103
01:13:14,640 --> 01:13:18,810
你是说那些照片显示了那晚
巴尼・奎尔被杀后她的样子吗？
You mean they showed how she looked
after Barney Quill was killed?

1104
01:13:18,910 --> 01:13:21,820
- 是的。
- 法官大人，她当时的样子与本案无关。
- Yes.
- How she looked is irrelevant.

1105
01:13:21,920 --> 01:13:25,410
没有证据将曼尼昂夫人的样子
和这个谋杀案相联系。
There's no evidence to connect
Mrs. Manion's appearance to this murder.

1106
01:13:25,520 --> 01:13:27,680
- 支持。
- 我很抱歉，法官大人。
- Sustained.
- I'm sorry.

1107
01:13:27,790 --> 01:13:31,160
我只是想确认一下控方没有扣留证物。
I just wanted to make sure prosecution 
wasn't withholding evidence.

1108
01:13:31,260 --> 01:13:32,920
你们听听！
Now look here!

1109
01:13:33,030 --> 01:13:36,400
我抗议被告律师对控方动机所作的…
I protest to the defense attorney's persistent attacks...

1110
01:13:36,500 --> 01:13:38,490
持续不断的攻击。
on the motives of the prosecution.

1111
01:13:38,600 --> 01:13:43,370
陪审团将忽略被告律师所说的这句话。
The jury will disregard the mark 
made by the defense attorney.

1112
01:13:43,470 --> 01:13:46,310
没有理由相信控方…
There's no reason to believe 
that the prosecution...

1113
01:13:46,410 --> 01:13:47,970
有不诚实的行为。
has not acted in good faith.

1114
01:13:48,080 --> 01:13:50,990
那我向控方道歉，还有向法庭道歉。
My apologies to the prosecution and to the court.

1115
01:13:51,090 --> 01:13:54,460
但是法官大人，既然谈到了抗议，
But Your Honor, as long as protests are being made...

1116
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:57,120
那我也想抗议一下。
I'd like to make a protest myself.

1117
01:13:57,230 --> 01:14:02,500
我完全乐意在任何时间、任何地点，
和这两位律界巨擘切磋交流，
I'm perfectly willing to take on these
two legal giants anytime, anyplace...

1118
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:05,440
但是他们得一个个来，这样才能显得公平嘛。
but in all fairness it ought to be one at a time.

1119
01:14:05,540 --> 01:14:08,980
我不希望这两个家伙
同时向我投出漫无目标的乱球。
I don't want these two fellas pitching 
knuckleballs at me at the same time.

1120
01:14:09,080 --> 01:14:12,480
在我看来你干得虽然不算尽善尽美，
但已相当不错了，比格勒先生，
It seems to me you're batting 
close to a thousand...

1121
01:14:12,580 --> 01:14:14,980
你的意思很明确。
but your point is well taken.

1122
01:14:15,080 --> 01:14:17,680
不管你们俩哪一位开始询问证人，
Whichever attorney opens with the witness...

1123
01:14:17,790 --> 01:14:22,420
那么只有他一个人可以继续询问
这个证人，直到证人离席。
he alone shall continue with that 
witness until the witness is excused.

1124
01:14:22,520 --> 01:14:25,050
谢谢您，法官大人。没有问题了。
Thank you, Your Honor. No more questions.

1125
01:14:25,160 --> 01:14:26,960
没有问题。
No questions.

1126
01:14:37,470 --> 01:14:40,200
- 喔哦，我们进展很顺利，对吗？
- 帕内尔在哪儿？
- My, we're drawing well, aren't we?
- Where's Parnell?

1127
01:14:40,310 --> 01:14:42,330
帕内尔？怎么，他不在这儿吗？
Parnell? Isn't he here?

1128
01:14:42,440 --> 01:14:45,500
没有，他不在这儿，
也不在他租的房子里，整晚都不在。
No, he's not here, not in his rooming 
house and hasn't been there all night.

1129
01:14:45,610 --> 01:14:47,640
你是最后一个见到他的，他去哪儿了？
You were the last to see him. Where is he?

1130
01:14:47,750 --> 01:14:51,740
- 我答应他不说的，所以你别问了。
- 他不会又开始喝上了吧？
- I promised not to tell, so don't ask.
- He hasn't fallen off the wagon?

1131
01:14:51,850 --> 01:14:54,450
- 不，他没酗酒。
- 那他去哪儿了呢？
- No, he was sober.
- Has he gone somewhere?

1132
01:14:54,560 --> 01:14:57,250
他的确借了我的车去干什么了。
He did borrow my car for something or other.

1133
01:14:57,360 --> 01:15:00,490
你的车？那太明智了。
他有20年没开过车了，
Your car? That was smart.
He hasn't driven a car in 20 years.

1134
01:15:00,600 --> 01:15:02,690
他会杀了他自己的。他究竟去哪儿啦？
He'll kill himself. Now where's he gone?

1135
01:15:02,800 --> 01:15:05,130
我得言而有信。
My word is my bond.

1136
01:15:23,780 --> 01:15:28,330
“慢行，距加拿大海关检查站半英里”

1137
01:15:30,390 --> 01:15:33,790
早上好，女士们、先生们。
可以开始了。
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen. 
You may proceed.

1138
01:15:33,900 --> 01:15:36,300
法官大人，
Your Honor...

1139
01:15:36,400 --> 01:15:40,030
辩方注意到控方的桌旁，坐着第三个人。
the defense notices a third person 
at the prosecution's table.

1140
01:15:40,140 --> 01:15:43,540
我们想知道是否法庭能透露点信息，
告诉我们他是谁，以满足我们的好奇？
We're wondering if the court shares 
our curiosity as to just who he is?

1141
01:15:43,640 --> 01:15:45,540
我正准备给大家介绍。
I was about to introduce him.

1142
01:15:45,640 --> 01:15:49,580
法官大人，这位先生是格雷戈里・哈考特医生。
Your Honor, this gentlemen is Dr. W. Gregory Harcourt.

1143
01:15:49,680 --> 01:15:53,710
哈考特医生是公诉方为此案请的精神病医生。
Dr. Harcourt is the people's psychiatrist in this case.

1144
01:15:53,820 --> 01:15:58,250
我们请求允许哈考特医生
作为一名观察员，坐在我们桌旁。
We ask that Dr. Harcourt be allowed 
to sit at our table as an observer.

1145
01:15:58,350 --> 01:16:00,080
你想让他观察什么呢？
What are you going to have him observe--

1146
01:16:00,190 --> 01:16:03,630
是金牛星座呢，还是大黄蜂的一生？
the constellation of Taurus 
or the life and times of a bumblebee?

1147
01:16:03,730 --> 01:16:06,490
当然是观察被告啦。
To observe the defendant, of course.

1148
01:16:06,600 --> 01:16:09,860
噢，那没问题。辩方不反对，法官大人。
That's fine. The defense has no objection.

1149
01:16:09,970 --> 01:16:12,060
我只是想说我松了一口气，
I just wish to express my relief...

1150
01:16:12,170 --> 01:16:16,870
因为新的成员还好不是从
州府兰辛来的司法增援部队。
that the new recruit is not additional
legal reinforcements from Lansing.

1151
01:16:16,970 --> 01:16:19,300
传阿尔方斯・帕盖特出庭。
Call Alphonse Paquette.

1152
01:16:25,750 --> 01:16:27,580
请举起右手。
Raise your right hand.

1153
01:16:27,680 --> 01:16:30,520
你能不能在上帝面前庄严宣誓，
Do you solemnly swear the testimony 
you give in this case...

1154
01:16:30,620 --> 01:16:34,150
你即将为本庭所作的证词将是事实，
完全是事实，除了事实没有别的？
shall be the whole truth and nothing 
but the truth, so help you God?

1155
01:16:34,260 --> 01:16:36,160
- 我宣誓。
- 请坐下。
- I do.
- Take a seat, please.

1156
01:16:38,690 --> 01:16:42,220
- 请报上你的姓名。
- 阿尔方斯・帕盖特。
- Will you state your name?
- Alphonse Paquette.

1157
01:16:42,330 --> 01:16:46,530
- 你在“雷鸣湾旅店”工作是吗，帕盖特先生？
- 我是那里的酒吧侍者。
- You work at the Thunder Bay Inn?
- I'm bartender there.

1158
01:16:46,640 --> 01:16:50,000
在巴尼・奎尔被弗雷德里克・曼尼昂
开枪打死的那个晚上，你是不是在工作？
Were you working the night that Barney 
Quill was shot by Frederick Manion?

1159
01:16:50,110 --> 01:16:52,510
- 我在工作。
- 你看到开枪过程了吗？
- I was.
- Were you witness to the shooting?

1160
01:16:52,610 --> 01:16:53,840
我看到了。
I was.

1161
01:16:53,940 --> 01:16:57,670
能不能请你用自己的语言，
告诉我们当时发生的情况？
Will you tell us please 
in your own words what happened?

1162
01:16:57,780 --> 01:17:01,310
当曼尼昂中尉进来时，
我在靠近门口的一张桌子旁。
I was at a table by the door
when Lt. Manion came in.

1163
01:17:01,420 --> 01:17:04,210
- 你当时一看到就认出那是曼尼昂中尉？
- 是的。
- Did you know Lt. Manion by sight and name?
- Yes.

1164
01:17:04,320 --> 01:17:06,220
请继续。
Go ahead.

1165
01:17:06,320 --> 01:17:10,780
他进来后朝吧台走去并开始射击。
Well, he came in and walked 
over to the bar and began to shoot.

1166
01:17:10,890 --> 01:17:13,490
他一边朝吧台走一边向巴尼开枪，
He shot Barney when he came up to the bar...

1167
01:17:13,600 --> 01:17:17,460
在巴尼倒下后，他仍然向
吧台后面的巴尼不停地射击。
and when Barney fell he kept on shooting 
at Barney behind the bar.

1168
01:17:17,570 --> 01:17:19,470
然后他转过身子，走了出去。
Then he turned around and walked out.

1169
01:17:19,570 --> 01:17:23,800
在曼尼昂中尉进入酒吧时，他的举止如何？
When Lt. Manion entered the bar, 
how did he appear to you?

1170
01:17:23,910 --> 01:17:28,470
唔，他走得不急不慢，
好像是早有准备，你可以这么说。
Well, he walked slow, kind of deliberate 
I guess you could say.

1171
01:17:28,580 --> 01:17:30,670
他和巴尼・奎尔说话了吗？
Did he speak to Barney Quill?

1172
01:17:30,780 --> 01:17:34,040
一个字都没说，就这样走了过去，拔出了枪…
Not a word. Just walked over 
and pulled out his gun...

1173
01:17:34,150 --> 01:17:35,620
“砰”。
and bang.

1174
01:17:35,720 --> 01:17:38,850
- 然后他就走了出去。
- 是的。
- And then he walked out?
- Yes.

1175
01:17:38,950 --> 01:17:42,120
他走出去时，看上去怎么样？
When he walked out, how did he appear to you?

1176
01:17:42,220 --> 01:17:44,720
他看上去和他进来时一样，
He seemed just like he did when he walked in--

1177
01:17:44,830 --> 01:17:47,060
好像他是个邮差，来送了一封信。
like he was the mailman delivering the mail.

1178
01:17:47,160 --> 01:17:50,530
当曼尼昂中尉走出酒吧时，你做了什么？
When Lt. Manion walked out of the bar, 
what did you do?

1179
01:17:50,630 --> 01:17:53,900
唔，一切发生得太快，我想我当时懵了。
Well, it happened so fast, I guess I was stunned.

1180
01:17:54,000 --> 01:17:56,870
- 然后我就跑出去追他。
- 你在外面看到他了吗？
- But then I ran out after him.
- Did you find him outside?

1181
01:17:56,970 --> 01:17:59,870
- 是的，先生，他正离开。
- 你和他说话了吗？
- Yes, sir. He was walking away.
- Did you speak to him?

1182
01:17:59,980 --> 01:18:03,930
是的，先生。我说：“中尉，出了这样的事，
你最好还是别跑。”
Yes, sir. I said, "Lieutenant, 
you'd better not run away from this."

1183
01:18:04,050 --> 01:18:06,480
他回答你了吗？
Did he reply to you?

1184
01:18:06,580 --> 01:18:10,070
他说：“你也想吃几颗吗，小子？”
He said, "Do you want some too, buster?"

1185
01:18:10,190 --> 01:18:12,180
他拿枪对着你了吗？
Was he pointing the gun at you?

1186
01:18:12,290 --> 01:18:16,090
他拿枪指着我的方向，但是枪口朝着下面。
He was holding the gun in my direction, 
but the muzzle was low.

1187
01:18:16,190 --> 01:18:20,320
当他说“你也想吃几颗吗，小子？”的时候，
When he said, "Do you want some too, buster?"...

1188
01:18:20,430 --> 01:18:22,330
他的语调是怎样的？
how was that expressed?

1189
01:18:22,430 --> 01:18:25,330
他是喊出来的？歇斯底里的？
Did he shout it? Was it hysterical?

1190
01:18:25,430 --> 01:18:28,130
粗着嗓子说的？声音里有颤抖吗？
Was he hoarse? Did his voice tremble?

1191
01:18:28,240 --> 01:18:32,430
没有，先生。他说的时候冷静镇定，
并直勾勾地看着我。
No, sir. He just said it 
cool and hard and looked right at me.

1192
01:18:32,540 --> 01:18:35,570
就你所能判断而言，他看起来…
Did he appear to you, as far as you could tell...

1193
01:18:35,680 --> 01:18:38,840
是不是完全处于清醒状态？
to be in complete possession of his faculties?

1194
01:18:38,950 --> 01:18:42,380
- 是的，先生，我是这样认为的。
- 你来质询吧。
- Yes, sir, as far as I could tell.
- Your witness.

1195
01:18:42,480 --> 01:18:47,110
帕盖特先生，那天晚上你在酒吧见到过
曼尼昂夫人，也就是曼尼昂中尉的妻子吗？
Mr. Paquette, did you see Laura Manion 
in the bar that night?

1196
01:18:47,220 --> 01:18:50,450
法官大人，他又来了！
这是非实质的，与本案无关。
There he goes again.
This is immaterial and irrelevant.

1197
01:18:50,560 --> 01:18:54,430
法官大人，我不明白为什么控方
那么容易激动，我还没说什么呢。
I don't see why the prosecution's 
so jumpy. I haven't gone any place yet.

1198
01:18:54,530 --> 01:18:58,400
我们先看看他想说什么，
然后再来反对，罗德威克先生。
Let's see where he's going 
before we start objecting.

1199
01:18:58,500 --> 01:19:00,560
你可以继续，比格勒先生。
You may proceed.

1200
01:19:00,670 --> 01:19:03,330
那天晚上你在酒吧见过曼尼昂夫人吗？
Did you see Mrs. Manion in the bar that night?

1201
01:19:03,440 --> 01:19:07,310
- 她在那儿。
- 那天晚上巴尼・奎尔离开过酒吧吗？
- She was there.
- Did Barney Quill leave that night?

1202
01:19:07,410 --> 01:19:09,780
- 是的。
- 你记不记得他是什么时候回来的？
- Yes.
- Do you remember when he returned?

1203
01:19:09,880 --> 01:19:11,810
我想他大概半夜的时候回来的。
I think he came back around midnight.

1204
01:19:11,910 --> 01:19:15,470
那么他是从哪个入口进来的？
他是从大厅的门进来的呢？
Now from which entrance did he come?
Did he come from the lobby entrance...

1205
01:19:15,580 --> 01:19:18,180
还是从外面的门进来的？
or come from that outside entrance?

1206
01:19:18,290 --> 01:19:20,480
大厅的门进来的。
It was from the lobby.

1207
01:19:20,590 --> 01:19:23,390
- 那时他的举止如何？
- 你什么意思？
- And how did he appear to you then?
- How do you mean?

1208
01:19:23,490 --> 01:19:26,760
在控方问你有关曼尼昂中尉的举止的问题时，
You understood the prosecution well 
when he asked you that question...

1209
01:19:26,860 --> 01:19:28,760
你倒是理解得很透彻。
about Lt. Manion's appearance.

1210
01:19:28,860 --> 01:19:32,200
噢，他看上去就像老巴尼，和平常一样。
Oh, well, he was just old Barney, like usual.

1211
01:19:32,200 --> 01:19:37,700
你的意思是他还是那个
和蔼朴实的、温和可靠的、
You mean he was just good old 
sober, reliable, gentle...

1212
01:19:37,810 --> 01:19:40,400
高尚中坚的、平易近人的老巴尼。
salt-of-the-earth, friend-to-man Barney.

1213
01:19:40,510 --> 01:19:42,640
法官大人，法官大人，这算什么问题？
Your Honor, what kind of a question is that?

1214
01:19:42,740 --> 01:19:45,110
我收回我的问题好了，法官大人。
I withdraw the question, Your Honor.

1215
01:19:46,420 --> 01:19:51,940
帕盖特先生，巴尼离开酒吧后，
他有没有换过衣服？
Had Barney changed his clothes 
since he left the bar?

1216
01:19:52,050 --> 01:19:53,280
我不记得了。
I don't remember.

1217
01:19:53,390 --> 01:19:56,380
也许他回来时的衣服和离开时的不一样，
Might his clothing have been different 
when he returned--

1218
01:19:56,490 --> 01:19:59,090
也就是说，他有没有可能换过衣服？
that is, might he have changed his clothes?

1219
01:19:59,190 --> 01:20:01,090
说不好，我没注意。
I didn't notice.

1220
01:20:01,200 --> 01:20:03,360
那天晚上巴尼喝酒了吗？
Was Barney drinking that night?

1221
01:20:03,470 --> 01:20:07,700
他和客人聊天时总会喝上几口。
Well, he always had a few shots
while he was talking to the customers.

1222
01:20:07,800 --> 01:20:11,260
- 他很友善。
- 噢，当然，可爱的老巴尼。
- He's friendly.
- Oh, sure, he was. Good old Barney.

1223
01:20:11,370 --> 01:20:15,140
那么你说可爱的老巴尼通常会喝多少酒呢？
Now how many shots would you say
good old Barney usually had?

1224
01:20:15,240 --> 01:20:16,800
我不知道准确的有多少。
I don't know.

1225
01:20:16,910 --> 01:20:19,610
那晚他没有喝过头吗，帕盖特先生？
Wasn't he in fact pretty loaded that night?

1226
01:20:19,710 --> 01:20:22,770
反对，法官大人。即使死者酩酊大醉，
Objection. Even if the deceased was dead drunk...

1227
01:20:22,880 --> 01:20:24,780
也不能作为被控罪名的辩护理由。
it's no defense to this charge.

1228
01:20:24,890 --> 01:20:28,820
反对有效。我建议你停止这方面问题，比格勒先生。
Sustained. I suggest you get off this.

1229
01:20:28,830 --> 01:20:33,830
帕盖特先生，你怎么称呼一个
对女性有着贪得无厌兴趣的男人？
What would you call a man with 
an insatiable penchant for women?

1230
01:20:33,930 --> 01:20:35,620
一个什么？
A what?

1231
01:20:35,730 --> 01:20:39,390
兴趣、欲望、喜好、热情。
A penchant, a desire, taste, passion.

1232
01:20:39,500 --> 01:20:42,600
呃，花花公子，我想是。
Well, a ladies man, I guess.

1233
01:20:42,700 --> 01:20:44,930
或者叫大白痴更合适。
Or maybe just a damn fool.

1234
01:20:46,340 --> 01:20:49,370
你只要回答问题就行了，帕盖特先生。
Just answer the questions.

1235
01:20:49,380 --> 01:20:52,240
俏皮话留给律师们去说好了。
The attorneys will provide the wisecracks.

1236
01:20:52,250 --> 01:20:56,180
哈，对那样的男人你还有什么
其它的叫法吗，帕盖特先生？
Well, what else would you 
call a man like that?

1237
01:20:56,280 --> 01:21:00,550
- 我们不明白这样问话的目的是什么。
- 我看你明白得很，罗德威克先生。
- We can't see the drift of this.
- You mean you do see.

1238
01:21:00,660 --> 01:21:01,820
你可以回答。
You may answer.

1239
01:21:01,920 --> 01:21:04,320
你能想起其它的名字吗，帕盖特先生？
Can you think of another name?

1240
01:21:04,430 --> 01:21:06,120
浪荡公子。
Woman chaser.

1241
01:21:06,230 --> 01:21:08,820
- 还有呢？
- 情圣？
- Try again.
- Masher?

1242
01:21:08,930 --> 01:21:10,860
噢，算了吧，帕盖特先生。
Oh, come now.

1243
01:21:10,970 --> 01:21:14,400
情圣追逐的是穿着鲸须束胸、
头戴发网的女人。
Mashers went out with 
whalebone corsets and hairnets.

1244
01:21:14,500 --> 01:21:16,400
你没听说过“色狼”的说法吗？
Did you ever hear the expression "wolf"?

1245
01:21:16,510 --> 01:21:19,200
当然，我听说过，只是一时没想到而已。
Sure, I heard that. It just slipped my mind.

1246
01:21:19,310 --> 01:21:21,400
“一时没想到而已”，当然你会记不起来了，
Well, naturally, it would...

1247
01:21:21,410 --> 01:21:24,640
有那些老掉牙的“情圣”这样的词
在你脑子里哐当乱响。
clanking around in there with all those 
rusty old "mashers."

1248
01:21:24,650 --> 01:21:27,880
你认识的人当中有没有
可以被称为色狼的呢，帕盖特先生？
Have you ever known a man 
you could call a wolf?

1249
01:21:27,980 --> 01:21:30,950
- 我不确定。
- 巴尼・奎尔是色狼吗，帕盖特先生？
- I'm not sure.
- Was Barney Quill a wolf?

1250
01:21:31,050 --> 01:21:32,610
- 我说不好。
- 还是不愿意说？
- I couldn't say.
- Or wouldn't?

1251
01:21:32,720 --> 01:21:34,620
- 反对！
- 反对有效。
- Objection.
- Sustained.

1252
01:21:34,720 --> 01:21:38,160
他已经回答了你的问题，
他说他说不好。
The question was answered.
He said he couldn't tell you.

1253
01:21:38,260 --> 01:21:43,220
帕盖特先生，当巴尼从不知道哪边回来后，
Mr. Paquette, when Barney returned
from wherever he had gone...

1254
01:21:43,330 --> 01:21:45,700
- 他有没有让你离开吧台的工作？
- 是的。
- did he relieve you at the bar?
- Yes.

1255
01:21:45,800 --> 01:21:48,960
- 他怎么对你说的？
- 他说：“交给我吧。”
- And what did he say then?
- He said, "I'll take over."

1256
01:21:49,070 --> 01:21:52,510
你从吧台后面出来后，你去哪儿啦？
When you came out from behind the bar, 
where did you go?

1257
01:21:52,610 --> 01:21:55,370
我去了彼德森夫妇坐着的桌子。
I went over to the table 
where the Pedersons were sitting.

1258
01:21:55,480 --> 01:21:59,440
你作证说曼尼昂中尉进来时，你在门边上。
Now you testified that you were 
by the door when Lt. Manion came in.

1259
01:21:59,550 --> 01:22:02,520
你在门边的原因是不是因为
彼德森夫妇的桌子在那儿？
Is that the reason you were by the door, 
because the Pedersons' table was there?

1260
01:22:02,620 --> 01:22:04,050
是的。
Yes.

1261
01:22:04,150 --> 01:22:07,750
在曼尼昂中尉进来之前，你在那儿多长时间？
And how long was it before Lt. Manion came in?

1262
01:22:07,860 --> 01:22:10,950
我不知道确切长短，大概30分钟吧。
I don't know exactly. Maybe 30 minutes.

1263
01:22:11,060 --> 01:22:13,720
在那段时间里，你一直呆在
彼德森夫妇的桌旁？
And you remained at the Pedersons' 
table all that time?

1264
01:22:13,830 --> 01:22:18,200
- 是的，他们是我的朋友。
- 在那桌子旁边有窗子吗？
- Yes, they're friends of mine.
- Is there a window beside that table?

1265
01:22:18,300 --> 01:22:20,270
- 我想有。
- 你想有。
- I think so.
- You think so.

1266
01:22:20,370 --> 01:22:23,530
你在“雷鸣湾旅店”工作
多长时间了，帕盖特先生？
How long have you worked 
at the Thunder Bay Inn?

1267
01:22:23,640 --> 01:22:25,400
大概六七年了吧。
About six, seven years.

1268
01:22:25,510 --> 01:22:27,670
桌旁的这扇窗户会不会…
Does this window beside the table...

1269
01:22:27,780 --> 01:22:33,340
突然消失和出现，像个幽灵似地游移不定？
suddenly vanish and reappear and
come and go in a ghostly fashion?

1270
01:22:33,450 --> 01:22:35,210
它一直在那儿。
It's there all the time.

1271
01:22:35,320 --> 01:22:39,380
当你在那儿和朋友聊天时，
你有没有朝窗外看？
While you were talking to your friends there, 
did you look out of the window?

1272
01:22:39,490 --> 01:22:43,220
- 可能看过。
- 当你朝窗外看时，你有没有刻意想看到什么东西？
- I might have.
- Were you looking for something special?

1273
01:22:43,330 --> 01:22:45,350
没有，我没有刻意想看到什么东西。
No, I wasn't looking for anything.

1274
01:22:45,460 --> 01:22:49,920
巴尼・奎尔没有让你到窗边留意曼尼昂中尉？
Didn't Barney Quill tell you to go to 
that window and look out for Lt. Manion?

1275
01:22:53,300 --> 01:22:56,330
他有没有让你注意曼尼昂中尉？
Did he tell you to look out for Lt. Manion?

1276
01:22:56,440 --> 01:22:59,500
他没有这么说。
He did not.

1277
01:22:59,610 --> 01:23:03,440
帕盖特先生，巴尼是个神枪手，是吗？
打枪很厉害。
Barney was quite a marksmen, 
wasn't he, with guns?

1278
01:23:03,550 --> 01:23:07,080
- 他赢过好多射击奖，是吗？
- 是的。
- He won a lot of prizes?
- Yes.

1279
01:23:07,180 --> 01:23:09,980
他在吧台后面放有枪吗？
Did he keep any guns behind the bar?

1280
01:23:15,860 --> 01:23:17,320
可能有吧。
He might have.

1281
01:23:17,330 --> 01:23:21,430
在吧台下面，有三个藏手枪的架子，
这是事实吗，帕盖特先生？
Isn't it a fact there are three 
concealed pistol racks behind the bar?

1282
01:23:21,430 --> 01:23:25,260
法官大人，被告的抗辩理由是
精神错乱，而非正当防卫。
The defendant's plea is one of insanity, 
not self-defense.

1283
01:23:25,370 --> 01:23:29,200
我确信比格勒先生没有忘记这一点，罗德威克先生。
I'm sure Mr. Biegler hasn't forgotten
that fact, Mr. Lodwick.

1284
01:23:29,300 --> 01:23:30,770
你可以回答。
You may answer.

1285
01:23:30,870 --> 01:23:33,170
在吧台下面，有没有藏着枪架？
Are there concealed gun racks behind the bar?

1286
01:23:33,270 --> 01:23:34,500
有。
Yes.

1287
01:23:34,610 --> 01:23:37,770
那么有多少人知道有这些枪架？
And how many people know about these gun racks?

1288
01:23:37,880 --> 01:23:40,140
- 我说不准。
- 那么巴尼有没有…
- I couldn't say.
- Isn't it a fact...

1289
01:23:40,250 --> 01:23:44,410
偶尔会从这些架子里取出手枪
在手指上转着圈玩儿，
that Barney would take the guns out
of the racks and twirl them...

1290
01:23:44,520 --> 01:23:48,220
以向他的客人们展示他的技巧？
to demonstrate his skill to the patrons?

1291
01:23:48,320 --> 01:23:50,260
- 我不记得了。
- 噢，得了吧，
- I don't remember.
- Come on.

1292
01:23:50,360 --> 01:23:53,620
努力想想！你自己没有看到他玩过吗？
Try and remember. 
Did you ever see him do that yourself?

1293
01:23:53,730 --> 01:23:57,100
- 看他玩过一两次吧。
- 行了，帕盖特先生。
- Once or twice he did.
- That's all.

1294
01:23:57,200 --> 01:24:00,260
- 没有其它问题了。
- 证人可以退下了。
- No further questions.
- The witness may step down.

1295
01:24:00,370 --> 01:24:02,600
传唤乔治・莱蒙。
Call George Lemon.

1296
01:24:08,240 --> 01:24:10,970
比格勒现在四处出击。
Biegler's going off in all directions.

1297
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:13,310
他究竟想干什么？
What's he getting at?

1298
01:24:15,920 --> 01:24:19,720
我的感觉是他在担心我们要干的。
I have a feeling he's afraid 
of what we'll get at.

1299
01:24:19,820 --> 01:24:22,690
比格勒先生出于某种原因，正制造烟幕。
Mr. Biegler's putting up 
a smoke screen for some reason.

1300
01:24:22,790 --> 01:24:25,520
- 我宣誓。
- 请坐下。
- I do.
- Take a seat please.

1301
01:24:27,030 --> 01:24:30,460
- 请报上你的姓名。
- 乔治・莱蒙。
- Will you state your name, please?
- George Lemon.

1302
01:24:30,570 --> 01:24:32,470
你做什么工作，莱蒙先生？
What kind of work do you do?

1303
01:24:32,570 --> 01:24:35,700
我是雷鸣湾旅游公园的管理员。
I'm caretaker of the tourist park in Thunder Bay.

1304
01:24:35,800 --> 01:24:37,830
我负责那个地方的整洁和秩序。
I see the place is clean and orderly.

1305
01:24:37,940 --> 01:24:40,370
我看着他们进进出出，
并在夜里锁好大门。
I check people in and out 
and lock the gate at night.

1306
01:24:40,480 --> 01:24:43,740
你向谁负责这份工作呢？
And what is your authority for these duties?

1307
01:24:43,850 --> 01:24:47,610
我受雇于马斯顿镇区，
我还是代理治安官，
I'm paid by Madison Township 
and I'm also a deputy sheriff.

1308
01:24:47,720 --> 01:24:49,150
某种荣誉性质的。
Just courtesy, sort of.

1309
01:24:49,250 --> 01:24:52,950
15日夜晚你有没有见过曼尼昂中尉？
Did you see Lt. Manion on the night of the 15th?

1310
01:24:52,950 --> 01:24:55,620
- 就是巴尼・奎尔被杀的那个晚上？
- 见过，先生。
- The night Barney Quill was killed?
- Yes, sir.

1311
01:24:56,660 --> 01:25:01,120
你能不能告诉法庭你是怎样以及何时…
Will you tell the court about how and when...

1312
01:25:01,230 --> 01:25:03,660
见到曼尼昂中尉的？
you saw Lt. Manion.

1313
01:25:03,770 --> 01:25:06,860
大约凌晨1点的时候我被一阵敲门声闹醒。
About 1:00 a.m. a knock on my door waked me up.

1314
01:25:06,970 --> 01:25:09,530
我打开门看见曼尼昂中尉站在那儿。
I went to the door and Lt. Manion was standing there.

1315
01:25:09,640 --> 01:25:14,440
他说：“你最好把我抓起来，莱蒙先生，
因为我刚杀了巴尼・奎尔。”
He said, "You better take me, Mr. Lemon, 
because I just shot Barney Quill."

1316
01:25:14,540 --> 01:25:17,740
我告诉他先回他的车房里，
我会给州警打电话。
I told him to go back to his trailer 
and that I would call the state police.

1317
01:25:17,850 --> 01:25:21,710
当曼尼昂中尉让你抓他的时候，
在你看来他的举止如何？
How did Lt. Manion appear to you 
when he asked you to take him?

1318
01:25:21,820 --> 01:25:25,410
他说了他想说的，然后他按我说的做了，
没有惊慌失措的样子。
He said what he had to say 
and did what I told him. No fuss.

1319
01:25:25,520 --> 01:25:29,010
就你所能判断而言，他看起来是不是…
Did he appear to you to be--
as far as you could tell--

1320
01:25:29,120 --> 01:25:31,350
完全处于清醒状态？
in complete possession of his faculties?

1321
01:25:31,460 --> 01:25:33,590
在我看来，是的，先生。
As far as I could tell, yes, sir.

1322
01:25:35,300 --> 01:25:37,260
轮到你了。
Take the witness.

1323
01:25:37,370 --> 01:25:40,730
莱蒙先生，你到曼尼昂的车房去了吗？
Mr. Lemon, did you go to the Manions' trailer?

1324
01:25:40,840 --> 01:25:43,800
- 是的，先生。
- 你在车房见到曼尼昂夫人了吗？
- Yes, sir.
- Did you see Mrs. Manion at the trailer?

1325
01:25:43,910 --> 01:25:47,400
- 是的，先生。
- 她看上去怎么样？
- Yes, sir.
- What was her appearance?

1326
01:25:47,510 --> 01:25:49,740
她当时一团糟。
She was a mess.

1327
01:25:49,840 --> 01:25:51,070
反对。
Objection.

1328
01:25:51,180 --> 01:25:55,380
没有证据显示曼尼昂夫人的样子和本案有关。
No evidence has been introduced to make 
Mrs. Manion's appearance relevant.

1329
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:59,040
也没有证据显示巴尼・奎尔的样子和本案有关，
No evidence has been introduced to make 
Barney Quill's appearance relevant...

1330
01:25:59,150 --> 01:26:01,380
但那时你倒不反对对此提问。
but you didn't object to the question then.

1331
01:26:01,490 --> 01:26:04,930
是否那是因为你知道巴尼・奎尔
在强奸和殴打了…
Is that because you know Barney Quill 
bathed and changed...

1332
01:26:05,030 --> 01:26:07,820
这位可怜的女士之后，
洗了澡换了衣服？
after he raped and beat hell
out of this poor woman?

1333
01:26:07,930 --> 01:26:11,300
法官大人，在这个法庭上，似乎人人
都受到了审判，除了曼尼昂先生。我必须抗议……
Your Honor, everybody in this court
is being tried except Mr. Manion.

1334
01:26:11,300 --> 01:26:16,230
你给我听好了，这是对一起谋杀案进行的
交叉质询，而不是一场高中生之间的辩论！
Now listen, this is a cross-examination
murder case, not a high school debate!

1335
01:26:16,240 --> 01:26:20,500
你和丹瑟想干什么？轻率地将这个士兵
送入大牢你们就满意啦？
What are you trying to do, 
railroad this soldier into the clink?

1336
01:26:20,510 --> 01:26:22,740
比格勒先生，你是个有资历的律师，
Mr. Biegler, you are an experienced attorney...

1337
01:26:22,840 --> 01:26:25,570
你不应该有这样失控的发作。
and you know better than to make such an outburst.

1338
01:26:25,680 --> 01:26:28,870
我不会容忍这样的放纵。
I will not tolerate intemperance of this sort.

1339
01:26:28,880 --> 01:26:31,910
如果你再一次试探本庭的忍耐度，
If you once again try the patience of this court...

1340
01:26:31,920 --> 01:26:34,360
我会判你藐视法庭。
I shall hold you in contempt.

1341
01:26:35,460 --> 01:26:37,520
对不起，
Sorry.

1342
01:26:37,630 --> 01:26:39,720
法官大人，
Your Honor...

1343
01:26:39,830 --> 01:26:43,260
我向您道歉，不会再发生了。
I apologize and it won't happen again.

1344
01:26:43,360 --> 01:26:45,390
从记录中删除证人的回答，
The witness's answer will be stricken...

1345
01:26:45,500 --> 01:26:48,370
陪审团不要考虑他的回答。
and the jury will disregard the answer.

1346
01:26:48,470 --> 01:26:51,230
你可以继续了，比格勒先生。
Now you may proceed, Mr. Biegler.

1347
01:26:51,340 --> 01:26:52,310
好的，先生。
Yes, sir.

1348
01:26:53,280 --> 01:26:58,910
莱蒙先生，那天晚上曼尼昂中尉
将你弄醒并自首之前，
On the night when Lt. Manion 
awakened you and turned himself in...

1349
01:26:58,910 --> 01:27:03,080
你有没有被其它动静吵醒过――
有没有其它事情打搅过你的睡梦？
had you been awakened before-- had
anything else disturbed your slumbers?

1350
01:27:03,080 --> 01:27:05,550
- 没有，先生。
- 士兵们没有唱歌？
- No, sir.
- There were no soldiers singing?

1351
01:27:05,650 --> 01:27:08,210
没有，先生。10点后公园里没有人唱歌。
No, sir. Not in my park after 10:00.

1352
01:27:08,320 --> 01:27:12,560
- 也没有女人的叫声。
- 嗯，有叫声从大门方向传过来。
- There were no women screaming?
- Those screams were down by the gate.

1353
01:27:12,560 --> 01:27:14,190
反对！反对！
Objection!

1354
01:27:14,300 --> 01:27:17,200
我看不出现在有何反对的理由，罗德威克先生。
I see no reason for objecting yet.

1355
01:27:17,300 --> 01:27:20,390
跟我们说说那些叫声吧，莱蒙先生。
Tell us about those screams.

1356
01:27:20,500 --> 01:27:23,990
我自己并没听到。
公园里有几个俄亥俄来的旅游者，
I didn't hear them myself. There were 
tourists from Ohio in the park...

1357
01:27:24,110 --> 01:27:26,570
他们听到了喊叫，第二天告诉我的。
and they heard them and told me 
about it the next day.

1358
01:27:26,670 --> 01:27:29,580
- 现在轮到你了，罗德威克先生。
- 这一证词无法律资格，
- Now, Mr. Lodwick.
- This testimony is incompetent...

1359
01:27:29,680 --> 01:27:33,740
是与本案无关的道听途说，
是非实质性的、非决定性的……
hearsay, irrelevant, immaterial, inconclusive--

1360
01:27:33,850 --> 01:27:37,880
我可受够了。证人交给你吧，罗德威克先生。
Well, that's too much for me.
The witness is yours, Mr. Lodwick.

1361
01:27:37,890 --> 01:27:40,010
嗯？噢…呃…
Huh?

1362
01:27:40,020 --> 01:27:42,080
我没问题了。
No questions.

1363
01:27:42,190 --> 01:27:44,250
证人可以退席了。
The witness may step down.

1364
01:27:44,360 --> 01:27:46,160
传唤你的下一个证人。
Call your next witness.

1365
01:27:48,160 --> 01:27:50,490
詹姆士・德构警探。
Detective Sergeant James Durgo.

1366
01:27:52,270 --> 01:27:54,830
- 嗨，保利。
- 嗨，詹姆士。过来。
- Hi, Paulie.
- Hi, Jim. Come here.

1367
01:27:56,540 --> 01:27:59,470
庭审一休息，你就打电话给
那位军队里的精神病医生，
As soon as we break, you'd better phone 
that army psychiatrist.

1368
01:27:59,570 --> 01:28:02,270
- 告诉他后天到达这儿。
- 行。
- Tell him to be here day after tomorrow.
- Will do.

1369
01:28:02,380 --> 01:28:05,740
你能不能告诉我帕内尔去哪儿啦？
Will you please tell me where Parnell has gone?

1370
01:28:05,850 --> 01:28:07,780
不行。
Won't do.

1371
01:28:07,880 --> 01:28:10,180
那么你被解雇了。
Well, you're fired.

1372
01:28:10,290 --> 01:28:12,950
在你没付我薪水之前，你不能解雇我。
You can't fire me till you pay me.

1373
01:28:13,050 --> 01:28:15,280
…州警警探，詹姆士・德构。
Detective Sergeant James Durgo of the state police.

1374
01:28:15,390 --> 01:28:18,620
在巴尼・奎尔被杀的那个晚上，
你是否接到雷鸣湾的代理治安官…
Were you called to Thunder Bay by 
Deputy Sheriff Lemon of Thunder Bay...

1375
01:28:18,730 --> 01:28:20,660
莱蒙的电话，让你去雷鸣湾？
on the night Barney Quill was killed?

1376
01:28:20,760 --> 01:28:24,530
是的，先生。我和我的搭档一起，
第一个赶到那儿。
Yes, sir. My companion officer and I
were the first to be called in.

1377
01:28:24,600 --> 01:28:28,300
德构警探，当你们赶到曼尼昂的
车房时，谁在那儿？
When you arrived at the Manion 
trailer, who was there?

1378
01:28:28,400 --> 01:28:30,630
曼尼昂中尉和他的妻子在那里。
Lt. Manion and his wife were there.

1379
01:28:30,740 --> 01:28:33,970
曼尼昂中尉对你说了些什么？
What did Lt. Manion say to you?

1380
01:28:34,080 --> 01:28:37,340
他说他妻子和巴尼・奎尔有了点麻烦。
He said that his wife had had 
some trouble with Barney Quill.

1381
01:28:37,450 --> 01:28:40,210
他去酒店向奎尔开了枪。
He had gone to the tavern and shot Quill.

1382
01:28:40,320 --> 01:28:43,610
他问我们奎尔是否还活着。
我们告诉他他已经死了。
He asked us whether Quill was dead 
or not. We told him he was.

1383
01:28:43,720 --> 01:28:46,650
曼尼昂中尉听到这一消息后有什么反应？
How did Lt. Manion take this information?

1384
01:28:46,750 --> 01:28:48,520
他看上去并不吃惊。
He didn't seem surprised.

1385
01:28:48,620 --> 01:28:50,520
然后你们干了什么，德构警探？
What did you do then?

1386
01:28:50,630 --> 01:28:52,530
我问他要他用过的枪。
I asked for the gun he'd used.

1387
01:28:52,630 --> 01:28:56,720
那晚你有没有将曼尼昂中尉
带到这儿的铁城县监狱？
Did you take Lt. Manion to the county 
jail here in Iron City that same night?

1388
01:28:56,830 --> 01:28:59,530
是的，先生。我们和他妻子一起，
驾车将中尉带到这里。
Yes, sir. We drove the Lieutenant 
down with his wife.

1389
01:28:59,630 --> 01:29:04,730
在通往铁城的路上，
中尉有没有进一步说他开枪的事？
On the drive to Iron City, did Manion 
talk further about the shooting?

1390
01:29:04,840 --> 01:29:08,400
他说如果有机会让他重新选择的话，
他仍然会这么做。
He remarked that if he had the whole 
thing to do over, he'd still do it.

1391
01:29:08,510 --> 01:29:12,170
在所有这期间――在车房里，
在驱车来铁城的路上，
During all this, at the trailer, 
the drive to Iron City...

1392
01:29:12,280 --> 01:29:14,180
曼尼昂中尉看上去怎么样？
how did Lt. Manion appear to you?

1393
01:29:15,480 --> 01:29:18,980
他大部分时间都很沉默，
看上去头脑也很清楚。
He was very quiet most of the time.
Seemed clearheaded.

1394
01:29:19,090 --> 01:29:23,290
你是不是说他完全处于清醒状态？
Would you say he was in complete
possession of his faculties?

1395
01:29:23,390 --> 01:29:25,990
- 在我看来是这样。
- 你来问证人。
- Seemed so to me.
- Your witness.

1396
01:29:26,090 --> 01:29:29,890
德构警官，你作证说曼尼昂中尉跟你说…
Sergeant Durgo, you testified 
that Lt. Manion told you...

1397
01:29:30,000 --> 01:29:35,300
在他得知他妻子和奎尔有了点麻烦后
他开枪打的巴尼・奎尔。
he shot Barney Quill after he learned 
his wife had some trouble with Quill.

1398
01:29:35,400 --> 01:29:38,840
曼尼昂中尉用的是“有了点麻烦”这些词吗？
Were these the words Lt. Manion used, "some trouble"?

1399
01:29:38,940 --> 01:29:41,270
不，先生，这些是我的话，不是他的用词。
No, sir. Those were my words, not his.

1400
01:29:41,380 --> 01:29:44,370
那么这是你自己的主意吗，
到这里来用你自己的词？
And was it your notion to come here 
and use your own words?

1401
01:29:44,480 --> 01:29:46,140
不，先生，不是的。
No, sir.

1402
01:29:46,250 --> 01:29:48,550
那么是不是此法庭在座的某位…
And was the suggestion to call it "some trouble"...

1403
01:29:48,650 --> 01:29:51,580
建议你这样说的呢，“有了点麻烦”？
made by somebody here in the courtroom?

1404
01:29:53,390 --> 01:29:54,510
是的，先生，是这样的。
Yes, sir.

1405
01:29:55,890 --> 01:30:00,620
好的，警官，你能不能告诉法庭，
在描述他妻子所碰到的麻烦时，
Sergeant, would you tell the court 
what words Lt. Manion actually used...

1406
01:30:00,730 --> 01:30:03,030
曼尼昂中尉实际上是怎么说的？
to describe the trouble his wife had had?

1407
01:30:03,130 --> 01:30:05,730
反对，法官大人。他又来了不是。
Objection. We've been over this before.

1408
01:30:05,830 --> 01:30:08,960
这个问题和本庭所讨论的任何论点无关。
This information would not be relevant 
to any issues before the court.

1409
01:30:09,070 --> 01:30:11,660
我的“有了点麻烦”的问题是由…
This statement concerning some trouble 
was brought out...

1410
01:30:11,770 --> 01:30:14,640
你对控方证人德构警官的初度询问而引起的。
during the direct examination of Sergeant Durgo.

1411
01:30:14,740 --> 01:30:17,940
到现在为止，只要和劳拉・曼尼昂有关的证词，
Up to now, you've adroitly restricted all testimony...

1412
01:30:18,050 --> 01:30:20,140
你都敏捷地进行限制。
as far as Laura Manion's concerned.

1413
01:30:20,250 --> 01:30:23,550
很好，猫腻开始藏不住了，
那就让我们彻底揭开来看看好了。
All right, the cat's out of the bag.
It's fair game for me to chase it.

1414
01:30:23,650 --> 01:30:27,110
这种说法很令人不快，比格勒先生，
不要太过分了。
This is a sore point, Mr. Biegler,
and it's getting sorer.

1415
01:30:27,220 --> 01:30:29,420
我想听听控方的意见。
I'd like to hear from the prosecution.

1416
01:30:29,520 --> 01:30:34,020
辩方的任务是证明被告开枪时的“临时性精神错乱”。
Burden is on defense to prove temporary 
insanity at the time of the shooting.

1417
01:30:34,130 --> 01:30:38,060
因此，如果导致辩方声称的精神错乱的原因
是本案的关键所在的话，
Now, if the reason for the alleged
insanity is important to this case...

1418
01:30:38,170 --> 01:30:40,690
那么应该把这个关键问题交给一个能胜任的证人――
then that is a matter for a competent witness--

1419
01:30:40,800 --> 01:30:44,430
一个人类精神方面问题的专家――来处理。
an expert on the subject of the human mind.

1420
01:30:44,540 --> 01:30:47,200
而辩方一直在做的却是…
What the defense is trying to do...

1421
01:30:47,310 --> 01:30:50,000
引入一些耸人听闻的材料，
is introduce some sensational material...

1422
01:30:50,110 --> 01:30:53,650
其目的就是为了隐匿真正的问题。
for the purposes of obscuring the real issues.

1423
01:30:53,650 --> 01:30:58,650
法官大人，要是陪审团不先搞清楚
这整个审判背后的原因――
How can the jury accurately estimate 
the testimony being given here...

1424
01:30:58,650 --> 01:31:00,000
曼尼昂中尉为什么要杀死巴尼・奎尔，
那么他们怎么能准确判断…
unless they first know the reason 
behind this whole trial--

1425
01:31:00,000 --> 01:31:02,870
在这里给出的这些证词呢？
why Lt. Manion shot Barney Quill?

1426
01:31:02,870 --> 01:31:06,830
而控方却试图将动机和行为分离。
The prosecution would like to separate
the motive from the act.

1427
01:31:06,940 --> 01:31:11,940
这就像是要把一个苹果的核心取出来，
却不想破坏苹果的表皮。
That's like trying to take the core 
from an apple without breaking the skin.

1428
01:31:12,050 --> 01:31:16,990
而我们辩护的核心就是：
被告的“临时性精神错乱”，
Now the core of our defense is that 
the defendant's temporary insanity...

1429
01:31:17,090 --> 01:31:20,450
是由所谓的和奎尔“有了点麻烦”所导致的。
was triggered by the so-called trouble with Quill.

1430
01:31:20,560 --> 01:31:22,680
因此我请求法庭…
And I beg the court--

1431
01:31:22,790 --> 01:31:28,090
我…我请求法庭，允许我把这个苹果切了进去。
I-- I beg the court to let me cut into the apple.

1432
01:31:29,030 --> 01:31:32,860
我仍然坚持我们的反对，法官大人。
Our objection still stands, Your Honor.

1433
01:31:46,150 --> 01:31:48,380
反对无效。
Objection overruled.

1434
01:31:54,660 --> 01:31:57,960
德构警官，请告诉法庭…
Sergeant Durgo, tell the court...

1435
01:31:58,060 --> 01:32:02,050
曼尼昂中尉是如何描述
他妻子和奎尔的麻烦的。
how Lt. Manion described 
the trouble his wife had with Quill.

1436
01:32:02,170 --> 01:32:05,600
他告诉我们奎尔强奸了他的妻子。
He told us that Quill had raped his wife.

1437
01:32:05,700 --> 01:32:10,700
那么你能不能大概回忆一下，关于强奸
曼尼昂中尉说了些什么？
Now, can you recall generally what 
Lt. Manion told you about this rape?

1438
01:32:10,810 --> 01:32:14,940
好的，先生。他说他一吃完饭就去睡了。
Yes, sir. He said he'd been asleep 
right after dinner.

1439
01:32:15,050 --> 01:32:19,110
他被一阵喧闹吵醒――是叫喊声，他认为。
He was waked up by some noise--
screams he thought.

1440
01:32:19,220 --> 01:32:23,210
他起床打开了车房门，走了出去。
He got up, opened the trailer door 
and went outside.

1441
01:32:23,320 --> 01:32:26,350
他妻子从黑暗里跑了出来，倒在他的手臂里。
His wife came running out of the dark 
and fell into his arms.

1442
01:32:26,460 --> 01:32:29,720
你在车房见到他妻子时，她看上去怎样？
As you saw his wife in the trailer, 
how did she look?

1443
01:32:29,830 --> 01:32:32,920
她有点歇斯底里，她被打得很厉害。
She was a little hysterical.
She'd been pretty badly beaten up.

1444
01:32:33,030 --> 01:32:35,930
她的脸和双臂有大块乌青的瘀伤。
She had big black bruises 
all over her face and arms.

1445
01:32:36,030 --> 01:32:39,200
曼尼昂夫人告诉你强奸和殴打的情况了吗？
Did Mrs. Manion tell you 
about this rape and beating?

1446
01:32:39,300 --> 01:32:42,170
- 是的。
- 她带你去事发地点了？
- She did.
- Did she take you to where it happened?

1447
01:32:42,270 --> 01:32:43,740
是的，先生，在第二天上午。
Yes, the next morning.

1448
01:32:43,840 --> 01:32:49,110
你有没有发现什么呢？任何与曼尼昂夫人
告诉你的情况有关的什么证据？
Did you find anything there pertaining 
to the story Mrs. Manion told you?

1449
01:32:49,210 --> 01:32:54,210
在林中的小径上，我们发现了
一些轮胎印和一些狗的足印，
On the lane in the woods we found 
some tire tracks and some dog tracks...

1450
01:32:54,320 --> 01:32:58,880
还有一只皮质的盒子，
里面是一副角质架的眼镜。
and a leather case with 
some horn-rimmed glasses inside.

1451
01:32:58,990 --> 01:33:01,620
我们也试着找…
We also looked for...

1452
01:33:01,730 --> 01:33:04,790
曼尼昂夫人的一件内衣，但是没找到。
a certain undergarment of Mrs. Manion's, 
but we didn't find it.

1453
01:33:04,900 --> 01:33:08,890
请双方律师到法官席前来。
Will the attorneys for both sides 
approach the bench?

1454
01:33:11,940 --> 01:33:15,770
比格勒先生，你最终还是
把你的强奸带进了这个案子。
Mr. Biegler, you've finally got 
your rape into the case.

1455
01:33:15,870 --> 01:33:19,830
我认为从现在起，陪审团必须了解所有的细节。
I think all the details should now 
be made clear to the jury.

1456
01:33:19,940 --> 01:33:23,670
- 你同意吗，罗德威克先生？
- 完全同意。
- Do you agree, Mr. Lodwick?
- Absolutely.

1457
01:33:23,780 --> 01:33:27,270
刚才提到的“内衣”到底是什么东西？
What exactly was the undergarment just referred to?

1458
01:33:27,380 --> 01:33:29,110
内裤，法官大人。
Panties, Your Honor.

1459
01:33:29,220 --> 01:33:32,660
- 你觉得它在后面还会出现吗？
- 是的，大人。
- Do you expect this to come up again?
- Yes, sir.

1460
01:33:32,760 --> 01:33:37,060
“内裤”这个词听上去有点轻浮。
There's a certain light connotation 
attached to the word "panties."

1461
01:33:37,160 --> 01:33:39,320
我们可以想一个其它的词代替吗?
Can we find another name for them?

1462
01:33:39,430 --> 01:33:42,160
我从没听过我妻子还有什么其它的叫法。
I never heard my wife call them anything else.

1463
01:33:42,270 --> 01:33:45,430
- 你呢，比格勒先生。
- 我是单身，法官大人。
- Mr. Biegler?
- I'm a bachelor, Your Honor.

1464
01:33:45,540 --> 01:33:48,270
真太有用了。丹瑟先生？
That's a great help. Mr. Dancer?

1465
01:33:48,370 --> 01:33:53,240
大战时我到过海外，法官大人，
我知道法文里怎么说。
I was overseas during the war.
I learned a French word.

1466
01:33:53,340 --> 01:33:55,610
但是我担心那个词有点挑逗性。
I'm afraid that might be slightly suggestive.

1467
01:33:55,710 --> 01:33:57,700
大部分法文单词都有点挑逗性。
Most French words are.

1468
01:33:57,810 --> 01:34:01,150
好吧，先生们，回到你们的座位上。
All right, gentlemen, back to your places.

1469
01:34:01,250 --> 01:34:06,150
为了有助于陪审团理解，
特别是为了旁听的观众，
For the benefit of the jury, but more 
especially for the spectators...

1470
01:34:06,260 --> 01:34:10,160
在上面的证词中所提到的“内衣”，
严格的说是指…
the undergarment referred to 
in the testimony was, to be exact...

1471
01:34:10,260 --> 01:34:13,290
曼尼昂夫人的内裤。
Mrs. Manion's panties.

1472
01:34:16,200 --> 01:34:19,970
我希望你们停止窃笑，下不为例。
I wanted you to get your snickering over and done with.

1473
01:34:20,070 --> 01:34:24,340
这条内裤在此番庭审过程中，将还会被提及，
This pair of panties will be mentioned 
again in the course of this trial.

1474
01:34:24,440 --> 01:34:27,840
到时候在我的法庭上，不允许出现任何笑声，
And when it happens, there will not be 
one laugh, one snicker...

1475
01:34:27,840 --> 01:34:32,100
不允许窃笑，不允许痴笑，甚至不允许暗笑。
one giggle or even one smirk in my courtroom.

1476
01:34:32,120 --> 01:34:35,710
鉴于这条内裤已经引起了一名男子的暴死，
There isn't anything comic about a pair of panties...

1477
01:34:35,820 --> 01:34:39,310
也有可能导致另一名男子的囚禁，
which figure in the violent death of one man...

1478
01:34:39,420 --> 01:34:43,620
它其实没有任何喜剧色彩。
and the possible incarceration of another.

1479
01:34:43,730 --> 01:34:45,460
继续，比格勒先生。
Proceed, Mr. Biegler.

1480
01:34:45,560 --> 01:34:47,690
你有没有给曼尼昂夫人做测谎仪测试？
Did you give Mrs. Manion a lie detector test?

1481
01:34:47,800 --> 01:34:51,260
反对。测谎仪测试在法庭上
不能作为可接受的证据。
Objection. A polygraph test is 
inadmissible evidence in our courts.

1482
01:34:51,370 --> 01:34:54,740
我只是问他有没有做，
我又没问他测试结果。
I only asked if he gave the test.
I didn't ask the results.

1483
01:34:54,840 --> 01:34:56,740
你可以回答这个问题。
He may answer that.

1484
01:34:56,840 --> 01:34:59,870
在她的要求下，我给她做了测谎仪测试。
I gave her a lie detector test at her request.

1485
01:34:59,980 --> 01:35:03,470
那么，在经过了所有这些调查之后，
你相信曼尼昂夫人吗？
Now after all this investigation, 
did you believe Mrs. Manion?

1486
01:35:03,580 --> 01:35:06,180
- 我相信。
- 甚至在做了测谎仪测试之后？
- I did.
- Even after the lie detector test?

1487
01:35:06,180 --> 01:35:11,640
法官大人，我反对这个提问！那是被告律师
明目张胆地利用卑鄙而狡猾的逃避手段。
That question constitutes flagrant 
subterfuge on part of the defense.

1488
01:35:11,760 --> 01:35:13,350
反对有效。
Objection sustained.

1489
01:35:14,460 --> 01:35:17,990
陪审团的女士们先生们，测谎仪测试…
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury, 
a polygraph or lie detector test...

1490
01:35:18,100 --> 01:35:20,000
不能作为可接受的证据，
is not admissible in evidence...

1491
01:35:20,100 --> 01:35:22,220
因为从来没有人否定…
because no one has ever been quite sure...

1492
01:35:22,330 --> 01:35:26,100
有人可以对测谎仪撒谎并通过测试。
that some people couldn't lie 
to a lie detector and get away with it.

1493
01:35:26,200 --> 01:35:27,830
继续，比格勒先生。
Go ahead.

1494
01:35:27,940 --> 01:35:31,930
总之，德构警官，以你自己心智和头脑判断，
In any case, you yourself 
in your own heart and mind...

1495
01:35:32,040 --> 01:35:34,670
你非常确信曼尼昂夫人是诚实的？
are quite convinced of Mrs. Manion's honesty?

1496
01:35:34,780 --> 01:35:37,340
- 是的，先生。
- 我问完了。
- Yes, sir.
- That's all.

1497
01:35:38,620 --> 01:35:41,970
请等一会儿。
好的，当然。
Just a moment. 
Yes, of course.

1498
01:35:43,950 --> 01:35:48,860
德构警官，除了在林间小径，
你有没有在别的地方搜寻过那条内裤？
Did you look for the panties elsewhere 
other than the lane in the woods?

1499
01:35:48,960 --> 01:35:52,190
我们还搜查了巴尼・奎尔的轿车，
和他旅店的房间。
We looked in Barney Quill's car, 
his room in the hotel.

1500
01:35:52,300 --> 01:35:53,760
我们没有找到内裤。
We didn't find them.

1501
01:35:53,860 --> 01:35:57,430
你知道曼尼昂夫人为什么
要求接受测谎仪测试吗？
Do you know why Mrs. Manion 
requested a lie detector test?

1502
01:35:57,530 --> 01:35:59,430
- 我记得她曾说过。
- 说过什么？
- I know what she said.
- What?

1503
01:35:59,540 --> 01:36:03,400
她想让大家相信她的话，
因为她知道那样会有助于他丈夫。
She wanted everyone to believe her story 
because she knew it'd help her husband.

1504
01:36:03,410 --> 01:36:05,170
那是她给你的唯一理由吗？
Was that the only reason she gave?

1505
01:36:05,280 --> 01:36:09,580
她说她已经向她丈夫起过誓，
她希望别的人也都相信她。
Said she swore to her husband. Said she 
wanted everyone else to believe it too.

1506
01:36:09,680 --> 01:36:11,580
请稍等一下，法官大人。
One moment, please.

1507
01:36:15,320 --> 01:36:17,910
问问他她以何种方式起的誓。
Ask him in what manner she swore.

1508
01:36:18,020 --> 01:36:21,320
那么曼尼昂夫人有没有说
她是怎样向她丈夫起的誓？
Did Mrs. Manion say how 
she had sworn to her husband?

1509
01:36:21,420 --> 01:36:25,360
说了，先生。她说她以《玫瑰经》起的誓。
Yes, sir. She said she had sworn on a rosary.

1510
01:36:25,460 --> 01:36:30,300
德构警官，那条林中小径，
是干什么用的？它通向哪里？
This lane in the woods, 
what's it used for, where does it go?

1511
01:36:30,400 --> 01:36:33,600
以前是运伐木用的，不通向哪里，是死路。
It used to be a logging road.
It doesn't go anyplace, just stops.

1512
01:36:33,700 --> 01:36:35,600
现在谁会用呢？
Who uses it now?

1513
01:36:35,710 --> 01:36:37,940
我想是孩子们去公园玩时用的路。
I think it's a road kids drive down to park.

1514
01:36:38,040 --> 01:36:40,670
- 你的意思是那是一条情人小径？
- 我想是的。
- You mean it's a lovers' lane?
- I think so.

1515
01:36:40,780 --> 01:36:43,340
- 你来问吧，比格勒先生。
- 没有问题了。
- The witness is yours.
- No more questions.

1516
01:36:43,350 --> 01:36:47,180
- 证人可以退下了。
- 鉴于法官大人您裁定…
- The witness may step down.
- In view of evidence concerning rape...

1517
01:36:47,190 --> 01:36:49,550
涉及强奸的证据可以纳入本案，
which Your Honor has ruled admissible...

1518
01:36:49,550 --> 01:36:51,480
公诉方请求30分钟休庭，
the prosecution asks for a 30-minute recess...

1519
01:36:51,490 --> 01:36:55,080
以便我方带另一位证人出庭，
尽管我们原本并没有安排。
in order to bring in another witness 
we had not anticipated using?

1520
01:36:55,080 --> 01:36:57,790
好的。休庭30分钟。
All right. We'll take a 30-minute recess.

1521
01:36:57,790 --> 01:36:59,280
现在休庭。
Recess.

1522
01:37:06,240 --> 01:37:08,670
为什么你没有告诉我那什么《玫瑰经》？
Why didn't you tell me about that rosary?

1523
01:37:10,010 --> 01:37:11,910
我忘了。
I forgot it.

1524
01:37:12,010 --> 01:37:16,570
我们没忘。曼尼说也许我们不应该再提起此事。
We didn't forget it. Manny said maybe 
we shouldn't tell that again.

1525
01:37:16,680 --> 01:37:20,580
因为这看上去像有别的问题――
像是我不相信她。
It might have looked like something 
else-- like I didn't believe her.

1526
01:37:21,750 --> 01:37:26,920
- 你还有什么事没告诉我？
- 什么都告诉你了，所有事都告诉你了。
- How much more didn't you tell me?
- We told you everything else.

1527
01:37:27,020 --> 01:37:29,050
是这样吗，劳拉？
Is that right, Laura?

1528
01:37:29,160 --> 01:37:31,320
噢，是的，所有的事。
Oh, yes, everything else.

1529
01:37:31,430 --> 01:37:33,590
好的，听着，你们两个。
Now get this, both of you.

1530
01:37:33,700 --> 01:37:37,630
当你们走上证人席时，
我希望你们讲出事实。
When you get up on that stand, 
I want you to tell the truth.

1531
01:37:37,730 --> 01:37:40,230
我希望你们除了事实，不讲别的。
I don't want you to tell anything but the truth.

1532
01:37:40,340 --> 01:37:45,210
你们不要试着撒谎，不要试着隐瞒任何事情，
否则的话你们会被生吞活剥的。
Don't try and lie or conceal anything 
or you get skinned alive.

1533
01:37:45,310 --> 01:37:48,340
丹瑟那伙计就要出场了。
