精疲力尽、饥肠辘辘。
And I'm sure the jury is 
equally tired and hungry.

1666
01:44:58,590 --> 01:45:02,790
明天是辩护方的主辩，
我希望辩方律师加快一点，
Tomorrow the defense takes over 
and with expedition, prayer...

1667
01:45:02,790 --> 01:45:04,890
收敛一点，自我约束一点，
and a little self-discipline 
on the part of counsel...

1668
01:45:04,900 --> 01:45:07,830
这样也许到周六晚上，我们就可以结束了。
perhaps we can reach an end by Saturday night.

1669
01:45:07,830 --> 01:45:10,030
现在休庭吧。
Will you adjourn court?

1670
01:45:10,630 --> 01:45:12,560
注意，注意，注意，
Hear ye, hear ye, hear ye.

1671
01:45:12,570 --> 01:45:16,270
本法庭现在休庭，
明天上午9点继续开庭。
This court stands adjourned 
until 9:00 tomorrow morning.

1672
01:45:57,260 --> 01:46:00,260
他就撞了一下，没什么特别严重的。
He's banged up a little, but there 
doesn't seem to be anything else.

1673
01:46:00,260 --> 01:46:02,360
我们再观察他一两天吧。
We'd like to watch him for a day or so.

1674
01:46:02,860 --> 01:46:04,960
他损坏了什么东西吗？
How much damage did he do?

1675
01:46:04,960 --> 01:46:07,480
撞坏了一道大门和一扇谷仓的门。
Wrecked a gate and a barn door.

1676
01:46:08,260 --> 01:46:10,690
而且他没有驾照。
He hasn't got a driver's license.

1677
01:46:11,860 --> 01:46:15,700
当他能动时，他必须去普通治安法庭报道，
He'll have to appear 
in the J.P. court when he's able...

1678
01:46:15,700 --> 01:46:17,300
老傻瓜。
the old fool.

1679
01:46:17,300 --> 01:46:19,700
对死者厚道点。
Speak kindly of the dead.

1680
01:46:19,700 --> 01:46:21,970
能让我和尸体单独呆一会儿吗？
Mind if I have a minute with the corpse?

1681
01:46:21,970 --> 01:46:23,530
当然，保利。
Sure.

1682
01:46:27,240 --> 01:46:30,280
说说看，你到底在忙活什么呢，
Now, was it worth trying to kill yourself...

1683
01:46:30,280 --> 01:46:33,380
连老命都不要了？
for whatever it is you've been up to?

1684
01:46:33,380 --> 01:46:35,380
庭审进行得如何？
How is the trial going?

1685
01:46:35,380 --> 01:46:38,620
我整出不少动静，丹瑟针锋相对。
I'm making a lot of noise 
and Dancer's racking up all the points.

1686
01:46:38,620 --> 01:46:42,050
可是快点啊，你究竟去哪儿啦？
But come on. Where have you been?

1687
01:46:42,050 --> 01:46:46,330
奎尔从北面的圣玛丽急流市【安大略】
雇来的玛丽・皮兰特。
Quill hired Mary Pilant up north 
of Sault St. Marie.

1688
01:46:46,330 --> 01:46:50,730
我感到奇怪的是他为何大老远地
跑这么多路去雇某个人为他工作。
Struck me funny he'd go all the way up 
there to hire somebody to work for him.

1689
01:46:50,730 --> 01:46:52,900
于是我也去那里打探了一下。
I've been up there nosing around.

1690
01:46:52,900 --> 01:46:55,130
你发现什么有用的东西了吗？
Did you find anything useful?

1691
01:46:55,140 --> 01:46:58,260
我查到了她的出生证。
Not until I looked up her birth certificate.

1692
01:46:58,260 --> 01:47:02,010
1934年，她出生于安大略的盲人河，
Born Blind River, Ontario, 1934...

1693
01:47:02,010 --> 01:47:03,970
未婚所生。
out of wedlock.

1694
01:47:04,010 --> 01:47:08,110
母亲是一个女侍者，叫西蒙妮・皮兰特。
Mother was a waitress, Simone Pilant.

1695
01:47:08,120 --> 01:47:12,610
父亲是伐木工人，叫巴尼・奎尔。
Father was a lumberjack named Barney Quill.

1696
01:47:19,830 --> 01:47:23,800
- 我想见玛丽・皮兰特小姐。
- 已经很晚了，先生。
- I'd like to see Miss Mary Pilant.
- It's late, mister.

1697
01:47:23,800 --> 01:47:25,930
我知道，我知道。但这事很重要。
I know. This is important.

1698
01:47:25,930 --> 01:47:28,270
- 真的很重要？
- 真的很重要。
- Real important?
- Real important.

1699
01:47:32,880 --> 01:47:35,270
- 是我。
- 皮兰特小姐，抱歉把你吵醒了。
- Yes?
- Miss Pilant, sorry if I woke you.

1700
01:47:35,280 --> 01:47:37,480
有个人想见你，说有重要事情。
There's a guy to see you.
Says it's real important.

1701
01:47:37,480 --> 01:47:39,780
- 你的名……
- 保罗・比格勒。
- What's your--
- Paul Biegler.

1702
01:47:39,780 --> 01:47:43,080
- 我不想见他。
- 好的。
- I don't wish to see him,
- Okay.

1703
01:47:43,920 --> 01:47:46,120
她说那事不够重要。
She said it's not important enough.

1704
01:47:46,120 --> 01:47:50,260
好吧，那你再给她打过去，告诉她
我提到了安大略的盲人河。
Call her back and tell her I mentioned 
Blind River, Ontario.

1705
01:47:50,260 --> 01:47:52,560
我会在酒吧里。
I'll be in the bar.

1706
01:48:08,310 --> 01:48:09,660
晚上好，阿尔方斯。
Good evening, Alphonse.

1707
01:48:09,860 --> 01:48:12,690
喝点什么还是仅四下瞅瞅？
Drinking or just snooping?

1708
01:48:12,700 --> 01:48:16,650
唔，我想我两样都会做一点儿。
你看先给我来点啤酒怎么样？
I think I'll try a little of both.
What do you say we start with a beer.

1709
01:48:21,860 --> 01:48:24,790
本店请客。
你只能得到这些――一瓶啤酒。
On the house.
And that's all you get-- a beer.

1710
01:48:24,790 --> 01:48:26,860
没有问题，没有回答。
No questions, no answers.

1711
01:48:26,860 --> 01:48:29,430
我只是个律师，想做好我的工作。
I'm just a lawyer trying to do my job.

1712
01:48:29,430 --> 01:48:31,770
你有什么好怕的呢，嗯？
What are you so afraid of?

1713
01:48:34,600 --> 01:48:36,760
我们坐到那边去，行吗？
Let's sit over there, please.

1714
01:48:42,740 --> 01:48:47,210
皮兰特小姐，我得向你道歉，
因为我上次来这儿时不是太有礼貌。
Miss Pilant, I owe you an apology.
I was rough when I was here before.

1715
01:48:48,220 --> 01:48:50,320
我不知道巴尼・奎尔是你父亲。
I didn't know Barney Quill was your father.

1716
01:48:50,320 --> 01:48:52,860
你不是为了向我道歉才来的吧。
You didn't come here just to apologize.

1717
01:48:52,860 --> 01:48:55,260
不是，但是道歉是目的之一。
No, but the apology was part of it.

1718
01:48:55,260 --> 01:48:59,990
开诚布公地说，我是希望
能够和你达成一点谅解。
To tell you the truth, I was hoping 
it would thaw you out a little bit.

1719
01:49:00,000 --> 01:49:04,260
我希望你做的，就是听我说几句话，就几分钟。
All I want you to do is listen to me, 
just for a few minutes.

1720
01:49:04,260 --> 01:49:09,230
我需要一些强有力的证据，用来支持
劳拉・曼尼昂有关强奸的说法。
I need some strong evidence to back up 
Laura Manion's story about the rape.

1721
01:49:09,240 --> 01:49:12,740
公诉方会严厉抨击这一说法。
The prosecution's gonna attack 
that story pretty hard.

1722
01:49:12,740 --> 01:49:15,340
如果陪审团认定她在撒谎，
And if the jury thinks she's lying...

1723
01:49:15,340 --> 01:49:18,260
那么他们的裁决就会对曼尼昂不利，你明白吗？
that could turn the decision against Manion.

1724
01:49:18,260 --> 01:49:20,380
那么她没有撒谎吗？
Isn't she lying?

1725
01:49:20,380 --> 01:49:23,260
巴尼没有做过她说的事，他不可能做。
Barney didn't do what she said he did.
He couldn't have.

1726
01:49:23,260 --> 01:49:27,520
- 关于你父亲你了解多少？
- 了解一切。
- What did you know about your father?
- All I needed to know.

1727
01:49:27,520 --> 01:49:31,590
他精心照顾我，也精心照顾我妈妈，直到她去世。
He took care of me and my mother 
for as long as she lived.

1728
01:49:31,590 --> 01:49:34,960
当我需要他时，他总是在我身旁。
He was always there when I needed him.

1729
01:49:34,960 --> 01:49:37,630
这就是我了解的父亲，比格勒先生。
That's what I know about my father, Mr. Biegler.

1730
01:49:37,630 --> 01:49:39,930
那会支持劳拉・曼尼昂的说法吗？
Will that back up Laura Manion's story?

1731
01:49:39,940 --> 01:49:43,070
我不是想和你过不去，我也不想伤害你。
I don't want to get at you, hurt you.

1732
01:49:43,070 --> 01:49:45,900
我很赞赏你对你父亲的爱。
I appreciate your affection for your father.

1733
01:49:46,010 --> 01:49:51,540
但是作为一个律师，我见得太多了，
人不可能简单地划分为好人和坏人，
But as a lawyer I've had to learn 
that people aren't just good or bad...

1734
01:49:51,650 --> 01:49:53,640
人是多方面的。
but people are many things.

1735
01:49:53,650 --> 01:49:57,280
我有种感觉，巴尼・奎尔就是多方面的。
And I kind of have a feeling 
Barney Quill was many things.

1736
01:49:57,290 --> 01:50:00,380
- 我不想再听下去了。
- 请别走，请听我说完好吗？
- I don't want to hear any more.
- No, please. Hear me out.

1737
01:50:00,390 --> 01:50:04,360
我相信巴尼跟阿尔・帕盖特
谈过那晚发生的事。
I believe that Barney told Al Paquette 
what happened that night.

1738
01:50:04,360 --> 01:50:07,660
他让他去那扇窗子旁等着曼尼昂。
And he told him to go to this window 
and wait for Manion.

1739
01:50:07,660 --> 01:50:12,500
巴尼呆在吧台后面，
紧挨着枪架，就那样等着。
Barney stayed behind the bar 
next to a gun rack, just waiting.

1740
01:50:12,500 --> 01:50:16,000
曼尼昂走了进来，
刚一迈进那道门就开枪射击，
Manion came in and fired 
the minute he got inside that door...

1741
01:50:16,000 --> 01:50:18,800
第一枪就正好穿过巴尼的心脏。
and the first shot 
went right through Barney's heart.

1742
01:50:18,810 --> 01:50:21,140
下面是我想请你帮我做的。
Now here's what I want you to do.

1743
01:50:21,140 --> 01:50:24,140
我想请你试着说服阿尔，
I want you to try to persuade Al 
to come to the court...

1744
01:50:24,150 --> 01:50:28,880
作为辩方证人出庭，让他告诉法庭
那晚巴尼告诉他的事――
as a defense witness and tell the court
what Barney told him that night--

1745
01:50:28,880 --> 01:50:31,850
也就是他强奸和殴打曼尼昂夫人的事实。
that he raped and assaulted Mrs. Manion.

1746
01:50:31,850 --> 01:50:36,620
阿尔不会把那样的事隐瞒起来。
要真是那样的话，他为什么不把它说出来？
Al wouldn't conceal a thing like that.
Why wouldn't he tell it if it were true?

1747
01:50:36,630 --> 01:50:39,920
我不知道，我不知道。但是我知道这个。
I don't know. But I know this.

1748
01:50:39,930 --> 01:50:43,600
每个人都会爱什么事情或者什么人。
Everybody loves something or someone.

1749
01:50:43,600 --> 01:50:47,930
譬如说我，我爱钓鱼，
还有一个叫帕内尔的老家伙。
Me, I love fishing and an old guy 
by the name of Parnell.

1750
01:50:47,940 --> 01:50:51,540
曼尼昂爱他的自由。
他希望能获得更多一点的自由。
Manion loves his freedom.
He'd like to have a little more of it.

1751
01:50:51,540 --> 01:50:55,670
巴尼爱你，也许阿尔也爱着你。
Barney loved you. Maybe so does Al.

1752
01:50:55,680 --> 01:50:57,840
我不会怪他，
I wouldn't blame him.

1753
01:50:57,850 --> 01:51:01,650
因为他不想伤害你，
或是不想让你知道巴尼的真相――
But he doesn't want to hurt you or 
for you to know the truth about Barney--

1754
01:51:01,650 --> 01:51:03,850
即他可能会变得很危险和残忍。
that he could be dangerous and brutal.

1755
01:51:03,850 --> 01:51:08,480
那么，你能不能就问一下阿尔，
直接了当地问他一下。
Now, if you just ask Al--
if you just ask him right straight out.

1756
01:51:08,980 --> 01:51:10,300
阿尔。
Al.

1757
01:51:18,300 --> 01:51:22,300
阿尔，比格勒先生知道了巴尼是我父亲。
Al, Mr. Biegler knows that Barney was my father.

1758
01:51:23,510 --> 01:51:27,310
他认为关于我父亲被杀的那个晚上，
你知道一些事――
He thinks you know something
about the night my father was killed--

1759
01:51:27,310 --> 01:51:29,140
一些你不愿说出来的事。
something you won't tell.

1760
01:51:29,140 --> 01:51:33,510
律师，我已经告诉过你一次，
那么我再告诉你――没有问题，没有回答。
Lawyer, I told you once and I'll tell 
you again-- No questions, no answers.

1761
01:51:33,520 --> 01:51:35,270
慢着，阿尔！
Wait.

1762
01:51:37,260 --> 01:51:40,620
我父亲强奸了曼尼昂夫人吗？
Did my father rape Mrs. Manion?

1763
01:51:40,620 --> 01:51:42,950
巴尼不会伤害一个女人。
Barney wouldn't hurt a woman.

1764
01:51:44,460 --> 01:51:48,760
有没有什么原因
使你不愿告诉我事实真相？
Is there any reason you wouldn't
tell me the truth about that?

1765
01:51:49,260 --> 01:51:51,260
什么原因？
What reason?

1766
01:51:57,040 --> 01:51:59,200
还有别的事吗，比格勒先生？
Anything else?

1767
01:51:59,740 --> 01:52:02,740
我给你和阿尔留下最后判决的通行证，
I'm going to leave a pass 
for you and Al at the trial.

1768
01:52:02,740 --> 01:52:06,610
或许你们乐意去看看
曼尼昂中尉被判有罪。
You might like to watch 
Lt. Manion get convicted.

1769
01:52:06,620 --> 01:52:08,980
你会四下散布玛丽是巴尼女儿的消息吗？
You going to spread it around 
about Mary being Barney's kid?

1770
01:52:08,980 --> 01:52:12,750
不，我不会四下散布，阿尔。
谢谢你的啤酒。
No, I'm not going to spread it 
around, Al. Thank you for the beer.

1771
01:52:12,750 --> 01:52:14,450
晚安，皮兰特小姐。
Good night, Miss Pilant.

1772
01:52:18,430 --> 01:52:21,390
好吧，现在让我们来谈谈《玫瑰经》这事。
All right. Let's get at this rosary thing.

1773
01:52:21,400 --> 01:52:24,560
前面的证词说你妻子以《玫瑰经》向你起誓，
It's been testified that your wife 
swore to you on a rosary...

1774
01:52:24,570 --> 01:52:27,100
说她遭到巴尼・奎尔强奸。
that she'd been raped by Barney Quill.

1775
01:52:27,100 --> 01:52:30,250
是你要求你妻子以《玫瑰经》起誓的吗？
Did you ask your wife to swear on a rosary?

1776
01:52:30,840 --> 01:52:34,140
当时我妻子表现得歇斯底里，说话语无伦次。
My wife was hysterical.
She wasn't making much sense.

1777
01:52:34,140 --> 01:52:37,280
我想要是我让她以《玫瑰经》的名义起誓，
I thought if I asked her to take 
an oath on a rosary...

1778
01:52:37,280 --> 01:52:40,280
或许可以使她平静下来，
使她脑子变得清楚一点。
it might serve to calm her, 
make her think more clearly.

1779
01:52:40,280 --> 01:52:42,380
《玫瑰经》有用吗？
Did the rosary help?

1780
01:52:42,380 --> 01:52:44,980
她能够开始告诉我
所发生事情的详细情况了。
She was able to tell me 
in detail what had happened.

1781
01:52:44,990 --> 01:52:48,250
好的，接着说。
然后你做了什么，中尉？
All right. Go on from there.
What did you do then, Lieutenant?

1782
01:52:49,060 --> 01:52:51,420
唔，我…
Well, I--

1783
01:52:51,430 --> 01:52:54,930
我让她躺到床上，
我去找了块冷的布…
I had her lie on the bed, 
and I got some cold cloths...

1784
01:52:54,930 --> 01:52:56,920
敷在她头上。
for her head.

1785
01:52:57,130 --> 01:53:00,960
然后，呃…噢，对了，
我给了她一杯白兰地。
And, uh-- Oh, yes. 
I gave her a drink of brandy.

1786
01:53:02,900 --> 01:53:06,540
过了一会儿，她安静了下来，
慢慢地睡着了。
After a while, she became calm, 
seemed to go to sleep.

1787
01:53:07,610 --> 01:53:10,010
然后我走到壁橱旁，
Then I went to the closet...

1788
01:53:10,010 --> 01:53:12,260
取出了我的枪，装上子弹。
I got my gun, and I loaded it.

1789
01:53:12,260 --> 01:53:15,280
你当时想着要去杀巴尼・奎尔吗？
Was it in your mind to kill Barney Quill?

1790
01:53:15,280 --> 01:53:16,540
没有。
No.

1791
01:53:16,550 --> 01:53:19,640
那么你为什么会走到壁橱旁，
取出枪并装上子弹呢？
Then why did you go to the closet 
and get your gun and load it?

1792
01:53:19,650 --> 01:53:23,260
我知道我得去奎尔的酒吧，
我想我可能会用得着。
I knew I had to go to Quill's place.
I thought I might need it.

1793
01:53:23,260 --> 01:53:24,960
为什么？
Why?

1794
01:53:25,260 --> 01:53:27,960
我知道奎尔先生在吧台后面藏着好多枪。
I knew Mr. Quill kept guns behind the bar.

1795
01:53:27,960 --> 01:53:29,730
我害怕他会向我开枪。
I was afraid he might shoot me.

1796
01:53:29,730 --> 01:53:31,730
你做什么会使他向你开枪？
Might shoot you if you did what?

1797
01:53:31,730 --> 01:53:34,730
你准备去干什么？
What were you going to do?

1798
01:53:34,740 --> 01:53:36,970
我不太肯定。
I'm not sure.

1799
01:53:36,970 --> 01:53:39,740
我记得当时我想的是…
I remember having some idea...

1800
01:53:39,740 --> 01:53:42,110
先找到他，
of finding him...

1801
01:53:42,110 --> 01:53:45,260
然后抓住他，接着再叫警察。
and holding him while I call the police.

1802
01:53:45,260 --> 01:53:47,150
唔，那位先生，那位叫什么来着…
Well, that Mr. Whatshisname--

1803
01:53:47,150 --> 01:53:50,310
对了，莱蒙先生，
他是旅游公园那儿的治安官。
Mr. Lemon at the tourist court there, 
he was a deputy sheriff.

1804
01:53:50,320 --> 01:53:52,820
你为什么没有叫上他跟你一起去？
Why didn't you get him to go with you?

1805
01:53:52,820 --> 01:53:54,950
也许是因为一直以来，他看上去只是…
Maybe because he always seemed to be just...

1806
01:53:54,960 --> 01:53:57,550
公园的一个老管理员。
the old caretaker of the park.

1807
01:53:58,530 --> 01:54:02,090
也许是因为我当时除了想
找到巴尼・奎尔，脑子里…
Maybe because I wasn't thinking 
about anything too clearly...

1808
01:54:02,100 --> 01:54:04,260
想不太清其它的事情。
except finding Barney Quill.

1809
01:54:04,260 --> 01:54:08,030
在你去酒吧之前，你为什么
不拿起电话，给警察打电话？
Why didn't you go to a phone, call 
the police before you went to the bar?

1810
01:54:08,040 --> 01:54:10,300
我不知道。
I don't know.

1811
01:54:10,310 --> 01:54:13,600
我可能有点晕了，
I was in sort of a daze.

1812
01:54:13,610 --> 01:54:16,610
看到那么可怕的事情发生在我妻子身上。
It was a horrible thing to see 
what had been done to my wife.

1813
01:54:16,610 --> 01:54:18,870
你说可能有点晕了，
Now, you say you were in sort of a daze.

1814
01:54:18,880 --> 01:54:22,640
那么当你到达酒吧时，
你看到酒吧里有好多人吗？
When you got to the bar, 
did you see that the bar was crowded?

1815
01:54:24,650 --> 01:54:28,050
我没注意到酒吧里的任何人，
I didn't see anyone at the bar...

1816
01:54:28,060 --> 01:54:30,950
除了巴尼・奎尔。
except Barney Quill.

1817
01:54:30,960 --> 01:54:34,420
- 他是我看见的唯一一个人。
- 他在干什么？
- He was the only person I saw.
- What was he doing?

1818
01:54:35,260 --> 01:54:39,100
我想他就站在那儿，在吧台后面。
I think he was just standing there behind the bar.

1819
01:54:39,100 --> 01:54:43,360
那么他有没有想要取枪威胁你呢？
Now, did he make a threatening move to get a gun?

1820
01:54:43,370 --> 01:54:46,900
我不知道，可能吧，我不知道。
I don't know. May have. I don't know.

1821
01:54:46,910 --> 01:54:49,940
好吧，你说你去那里找他，
All right. Now, you say you went there to find him...

1822
01:54:49,940 --> 01:54:51,980
想抓住他交给警察。
to hold him for the police.

1823
01:54:51,980 --> 01:54:54,280
那又为什么向他开枪？
Why did you shoot him?

1824
01:54:55,750 --> 01:54:58,260
我不记得向他开枪了。
I don't remember shooting him.

1825
01:54:59,090 --> 01:55:02,090
在你离开酒吧时，
你记不记得阿尔方斯・帕盖特…
Now, when you left the bar, 
do you remember Alphonse Paquette...

1826
01:55:02,090 --> 01:55:04,160
走向你，想阻止你说：
coming up to you and stopping you and saying...

1827
01:55:04,160 --> 01:55:07,190
“出了这样的事，你最好还是别跑。”
你回答他：
"You'd better not run away from this,"
and you replied...

1828
01:55:07,200 --> 01:55:09,420
“你也想吃几颗吗，小子？”
"You want some too, buster?"

1829
01:55:09,430 --> 01:55:11,100
还记得吗？
Remember that?

1830
01:55:11,600 --> 01:55:16,260
我只有些模糊的印象
好像是有人跟我说过话，
I seem to have a vague recollection 
of somebody speaking to me...

1831
01:55:17,310 --> 01:55:21,040
但是我不记得他对我说了什么，
或我对他说了什么。
but I don't remember what I said 
or what was said to me.

1832
01:55:21,040 --> 01:55:24,480
你什么时候意识到你开枪打了奎尔？
When did you realize that you'd shot Quill?

1833
01:55:26,710 --> 01:55:29,310
我去厨房取水喝，
I was getting a drink of water.

1834
01:55:29,320 --> 01:55:32,480
因为我记得我的嗓子干得生疼。
I remember my throat was so dry it hurt.

1835
01:55:33,820 --> 01:55:37,460
当我放下玻璃杯，看见那把抢
放在厨房的水槽上，
And when I put the glass down, 
I saw the gun on the kitchen sink...

1836
01:55:37,460 --> 01:55:39,720
在水龙头旁边。
beside the tap.

1837
01:55:39,730 --> 01:55:41,830
我发现枪是空的。
I noticed the gun was empty.

1838
01:55:42,730 --> 01:55:45,730
我想让你给法庭和陪审团演示一下，
Now, I'd like you to show the court and jury...

1839
01:55:47,500 --> 01:55:50,690
你怎么知道这把枪是空的。
just how you knew this gun was empty.

1840
01:55:50,710 --> 01:55:53,300
嗯，要是这个小部件…
Well, this gadget here...

1841
01:55:53,310 --> 01:55:57,270
处于这个位置，那么你就知道
你打完了最后一发子弹。
when it sticks up, 
you know the last round's been fired.

1842
01:55:57,280 --> 01:56:02,480
曼尼昂中尉，在你开枪的那个晚上，
你爱你妻子吗？
On the night of the shooting,
did you love your wife?

1843
01:56:02,480 --> 01:56:06,120
- 当然，先生。
- 你现在仍然爱她吗？
- Yes, sir.
- Do you still love her?

1844
01:56:09,260 --> 01:56:11,560
非常爱。
Very much.

1845
01:56:11,660 --> 01:56:13,890
证人是你的了，丹色先生。
The witness is yours, Mr. Dancer.

1846
01:56:13,900 --> 01:56:19,460
曼尼昂中尉，你杀过多少人？
How many men have you killed?

1847
01:56:19,470 --> 01:56:21,900
喂，拜托了！
Now, wait a minute!

1848
01:56:21,900 --> 01:56:25,340
法官大人，一个人的战争记录――
就曼尼昂中尉的情况而言，是一份出色的记录――
Your Honor, a man's war record--
in Lt. Manion's case, a great record--

1849
01:56:25,340 --> 01:56:27,470
显然不应该用来反对他。
certainly shouldn't be used against him.

1850
01:56:27,480 --> 01:56:30,510
法官大人，我和诸位一样，也非常爱国，
I'm as patriotic as the next man...

1851
01:56:30,510 --> 01:56:33,140
但是简单的事实是：
战争会改变一个人，
but the simple truth is, 
war can condition a man...

1852
01:56:33,150 --> 01:56:35,410
让他变得嗜杀。
to killing other men.

1853
01:56:35,420 --> 01:56:38,110
我只是想判断一下
中尉因战争而改变的程度，
I simply want to determine 
how conditioned the lieutenant may be...

1854
01:56:38,120 --> 01:56:41,680
是否轻易就用武器对付其他人。
to the use of firearms on other human beings.

1855
01:56:41,690 --> 01:56:45,640
我也不喜欢这个问题，比格勒先生，
但是我也看不出有什么理由不让他问。
I don't like the question, Mr. Biegler,
but I don't see how I can exclude it.

1856
01:56:45,660 --> 01:56:47,460
让他回答吧。
Let him answer.

1857
01:56:47,460 --> 01:56:51,260
我知道在朝鲜时，我至少杀过四个人――
I know I killed at least four men in Korea--

1858
01:56:51,260 --> 01:56:53,260
三个是用手雷，
three with a hand grenade...

1859
01:56:53,260 --> 01:56:55,560
一个是用我的自动武器。
and one with my service automatic.

1860
01:56:55,570 --> 01:56:59,470
也许我还杀过其他人，
一个战士并不总能知道。
I may have killed others.
A soldier doesn't always know.

1861
01:56:59,470 --> 01:57:01,800
那么中尉，在这些杀人行动中，
Now, Lieutenant, in these acts of killing...

1862
01:57:01,810 --> 01:57:05,540
你有没有发生过遗忘的现象呢，
就像你在杀死巴尼・奎尔时那样？
did you ever have a lapse of memory such 
as you had when you killed Barney Quill?

1863
01:57:05,550 --> 01:57:08,740
- 没有，先生。
- 那么在战场上，你有没有发生过遗忘现象？
- No, sir.
- Did you ever have one during battle?

1864
01:57:08,750 --> 01:57:10,410
- 没有，先生。
- 你有没有经常处于…
- No, sir.
- Were you ever submitted...

1865
01:57:10,420 --> 01:57:13,260
枪林弹雨之下，经常连续几个小时大汗淋漓，
to a constant barrage, 
constantly in a sweat for many hours...

1866
01:57:13,260 --> 01:57:15,550
- 经常不停地进攻和防守？
- 无数次。
- constantly under attack or attacking?
- Many times.

1867
01:57:15,560 --> 01:57:19,020
你是否曾因震弹症、战斗疲劳症、
神经官能症、或精神病接受过治疗？
Were you ever treated for shell shock,
battle fatigue, neuroses or psychoses?

1868
01:57:19,030 --> 01:57:21,290
- 没有，先生。
- 在战争期间，你有没有经历过…
- No, sir.
- Did you ever experience...

1869
01:57:21,300 --> 01:57:23,990
任何异常的精神状态？
any unusual mental state during the war?

1870
01:57:24,000 --> 01:57:26,330
唔，我的确记得有一种非常强烈的冲动。
Well, I do remember having one great urge.

1871
01:57:26,330 --> 01:57:29,770
- 那是什么？
- 离开这鬼地方回家。
- What was that?
- To get the hell out and go home.

1872
01:57:30,270 --> 01:57:32,930
你最好还是别忘了你现在…
You would do well to consider the seriousness...

1873
01:57:32,940 --> 01:57:34,740
所处境遇的严重性。
of the situation you're in.

1874
01:57:34,740 --> 01:57:37,830
- 对不起，法官大人。
- 我倒是和中尉有同感，
- I'm sorry, Your Honor.
- I sympathize with the lieutenant.

1875
01:57:37,850 --> 01:57:41,940
我估计他现在对于离开监狱，
大概也有类似的冲动。
I expect he has the same feeling 
about getting out of jail.

1876
01:57:41,950 --> 01:57:44,260
我的要点是，中尉，在你参与战争的整个期间，
But the main point here is that at no time...

1877
01:57:44,260 --> 01:57:46,910
没有任何一刻记录过你有精神方面的异常，
during your war service did you have
a record of mental disturbance.

1878
01:57:46,920 --> 01:57:49,260
你总是处于完全清醒的状态。
You were always in complete possession 
of your faculties.

1879
01:57:49,260 --> 01:57:51,690
是的，先生，你说得对。
Yes, sir. That's right.

1880
01:57:51,690 --> 01:57:54,590
- 没有问题了。
- 我也不用再质询了，法官大人。
- No more questions.
- No redirect, Your Honor.

1881
01:57:54,600 --> 01:57:57,130
请退席。传你的下一位证人。
Step down, please. Call your next witness.

1882
01:57:57,130 --> 01:57:59,980
我们传劳拉・曼尼昂上证人席。
We call Laura Manion to the stand.

1883
01:58:11,980 --> 01:58:15,280
- 上楼梯后朝右拐。
- 谢谢。
- Up these stairs and to the right.
- Thanks.

1884
01:58:21,290 --> 01:58:24,020
当你告诉你丈夫所发生的事之后，
隔了多久他…
How long after you told 
your husband what had happened...

1885
01:58:24,030 --> 01:58:26,260
离开的车房？
did he leave the trailer?

1886
01:58:26,260 --> 01:58:28,350
我不知道确切有多久，
I don't know exactly.

1887
01:58:28,360 --> 01:58:30,120
一切都模模糊糊的。
Everything was kind of fuzzy.

1888
01:58:30,130 --> 01:58:32,890
我头很晕，我躺到了床上。
I was faint, and I laid down on the bed.

1889
01:58:32,900 --> 01:58:35,070
他坐在我旁边。
He sat beside me.

1890
01:58:35,070 --> 01:58:38,100
我隐约记得他起身离开。
I vaguely remember his getting up and going out.

1891
01:58:38,110 --> 01:58:40,800
我也记得我当时想，
他是不是叫医生去了，
I remember wondering 
if he was going for a doctor...

1892
01:58:40,810 --> 01:58:43,110
后来他就回来了。
and then he came back in.

1893
01:58:43,110 --> 01:58:45,980
感觉就像是只有几秒钟，但是肯定不止。
It seemed like just a few seconds, 
but it must have been longer.

1894
01:58:45,980 --> 01:58:48,470
我可能睡过去了。
I must've gone to sleep.

1895
01:58:48,480 --> 01:58:51,480
当他回来后，他坐在我床边，
When he came back in, he sat on the bed...

1896
01:58:51,490 --> 01:58:53,610
手里拿着把枪。
and he had a gun in his hand.

1897
01:58:53,620 --> 01:58:56,260
我说：“你要干什么？”
And I said, "What are you going to do?"

1898
01:58:56,720 --> 01:58:59,820
他说：“我想我已经干了，
And he said, "I think I've already done it.

1899
01:58:59,830 --> 01:59:02,120
我想我杀了巴尼・奎尔。”
I think I've killed Barney Quill."

1900
01:59:02,130 --> 01:59:05,720
你能肯定他说的不是“我杀了巴尼・奎尔”？
Are you sure he didn't say, 
"I've killed Barney Quill"?

1901
01:59:05,730 --> 01:59:08,320
肯定，我记得很清楚，
No, I remember distinctly.

1902
01:59:08,340 --> 01:59:10,330
“我想我杀了巴尼・奎尔。”
"I think I've killed Barney Quill."

1903
01:59:10,340 --> 01:59:12,400
然后你干什么了？
Then what did you do?

1904
01:59:12,410 --> 01:59:16,770
我用双手抱着他，开始哭了起来，
I put my arms around him and began to cry...

1905
01:59:16,780 --> 01:59:19,780
我说：“你最好去找莱蒙先生。”
and I said, "You'd better go to Mr. Lemon."

1906
01:59:19,780 --> 01:59:21,870
我丈夫说：“我忘了这个。”
And my husband said, "I forgot about that."

1907
01:59:21,880 --> 01:59:24,710
他什么意思？他忘了什么？
What did he mean? Forgot about what?

1908
01:59:24,720 --> 01:59:28,310
他的意思是他忘了
莱蒙先生也是一名治安官。
He meant he'd forgotten 
Mr. Lemon was a deputy sheriff.

1909
01:59:28,320 --> 01:59:31,260
他说：“好的，我去向莱蒙先生自首。”
And he said, "Yes, I'll go 
turn myself in to Mr. Lemon."

1910
01:59:31,260 --> 01:59:32,620
好的，知道了。
Yes, I see.

1911
01:59:32,630 --> 01:59:36,030
法官大人，就此证人
目前我没有进一步的问题了。
Your Honor, I have no other 
direct questions at this time.

1912
01:59:36,030 --> 01:59:39,120
但是因为我敢肯定，
各位很难想象到一条小狗…
But since I'm sure it's difficult 
to visualize the part...

1913
01:59:39,130 --> 01:59:41,900
在那晚所起的作用，
a little dog played on this night...

1914
01:59:41,900 --> 01:59:45,730
所以我希望给我几分钟，
向法庭展示这只出色的小动物。
I should like a few minutes to show 
the court this remarkable little animal.

1915
01:59:45,740 --> 01:59:47,730
公诉方反对吗？
Do the people object?

1916
01:59:47,740 --> 01:59:49,740
我可以肯定，要是我们反对的话，法官大人，
I'm sure that if we raise 
an objection, Your Honor...

1917
01:59:49,740 --> 01:59:53,450
比格勒先生又会宣称
我们敌视所有幼小的、毛茸茸的动物。
Mr. Biegler will declare that we are
haters of all small, furry animals.

1918
01:59:53,680 --> 01:59:57,140
幸亏那个造物不会开口说话。
A creature that cannot talk 
will be a welcome relief.

1919
01:59:57,150 --> 01:59:59,260
把狗带进来。
Bring in the dog.

1920
01:59:59,260 --> 02:00:04,280
谢谢，大人。请庭警带狗进来好吗？
Thank you, sir. Will the deputy 
bring in the dog, please?

1921
02:00:17,060 --> 02:00:19,730
把他放在那儿吧。
You can put him right there.

1922
02:00:20,840 --> 02:00:23,740
嗨，毛毛！过来！过来！
Hey, Muff!. Come on!

1923
02:00:24,410 --> 02:00:26,660
真乖！
That's a boy.

1924
02:00:27,260 --> 02:00:31,240
现在我问曼尼昂夫人要个便携灯给小狗。
And now I'll ask Mrs. Manion 
to bring a flashlight for the dog.

1925
02:00:41,960 --> 02:00:46,570
我要法庭注意，小狗把灯打开了。
I'll ask the court to notice 
that the dog turned on the light.

1926
02:00:55,440 --> 02:00:58,810
很容易看出来，毛毛不知道谁是他的敌人。
It's easy to see that Muff doesn't know 
who his enemies are.

1927
02:00:58,810 --> 02:01:01,070
- 把狗带出去吧。
- 好的，大人。
- Remove the dog, please.
- Yes, sir.

1928
02:01:01,080 --> 02:01:03,940
- 证人回到证人席。
- 走吧，毛毛。
- The witness will resume the stand.
- There we go, Muff.

1929
02:01:06,960 --> 02:01:11,550
曼尼昂夫人，我要祝贺你有
这样一只训练有素的宠物。
May I congratulate you 
on your well trained pet.

1930
02:01:11,560 --> 02:01:14,590
我也想说，我很高兴看到你今天不再…
May I also say I'm pleased to see 
you're not today...

1931
02:01:14,600 --> 02:01:16,960
将你可爱的头发藏在帽子下面了。
hiding your lovely hair under a hat.

1932
02:01:16,960 --> 02:01:20,760
法官大人，从兰辛来的检查总长助理
算是在大献殷勤呢，
Your Honor, is the assistant attorney 
general from Lansing pitching woo...

1933
02:01:20,770 --> 02:01:24,600
- 还算是在交叉质询证人？
- 让我们切入正题吧。
- or is he going to cross-examine?
- Let's get on with it.

1934
02:01:24,610 --> 02:01:27,040
曼尼昂夫人，结婚之前你的职业是什么？
Mrs. Manion, what was your occupation 
before you were married?

1935
02:01:27,040 --> 02:01:30,040
- 家庭主妇。
- 那么之前你结过婚？
- Housewife.
- Then you've been married before?

1936
02:01:30,040 --> 02:01:34,510
- 是的，一次。
- 我猜你第一个丈夫去世了？
- Yes, once.
- I suppose your first husband died?

1937
02:01:34,520 --> 02:01:35,840
没有。
No.

1938
02:01:35,850 --> 02:01:38,650
你是和你第一个丈夫离婚后
才和曼尼昂中尉结婚的吗？
Did you divorce your first husband 
to marry Lt. Manion?

1939
02:01:38,650 --> 02:01:40,450
法官大人，如果对方律师想知道曼尼昂夫人的…
Your Honor, if counsel wants 
to know the grounds...

1940
02:01:40,450 --> 02:01:42,820
离婚理由的话，就让他直截了当问好了。
for Mrs. Manion's divorce, 
let him ask that question.

1941
02:01:42,820 --> 02:01:44,650
你离婚的理由是什么？
What were the grounds for divorce?

1942
02:01:44,660 --> 02:01:47,820
- 精神折磨。
- 自然。那么你离婚后多久…
- Mental cruelty.
- Naturally. And how long after...

1943
02:01:47,830 --> 02:01:50,560
和曼尼昂中尉结的婚？
your divorce was it that 
you married Lt. Manion?

1944
02:01:50,570 --> 02:01:52,390
呃…我不太确定。
I'm not sure.

1945
02:01:52,400 --> 02:01:55,560
我可以为丹瑟先生替证人回忆一下吗？
May I refresh the witness' memory 
for Mr. Dancer?

1946
02:01:55,570 --> 02:01:57,800
- 愿意洗耳恭听。
