- 你回答吧，曼尼昂夫人。
- That's all I'm trying to get at.
- You may answer, Mrs. Manion.

2081
02:08:25,960 --> 02:08:29,260
你总是穿内裤的吗？
You always wear panties?

2082
02:08:29,260 --> 02:08:31,060
不是。
No.

2083
02:08:31,170 --> 02:08:34,260
那么在什么情况下你不穿内裤？
当你一个人在夜里外出时？
On what occasions don't you wear them?
When you go out alone at night?

2084
02:08:34,270 --> 02:08:38,270
不，不，不！反对！他说他就问一件事情，
现在他又得寸进尺了。
No, no. Objection. He says he's going 
after one thing and goes after another.

2085
02:08:38,270 --> 02:08:40,300
我要说反对有效。
I'll sustain the objection.

2086
02:08:40,310 --> 02:08:44,000
删除最后两个问题和曼尼昂夫人的回答。
Strike out the last two questions 
in Mrs. Manion's answer.

2087
02:08:44,010 --> 02:08:48,550
丹瑟先生，立即抛开内裤，
你造成的损害够多了。
Now, Mr. Dancer, get off the panties.
You've done enough damage.

2088
02:08:48,550 --> 02:08:50,640
好的，法官大人。
Yes, Your Honor.

2089
02:08:50,650 --> 02:08:54,850
曼尼昂夫人，你丈夫是一个容易嫉妒的人吗？
Mrs. Manion, is your husband a jealous man?

2090
02:08:54,860 --> 02:08:58,260
- 他爱我。
- 当然，但是他是否极度地嫉妒？
- He loves me.
- I'm sure, but is he overly jealous?

2091
02:08:58,260 --> 02:09:01,090
法官大人，证人如何回答这样的问题？
Your Honor, how can the witness 
answer that question?

2092
02:09:01,100 --> 02:09:03,130
嫉妒的标准是什么？
What's the norm of jealousy?

2093
02:09:03,130 --> 02:09:06,260
你能不能换一个
不同一点的问题呢，丹瑟先生？
Can you put your question 
a little differently, Mr. Dancer?

2094
02:09:06,270 --> 02:09:09,260
- 你丈夫有没有因为嫉妒的爆发而打过你？
- 不，法官大人。
- Has your husband struck you in a rage?
- No, Your Honor.

2095
02:09:09,260 --> 02:09:12,530
我认为丹瑟先生这是在下套子。
这个问题究竟和本案有什么关系？
I think Mr. Dancer's fishing now.
What's the relevance of this question?

2096
02:09:12,540 --> 02:09:14,770
法官大人，比格勒先生
搬了石头砸了自己的脚。
Your Honor, the shoe is 
squeezing Mr. Biegler's foot.

2097
02:09:14,780 --> 02:09:16,780
用他自己话来说，这不是一场
高中生之间的辩论，
In his own words, this is 
not a high school debate.

2098
02:09:16,780 --> 02:09:19,040
这是对一起谋杀案进行的交叉质询。
This is a cross-examination in a murder trial.

2099
02:09:19,050 --> 02:09:21,350
继续，丹瑟先生。
Proceed, Mr. Dancer.

2100
02:09:22,050 --> 02:09:28,550
曼尼昂夫人，你参加过在雷鸣湾的社交活动吗？
Did you ever go out socially in Thunder Bay?

2101
02:09:28,760 --> 02:09:30,690
参加过几次吧。
Yes, a few times.

2102
02:09:30,690 --> 02:09:33,660
在你丈夫的部队开来雷鸣湾时，巴尼・奎尔…
When your husband's outfit moved 
to Thunder Bay, didn't Barney Quill...

2103
02:09:33,660 --> 02:09:36,660
是不是为军官和太太们搞过个鸡尾酒会？
throw a cocktail party 
for the officers and their wives?

2104
02:09:36,660 --> 02:09:37,260
是的。
Yes.

2105
02:09:37,260 --> 02:09:40,460
在这个晚会上，你丈夫是不是打过一个少尉？
Didn't your husband strike a young 
second lieutenant at this party?

2106
02:09:41,270 --> 02:09:44,530
有一点小的扭打，没什么。
There was a little scuffle. It wasn't much.

2107
02:09:44,540 --> 02:09:47,900
- 因为什么原因？
- 我想我不记得了。
- What was it about?
- I'm not sure I remember.

2108
02:09:47,910 --> 02:09:51,900
- 是因为当时喝得太多，记不起来了？
- 不，我没喝多。
- Were you too drunk to remember?
- No, I was not.

2109
02:09:52,950 --> 02:09:55,070
我想那是因为…
I think it was because...

2110
02:09:55,080 --> 02:09:59,180
当我和我丈夫跳舞时，
少尉老是想插进来。
the lieutenant was cutting in too much
when I was dancing with my husband.

2111
02:09:59,190 --> 02:10:02,450
紧接着在阳台上，
你丈夫有没有打你耳光，
Shortly after on the verandah, didn't
your husband slap you hard enough...

2112
02:10:02,460 --> 02:10:04,860
下手如此之重把你打得靠到了墙上？
so that you fell against the wall?

2113
02:10:07,260 --> 02:10:10,230
- 他喝了很多。
- 那是因为嫉妒的爆发吗？
- He was drinking.
- Wasn't this a jealous rage?

2114
02:10:10,230 --> 02:10:13,490
- 我不知道！
- 你记得为什么他会打你？
- I don't know!
- Do you remember why he struck you?

2115
02:10:13,500 --> 02:10:14,250
是的。
Yes.

2116
02:10:14,250 --> 02:10:18,100
不是出于他对你的愤怒吗，
因为他认为你在怂恿那位年轻人？
Wasn't he enraged at you because he 
thought you'd encouraged the young man?

2117
02:10:18,110 --> 02:10:21,510
- 他可能是这样想的。
- 曼尼昂夫人，有人看见了整个事件过程。
- He might have thought so.
- There are witnesses to this affair.

2118
02:10:21,510 --> 02:10:24,260
我想再问你一次，这是不是嫉妒的爆发？
I'll ask you again. Wasn't this a jealous rage?

2119
02:10:24,260 --> 02:10:26,910
我想你可以这样说。
I guess you could call it that.

2120
02:10:28,020 --> 02:10:30,940
现在我问你，
Now I'll ask you.

2121
02:10:31,650 --> 02:10:34,180
在枪击的那个晚上，
On the night of the shooting...

2122
02:10:34,190 --> 02:10:36,090
你穿了什么？
what did you swear?

2123
02:10:36,090 --> 02:10:38,690
以《玫瑰经》的名义，你起的什么誓？
What oath did you take on the rosary?

2124
02:10:39,530 --> 02:10:43,430
- 关于巴尼・奎尔强奸我的事。
- 为什么你要以《玫瑰经》的名义发誓说…
- It was about Barney Quill raping me.
- Why did you swear on the rosary...

2125
02:10:43,430 --> 02:10:45,760
他强奸了你？
that he raped you?

2126
02:10:45,770 --> 02:10:48,490
原因我丈夫已经说过――
因为我当时有点歇斯底里！
For the reason my husband said--
because I was hysterical!

2127
02:10:48,500 --> 02:10:51,260
那是他给出的他让你发誓的理由，
那么你为什么要发誓呢？
That was the reason he gave for asking 
you to swear. What was it for swearing?

2128
02:10:51,260 --> 02:10:53,260
- 好让他相信我。
- 为什么他会不相信你？
- So he'd believe me.
- Why shouldn't he?

2129
02:10:53,260 --> 02:10:56,540
反对！用《玫瑰经》的理由已经明确了，
Objection! The reason for the use 
of the rosary has been established.

2130
02:10:56,540 --> 02:10:58,260
这些问题都是非实质性的。
These questions are immaterial.

2131
02:10:58,260 --> 02:11:01,940
不，我想我愿意听听答案，比格勒先生。
No, I think I'll take the answer, Mr. Biegler.

2132
02:11:01,950 --> 02:11:05,910
我再问你一次，曼尼昂夫人，
为什么他不相信你？
I'll ask you again, Mrs. Manion.
Why shouldn't he believe you?

2133
02:11:07,420 --> 02:11:09,260
因为当时我说话语无伦次！
Because I wasn't making much sense!

2134
02:11:09,260 --> 02:11:11,550
他会认为你对这样的事情撒谎吗？
Did he think you'd lie about a thing like that?

2135
02:11:11,560 --> 02:11:15,260
反对，法官大人！曼尼昂中尉已经
作过证说他当时的想法！
Objection, Your Honor! Lt. Manion had 
already testified as to what he thought!

2136
02:11:15,260 --> 02:11:19,260
- 反对有效。
- 那天晚上你丈夫打你了吗？
- Sustained.
- Did your husband strike you that night?

2137
02:11:19,270 --> 02:11:21,600
他打你了吗那晚？
Did he hit you that night?

2138
02:11:23,400 --> 02:11:26,000
他…他…
Well, he--

2139
02:11:26,010 --> 02:11:29,470
他也许因为我的歇斯底里打了我一记耳光。
He may have slapped me because I was hysterical.

2140
02:11:29,480 --> 02:11:32,040
你是不是发了假誓好让他不再打你？
Didn't you swear to a lie to keep him 
from hitting you again?

2141
02:11:32,050 --> 02:11:34,040
不，我没有，我没有发假誓！
No, I didn't! I did not!

2142
02:11:34,050 --> 02:11:37,340
也有可能他在大门外面就已经把你打了个半死，
因为他正好逮住你和巴尼・奎尔从情人小径兜风回家？
Hadn't he already beaten you up when he 
caught you coming home with Quill?

2143
02:11:37,350 --> 02:11:41,680
反对！反对！证人已经作证说
她是被巴尼・奎尔殴打的！
Objection! The witness has already 
testified she was beaten by Quill!

2144
02:11:41,690 --> 02:11:43,920
安静，安静。
Quiet. Quiet.

2145
02:11:43,920 --> 02:11:46,320
没有问题了。
No more questions.

2146
02:11:46,730 --> 02:11:49,390
我想这位证人已经受够了，法官大人。
I think the witness has had enough, Your Honor.

2147
02:11:49,400 --> 02:11:52,970
证人可以退下了。
下面是午餐休庭。
The witness may step down. 
We'll recess for lunch.

2148
02:11:54,670 --> 02:11:57,170
休庭到下午1点。
Recess until 1:00.

2149
02:11:59,810 --> 02:12:02,210
对不起，亲爱的，你表现得很好。
I'm sorry, baby. You were fine.

2150
02:12:35,010 --> 02:12:36,970
史密斯医生。
Dr. Smith.

2151
02:12:37,260 --> 02:12:39,740
我是来接你的。我叫……
I've come to meet you. My name is--

2152
02:12:39,950 --> 02:12:42,780
- 对不起，你认错人了。
- 也许我是你要找的人。
- I'm sorry. You've been mistaken.
- Maybe I'm the one you're looking for.

2153
02:12:42,780 --> 02:12:44,750
你是比格勒先生吗？
Are you Mr. Biegler?

2154
02:12:44,850 --> 02:12:47,320
不，我是他这个案子的同事。
No, I'm his associate in the case.

2155
02:12:47,420 --> 02:12:50,290
- 别跟我说你就是史密斯医生。
- 就是我。
- Don't tell me you're Dr. Smith.
- That's me.

2156
02:12:50,290 --> 02:12:52,590
军方的精神病医生？
The army psychiatrist?

2157
02:12:52,590 --> 02:12:54,960
也许你估计我会穿军服。
Maybe you expected me to be in uniform.

2158
02:12:54,960 --> 02:12:57,260
不，
No.

2159
02:12:57,260 --> 02:12:59,790
我没料到你那么年轻。
I didn't expect anybody so young.

2160
02:12:59,800 --> 02:13:01,700
我四十了。
I'm 40.

2161
02:13:01,800 --> 02:13:04,740
我估计你可能有…
I sort of hoped you'd...

2162
02:13:04,840 --> 02:13:07,340
一把胡子，戴一个单片眼镜。
have a beard and wear a monocle.

2163
02:13:07,340 --> 02:13:09,530
噢，是这样啊。
I see.

2164
02:13:09,540 --> 02:13:11,940
这样是不是好点？
Is that better?

2165
02:13:12,050 --> 02:13:14,810
你今天下午出庭。
You're on the stand this afternoon.

2166
02:13:16,880 --> 02:13:19,750
医生，你是否已经就弗雷德里克・曼尼昂…
Doctor, have you formed an opinion 
as to Frederick Manion's...

2167
02:13:19,750 --> 02:13:22,790
在他杀巴尼・奎尔那晚的
精神和情绪状态形成意见了呢？
mental and emotional state 
at the time he killed Barney Quill?

2168
02:13:22,790 --> 02:13:24,520
- 是的。
- 你的意见是什么？
- I have.
- And what is that opinion?

2169
02:13:24,530 --> 02:13:27,620
在他开枪的时候，
他患有“临时性精神错乱”症。
He was temporarily insane 
at the time of the shooting.

2170
02:13:27,630 --> 02:13:29,920
在他开枪的时候，你相信他有…
At the time of the shooting, 
do you believe he was able...

2171
02:13:29,930 --> 02:13:32,160
分辨是非的能力吗？
to distinguish right from wrong?

2172
02:13:32,170 --> 02:13:35,330
也许有，也许没有。
这没有太大的区别。
He may or may not have been.
It doesn't make too much difference.

2173
02:13:35,340 --> 02:13:38,500
好吧，医生，你能不能尽可能清楚地…
Now, Doctor, as clearly as you can...

2174
02:13:38,510 --> 02:13:42,170
解释一下弗雷德里克・曼尼昂的
“临时性精神错乱”？
will you explain 
Frederick Manion's temporary insanity?

2175
02:13:42,180 --> 02:13:45,300
这又被称为“习惯性分裂反应”，指的是…
It is known as dissociative reaction...

2176
02:13:45,310 --> 02:13:47,740
一种精神上的震撼，它会产生…
a psychic shock which creates...

2177
02:13:47,750 --> 02:13:50,150
一种几乎是无法抗拒的紧张，
an almost overwhelming tension...

2178
02:13:50,150 --> 02:13:53,150
处于震撼中的人必须释放掉这种紧张。
which the person in shock must alleviate.

2179
02:13:53,150 --> 02:13:55,780
在曼尼昂中尉的这个案例中，他是个战士，
In Lt. Manion's case, a soldier...

2180
02:13:55,790 --> 02:13:58,720
所以他自然会诉诸于行动。
it is only natural that he would turn to action.

2181
02:13:58,730 --> 02:14:01,390
只有对巴尼・奎尔采取…
Only direct, simple action...

2182
02:14:01,400 --> 02:14:04,950
直截了当的、简单的行动，
才能释放掉这种无法忍受的紧张。
against Barney Quill would relieve 
this unbearable tension.

2183
02:14:04,970 --> 02:14:08,690
这并不特别罕见。例如在战场上，
一些更加异乎寻常的壮举，
This is not too uncommon. For example, 
in combat, some of the more...

2184
02:14:08,700 --> 02:14:11,640
就是发生在这样一种精神状态下。
remarkable heroics take place 
in this state of mind.

2185
02:14:11,640 --> 02:14:15,870
有没有一个更加容易理解的名字
指的是“习惯性分裂反应”？
Is there another name for dissociative
reaction that we might recognize?

2186
02:14:15,880 --> 02:14:19,280
有，它又被称为“无法抑制的冲动”。
Yes, it has been known as irresistible impulse.

2187
02:14:19,280 --> 02:14:22,610
医生，一个人要是被这种
“无法抑制的冲动”所控制，
Now, Doctor, a man in the grip
of irresistible impulse...

2188
02:14:22,620 --> 02:14:25,080
那么他还可能会征询邻居的建议，
would he be likely to go 
to his neighbor for advice...

2189
02:14:25,090 --> 02:14:27,880
或者打电话给警察寻求帮助吗？
or call up the police to come to his aid?

2190
02:14:27,890 --> 02:14:30,820
- 完全不相容。
- 是的，可是我们的这个人…
- Completely incompatible.
- Yes, but our man...

2191
02:14:30,820 --> 02:14:33,550
在他动身去找奎尔之前，
was able to think of going and taking out a gun...

2192
02:14:33,560 --> 02:14:36,030
他能够想着去取出枪来上好子弹。
and loading it before setting out to find Quill.

2193
02:14:36,030 --> 02:14:40,530
那是他的心理意识在起作用，
即使他弄不到枪，他也无论如何要去的。
That's his conscious mind working, but 
he'd go even if a gun wasn't available.

2194
02:14:40,530 --> 02:14:44,260
一个被“习惯性分裂反应”控制的人，
他看上去是怎么样的？
How would a man look 
in the grip of dissociative reaction?

2195
02:14:44,270 --> 02:14:48,400
他可能显得死一般的平静，
极度的从容谨慎。
He might appear to be deadly calm, 
fiercely deliberate.

2196
02:14:48,410 --> 02:14:51,070
嗯哼，你会不会形容他的行为…
Mm-hmm. Would you describe his behavior...

2197
02:14:51,080 --> 02:14:54,010
就像是一个邮差，来送了一封信？
as being like a mailman delivering the mail?

2198
02:14:54,010 --> 02:14:58,250
这个比喻不赖，像个邮差，
他有件活儿要干，他就会去干。
That's not bad. Like a mailman, he would 
have a job to do, and he would do it.

2199
02:14:59,820 --> 02:15:02,390
- 你的证人。
- 医生，
- Your witness.
- Doctor...

2200
02:15:02,390 --> 02:15:04,920
你发现弗雷德里克・曼尼昂有精神病吗？
did you find any psychosis in Frederick Manion?

2201
02:15:04,930 --> 02:15:06,960
- 没有。
- 神经官能症呢？
- I did not.
- Any neuroses?

2202
02:15:06,960 --> 02:15:08,990
我没发现他有神经官能症的病史。
I found no history of neuroses.

2203
02:15:09,000 --> 02:15:12,060
妄想症的病史呢？
Any history of delusion?

2204
02:15:12,070 --> 02:15:14,070
- 没有。
- 失去记忆？
- None.
- Loss of memory?

2205
02:15:14,070 --> 02:15:17,300
- 这起案子之前没有。
- 你有没有发现……
- Not before this instance.
- Did you find any history--

2206
02:15:17,300 --> 02:15:21,740
- 你们看见玛丽・皮兰特了吗？
- 她午饭后没有回来。
- Can you spot Mary Pilant?
- She didn't come back after lunch.

2207
02:15:21,740 --> 02:15:24,500
我想你得放弃那个证人了。
I think you'd better give up on that one.

2208
02:15:24,510 --> 02:15:27,410
医生，你说被告可能有、也可能没有…
Doctor, you stated that the defendant 
might or might not...

2209
02:15:27,410 --> 02:15:29,480
分辨是非的能力，
have been able to distinguish...

2210
02:15:29,480 --> 02:15:32,310
但是这并没有什么区别。
the difference between right and wrong,
but it wouldn't have made a difference.

2211
02:15:32,320 --> 02:15:34,550
- 你是那样说的，我说得没错吧？
- 大致可以这么说吧。
- Am I right? Is that what you said?
- Approximately, yes.

2212
02:15:34,550 --> 02:15:36,590
你的意思是在他开枪的时候，
Did you mean that at the time of the shooting...

2213
02:15:36,590 --> 02:15:38,560
他可能知道什么是对什么是错？
he could have known the difference 
between right and wrong?

2214
02:15:38,560 --> 02:15:40,560
可能吧，是的。
He might have, yes.

2215
02:15:40,560 --> 02:15:42,490
史密斯医生，
Dr. Smith...

2216
02:15:42,500 --> 02:15:45,530
如果被告能够知道他在做的事情，
if the defendant could have known 
what he was doing...

2217
02:15:45,530 --> 02:15:48,070
而且他能够意识到这事是错的，
那么你怎么可以跑到这儿来…
and could have known it was wrong,
how can you come here...

2218
02:15:48,070 --> 02:15:50,260
作证说他是正当的精神错乱？
and testify that he was legally insane?

2219
02:15:50,270 --> 02:15:52,840
我没说他是正当的精神错乱，
I'm not saying he was legally insane.

2220
02:15:52,840 --> 02:15:54,870
我说的是在他的精神状态下，
I'm saying that in his mental condition...

2221
02:15:54,880 --> 02:15:57,500
知不知道对错没有任何实质的区别。
it would not have made any difference
whether he knew right from wrong.

2222
02:15:57,510 --> 02:16:00,300
他无论如何都会向奎尔开枪。
He would still have shot Quill.

2223
02:16:00,320 --> 02:16:06,260
史密斯医生，你的这个意见
是否就是你对本案最终的证词？
Are you willing to rest your testimony 
in this case on this opinion?

2224
02:16:06,260 --> 02:16:08,550
是的，我就是这个意见。
Yes, I am.

2225
02:16:09,560 --> 02:16:12,450
法官大人，我想请求短暂休庭。
Your Honor, I'd like to ask for a short recess.

2226
02:16:12,460 --> 02:16:16,280
公诉方律师想在法庭议事室
和比格勒先生面议。
The attorneys for the people would like 
to meet with Mr. Biegler in chambers.

2227
02:16:16,290 --> 02:16:17,200
比格勒先生？
Mr. Biegler?

2228
02:16:17,200 --> 02:16:20,360
- 悉听尊便，法官大人。
- 短暂休庭。
- Glad to oblige, Your Honor.
- Short recess.

2229
02:16:20,370 --> 02:16:22,740
陪审团请留在原位。
The jury will remain.

2230
02:16:33,510 --> 02:16:35,710
总有一天，我会惊世骇俗，
Someday, I'm going to horrify tradition...

2231
02:16:35,720 --> 02:16:38,310
在那个神圣的法庭内，放出一团…
and lay a dense, blue cloud...

2232
02:16:38,320 --> 02:16:41,510
由燃烧的烟草产生的浓厚的蓝色烟云。
of tobacco smoke in that hallowed courtroom.

2233
02:16:41,520 --> 02:16:43,890
你心里想什么呢，丹瑟先生？
What's on your mind, Mr. Dancer?

2234
02:16:43,890 --> 02:16:46,320
法官大人，鉴于史密斯医生的证词，
我想也许辩方…
Your Honor, in view of Dr. Smith's 
testimony, I thought perhaps...

2235
02:16:46,330 --> 02:16:48,390
可能希望改变他们的辩护请求。
the defense might like to change their plea.

2236
02:16:48,400 --> 02:16:51,290
- 改成什么？
- 当然是服罪。
- Change it to what?
- Guilty, of course.

2237
02:16:51,300 --> 02:16:53,330
不，我们仍想拼尽全力。
No, we'll still go for broke.

2238
02:16:53,330 --> 02:16:55,990
见鬼，保利，你知道在密歇根，
一个家伙除非他不能明辨是非，
Hell, Paulie, you know a guy's 
not considered legally nuts...

2239
02:16:56,000 --> 02:16:58,130
否则的话他不会被认作是正当的疯子。
in Michigan unless 
he didn't know right from wrong.

2240
02:16:58,140 --> 02:17:02,700
- 为什么你不就此了结了呢？
- 法官大人，您可以翻到486页吗？
- Why don't you get this over with?
- Your Honor, will you turn to page 486?

2241
02:17:02,710 --> 02:17:07,270
- 那是什么？
- 看起来像是一本法律书，罗德威克先生。
- What's that?
- Appears to be a law book, Mr. Lodwick.

2242
02:17:08,750 --> 02:17:10,870
噢，对不起，法官大人。
Oh, I'm sorry, Your Honor.

2243
02:17:10,880 --> 02:17:13,510
有时我制作这些玩意儿来帮助我思考。
I make those things to help me think sometimes.

2244
02:17:13,520 --> 02:17:15,990
- 钓鲈鱼用的？
- 不，钓青蛙用的。
- For perch?
- No, it was for frog.

2245
02:17:15,990 --> 02:17:18,020
他引证了哪个案例，法官？
What case is he citing?

2246
02:17:18,020 --> 02:17:20,320
在我们那地方，我们用叉子叉青蛙。
We gig frogs in my part of the country.

2247
02:17:20,330 --> 02:17:23,120
这里也一样。我自己喜欢钓鳟鱼，
It's the same up here.
I'm a trout man, myself...

2248
02:17:23,130 --> 02:17:25,260
但是这是个新的窍门我想试一下。
but this is a new wrinkle I'm gonna try.

2249
02:17:25,260 --> 02:17:29,260
在南面的拜尤，他们就用这个。
其方法是，准备一根很长的杆子，
They do it in the Bayou, down South.
The idea, they get a big, long pole...

2250
02:17:29,260 --> 02:17:31,630
和一根十磅的线，然后就…
and about a ten-pound line, just sort of...

2251
02:17:31,640 --> 02:17:33,800
在船上沿着河岸漂流，
drift along a high bank in a boat.

2252
02:17:33,810 --> 02:17:37,810
当你看见石头缝里有只大个的老牛蛙，
Then you see that big, old bullfrog in the crevice...

2253
02:17:37,810 --> 02:17:40,000
你就把这玩意飘到它的前方。
and sort of float this along in front of him.

2254
02:17:40,010 --> 02:17:42,840
啪！它的老舌头一吐出来，
Pop! That old tongue of his snaps out, and--

2255
02:17:42,850 --> 02:17:44,920
那么蛙腿就到你晚餐桌上了。
You've got frog legs for supper.

2256
02:17:44,920 --> 02:17:47,010
- 噢，老天哪！
- 您留着吧。
- I'll be darned.
- Why don't you keep it?

2257
02:17:47,020 --> 02:17:49,950
- 有时间玩玩。
- 谢谢，我会的。
- Try it sometime.
- Thanks. I will.

2258
02:17:49,960 --> 02:17:52,290
四百八十六页。
Four eighty-six.

2259
02:17:53,130 --> 02:17:57,560
- 那是什么，法官大人？
- 对德费的公诉案，1886年。
- What is it, Your Honor?
- People v, Durfee, 1886.

2260
02:17:57,560 --> 02:18:00,290
看起来像是一个先例。
Looks like a precedent.

2261
02:18:00,300 --> 02:18:02,390
你愿意读一下吗，丹瑟先生？
Would you like to read it?

2262
02:18:03,400 --> 02:18:07,400
不，谢谢，法官大人。
我想我记起这个案子了。
No, thank you, Your Honor.
I think I recall the case.

2263
02:18:08,110 --> 02:18:11,040
我们咬钩了…
We're hooked...

2264
02:18:11,040 --> 02:18:13,340
像那只青蛙。
like the frog.

2265
02:18:15,450 --> 02:18:18,680
哈考特医生，你在哪儿受的大学教育？
Dr. Harcourt, where did you receive 
your university training?

2266
02:18:18,750 --> 02:18:20,790
马里兰州巴尔的摩市的约翰霍普金斯大学。
Johns Hopkins in Baltimore, Maryland.

2267
02:18:20,790 --> 02:18:22,950
你现在在哪儿从业？
And where do you practice now?

2268
02:18:22,960 --> 02:18:26,650
我是“邦德州立精神病院”的医务监督。
I'm the medical superintendent of the 
Bonder State Hospital for the Insane.

2269
02:18:26,660 --> 02:18:28,960
在这里有人指出，
It's been stated here that...

2270
02:18:28,960 --> 02:18:31,960
“习惯性分裂反应”或“无法抑制的冲动”
dissociative reaction, or irresistible impulse...

2271
02:18:31,970 --> 02:18:34,900
在参加过战斗的士兵当中并不罕见。
is not uncommon among soldiers in combat.

2272
02:18:34,900 --> 02:18:37,730
- 你同意这种说法吗？
- 同意，
- Do you agree with that statement?
- I do...

2273
02:18:37,740 --> 02:18:39,830
但不是像史密斯医生所说的那样。
but not as it was put by Dr. Smith.

2274
02:18:39,840 --> 02:18:43,710
- 你和史密斯医生的分歧在哪里？
- “习惯性分裂反应”…
- Where would you depart from Dr. Smith?
- Dissociative reaction...

2275
02:18:43,710 --> 02:18:47,540
不会无缘无故突然出现，之后又倏地离去。
is not something that comes out of 
the blue and disappears as quickly.

2276
02:18:47,550 --> 02:18:51,880
即使在参加过战斗的士兵当中，
它也只可能发生在那些…
It can only occur, 
even among soldiers in combat...

2277
02:18:51,890 --> 02:18:55,920
长期处于精神神经症状态的个体身上。
if the individual has a psychoneurotic 
condition of long standing.

2278
02:18:55,920 --> 02:18:59,690
前面有证词说，对被告的精神病检查，
It's been testified here that 
a psychiatric exam of the defendant...

2279
02:18:59,690 --> 02:19:02,450
没有证据表明他患有神经官能症，
showed no evidence of neuroses...

2280
02:19:02,460 --> 02:19:04,790
也没有“习惯性分裂反应”的病史。
and no history of dissociative reaction.

2281
02:19:04,800 --> 02:19:06,860
你还听证人说过，
You've further heard it testified...

2282
02:19:06,870 --> 02:19:08,960
在枪击的那个晚上，被告的行为…
that the defendant's behavior 
on the night of the shooting...

2283
02:19:08,970 --> 02:19:11,630
冷静而直接。
was cool and direct.

2284
02:19:11,640 --> 02:19:14,400
作为一名观察员，你记得这些证词吧？
As an observer, do you remember this testimony?

2285
02:19:14,400 --> 02:19:15,310
记得。
Yes.

2286
02:19:15,310 --> 02:19:18,640
由此，你是否形成了有关被告
在发生枪击那晚的…
From this, have you formed an opinion
about the defendant's sanity...

2287
02:19:18,650 --> 02:19:20,680
精神状况的意见了呢？
on the night of the shooting?

2288
02:19:20,680 --> 02:19:24,720
是的，我的意见是他完全处于清醒状态，
I'm of the opinion that he was in 
possession of his faculties...

2289
02:19:24,720 --> 02:19:27,480
因此他并没有受到自己的
无意识情绪的控制。
so that he was not dominated 
by his unconscious mind.

2290
02:19:27,490 --> 02:19:31,420
换句话说，他也没有受到
“无法抑制的冲动”的控制？
In other words, he was not 
in the grip of irresistible impulse.

2291
02:19:31,420 --> 02:19:33,750
- 在我看来，他没有。
- 谢谢你，医生。你的证人，比格勒先生。
- In my opinion, he was not.
- Thank you. Your witness.

2292
02:19:33,760 --> 02:19:37,850
哈考特医生，精神病学试图探究的是人类…
Dr. Harcourt, psychiatry is an effort 
to probe into the dark...

2293
02:19:37,860 --> 02:19:39,930
隐秘的、未知的精神世界。
undiscovered world of the mind.

2294
02:19:39,930 --> 02:19:43,300
在那里，世界可以是圆的，也可以是方的。
And in there, the world 
might be round, it could be square.

2295
02:19:43,300 --> 02:19:47,100
你的意见有可能是错的，而史密斯医生的意见
有可能是对的。是这样的吗？
Your opinion could be wrong, Dr. Smith's 
could be right. Is that true?

2296
02:19:47,110 --> 02:19:49,870
要是我不同意的话，会显得我很不专业。
I'd be a poor doctor 
if I didn't agree with that.

2297
02:19:49,880 --> 02:19:53,380
但是，我相信我的意见是对的。
But I believe my opinion to be right.

2298
02:19:53,380 --> 02:19:55,880
你认为你有可能改变看法吗，
Do you think you might've changed your opinion...

2299
02:19:55,880 --> 02:19:58,910
要是你也像史密斯医生那样为被告做过检查？
if you'd examined the defendant as Dr. Smith did?

2300
02:19:59,390 --> 02:20:02,120
- 我相信不会吧。
- 但是史密斯医生的意见…
- I don't believe so.
- But Dr. Smith's opinion...

2301
02:20:02,220 --> 02:20:04,310
是在更可靠的情况下形成的，不是吗？
was made under better circumstances, wasn't it?

2302
02:20:04,420 --> 02:20:07,260
如果你的意思是指他可以检查这个人，是的。
If you mean that he was able to 
examine the man, yes.

2303
02:20:07,260 --> 02:20:10,660
- 是这个意思。谢谢，医生。
- 好了，哈考特医生。
- Yeah. Thank you, Doctor.
- That's all, Dr. Harcourt.

2304
02:20:10,660 --> 02:20:14,630
- 还有什么辩驳的吗？
- 我们的处境不妙，米奇。
- Is there more rebuttal?
- We're over a barrel, Mitch.

2305
02:20:14,630 --> 02:20:17,330
我们必须用他。
We have to use him.

2306
02:20:17,340 --> 02:20:20,070
我们传杜温・米勒出庭。
We call Duane Miller to the stand.

2307
02:20:20,070 --> 02:20:22,500
请庭警带证人进来好吗？
Will the sheriff please bring in the witness?

2308
02:20:28,720 --> 02:20:31,260
他会说什么？
What can he tell?

2309
02:20:31,260 --> 02:20:33,840
什么都没有。
Nothing.

2310
02:20:33,850 --> 02:20:36,150
他没什么可以说的。
He can't tell anything.

2311
02:20:46,600 --> 02:20:50,070
举起你的右手。
你能不能在上帝面前庄严宣誓，
Raise your right hand. Do you swear 
the testimony you give in this cause...

2312
02:20:50,070 --> 02:20:53,140
你即将为本庭所作的证词将是事实，
完全是事实，除了事实没有别的？
shall be the truth, the whole truth, and
nothing but the truth, so help you God?

2313
02:20:53,140 --> 02:20:54,740
我宣誓。
I do.

2314
02:20:57,010 --> 02:21:01,410
- 请报上你的姓名。
- 杜温・米勒，大伙儿都叫我杜克。
- State your name, please.
- Duane Miller. Most folks call me Duke.

2315
02:21:01,410 --> 02:21:03,410
目前你住在那里，米勒先生？
Where do you presently reside?

2316
02:21:03,420 --> 02:21:05,580
就在街对面的监狱里。
Across the alley in the jail.

2317
02:21:05,590 --> 02:21:07,880
你认识被告弗雷德里克・曼尼昂吗？
You know the defendant, Frederick Manion?

2318
02:21:07,890 --> 02:21:10,820
是的，在过去几个星期里我认识他的，
他的牢房就在我旁边。
Yeah, I got to know him in the past 
few weeks. His cell's next to mine.

2319
02:21:10,820 --> 02:21:13,390
你和中尉最后一次谈话都谈了些什么？
What was the last conversation 
you had with the lieutenant?

2320
02:21:13,390 --> 02:21:17,090
除了今天早晨的打招呼，
最后一次是在昨天晚上。
Except for "hello" this morning, 
the last time was last night.

2321
02:21:17,100 --> 02:21:20,860
- 昨天晚上你们谈到他的审判啦？
- 是的，有一些。
- Did you discuss his trial last night?
- Yeah, some.

2322
02:21:20,870 --> 02:21:24,030
你能不能告诉法庭，曼尼昂中尉
对于他的审判都说了些什么？
Would you tell the court what Lt. Manion 
had to say about the trial?

2323
02:21:24,040 --> 02:21:27,630
嗯，我说：“你的事情怎么样啦，中尉？”
Well, I said, "Are things looking up, Lieutenant?"

2324
02:21:27,640 --> 02:21:30,740
他说：“我搞掂啦，伙计。”
And he said, "I got it made, buster."

2325
02:21:30,740 --> 02:21:33,410
他说：“我骗过了我的律师，
He said, "I fooled my lawyer...

2326
02:21:33,410 --> 02:21:35,140
我骗过了那个查脑瓜子的，
I fooled that head-shrinker...

2327
02:21:35,150 --> 02:21:37,810
我也会骗过陪审团的那帮玉米棒子【傻冒】。”
and I'm gonna fool 
that bunch of corn cobs on the jury."

2328
02:21:37,820 --> 02:21:41,880
撒谎！你个下流的、卑劣的骗子！
Liar! You're a lousy, stinkin' liar!

2329
02:21:42,820 --> 02:21:45,320
镇静，沉住气。
Take it easy, now.

2330
02:21:45,430 --> 02:21:48,390
我为我的委托人道歉，法官大人。
I apologize for my client, Your Honor.

2331
02:21:48,400 --> 02:21:52,260
但是他的爆发应该情有可原，因为控方居然…
Yet his outburst is almost excusable, 
since the prosecution has seen fit...

2332
02:21:52,260 --> 02:21:55,890
让一名罪犯出席作证，以控告一名美军军官。
to put a felon on the stand to testify
against an officer in the U.S. Army.

2333
02:21:55,900 --> 02:22:00,370
法官大人，我不知道谁是更加恶劣的违法者，
曼尼昂还是他的律师。
Your Honor, I don't know who's the 
worse offender, Manion or his lawyer.

2334
02:22:00,370 --> 02:22:02,840
我们快接近尾声了。
We're close to the end.

2335
02:22:02,840 --> 02:22:05,430
看在老天的份上，在这最后的几小时里，
In the name of heaven, let's have peace...

2336
02:22:05,450 --> 02:22:08,480
让我们心平气和、谦恭礼貌点。
and courtesy for these last few hours.

2337
02:22:08,480 --> 02:22:13,260
丹瑟先生，你继续你的质询
但不要发表评论。
Mr. Dancer, you will continue 
your interrogation without comment.

2338
02:22:13,260 --> 02:22:16,650
比格勒先生，你不要一有机会就放炮。
Mr. Biegler, you will not sound off 
at every opportunity.

2339
02:22:16,660 --> 02:22:20,050
被告在座位上坐好，把嘴巴闭上。
And the defendant will remain seated 
in his chair and keep his mouth shut.

2340
02:22:20,060 --> 02:22:22,450
- 现在继续吧。
- 米勒先生，
- Now go ahead.
- Mr. Miller...

2341
02:22:22,460 --> 02:22:25,260
你肯定曼尼昂中尉说的是：
are you certain that Lt. Manion said...

2342
02:22:25,270 --> 02:22:27,560
“我搞掂啦，伙计”？
"I've got it made, buster"?

2343
02:22:27,570 --> 02:22:30,430
- 他就是这么说的。
- 米勒先生，曼尼昂中尉还说了其它什么吗？
- That's what he said.
- Did Lt. Manion say anything else?

2344
02:22:30,440 --> 02:22:33,010
是的，先生。他说他出去后，
Yes, sir. He said when he got out...

2345
02:22:33,010 --> 02:22:35,540
要做的第一件事就是
一脚把那个婊子…
the first thing he was gonna do 
was kick that bitch...

2346
02:22:35,540 --> 02:22:38,440
从这儿踢到天国去。
from here to kingdom come.

2347
02:22:38,450 --> 02:22:41,840
- 他指的是谁？
- 他妻子。
- To whom was he referring?
- To his wife.

2348
02:22:42,350 --> 02:22:44,240
你的证人，比格勒先生。
Your witness.

2349
02:22:44,850 --> 02:22:47,650
- 你为什么入狱，米勒先生？
- 纵火。
- What are you in jail for, Mr. Miller?
- Arson.

2350
02:22:47,750 --> 02:22:49,740
我认罪了，正等候判决。
I copped out, and I'm waiting for a sentence.

2351
02:22:49,860 --> 02:22:51,850
你还犯有多少其它的罪？
How many other offenses have you committed?

2352
02:22:51,960 --> 02:22:55,260
小时候进过教养院，就这些了。
I was in reform school as a kid, but that's all.

2353
02:22:55,360 --> 02:22:58,300
法官大人，我想看一下这个人的犯罪记录。
Your Honor, I'd like to see 
this man's criminal record.

2354
02:22:58,400 --> 02:23:00,260
你有他的记录吗，罗德威克先生？
Do you have his record, Mr. Lodwick?

2355
02:23:00,260 --> 02:23:02,370
有，大人。
Yes, sir.

2356
02:23:02,770 --> 02:23:04,330
给你。
Here it is.

2357
02:23:07,140 --> 02:23:09,970
你的记录显示你曾六次入狱，
Your record shows you've been 
in prison six times...

2358
02:23:09,980 --> 02:23:12,600
在三个不同的州――
in three different states--

2359
02:23:12,610 --> 02:23:16,260
三项纵火罪，两项致命武器袭击罪，
three times for arson, twice for assault 
with a deadly weapon...

2360
02:23:16,260 --> 02:23:18,260
一项盗窃罪。
once for larceny.

2361
02:23:20,190 --> 02:23:23,260
记录还显示了你在四座城市监狱服过短刑，
Also shows you've done short stretches 
in four city jails...

2362
02:23:23,260 --> 02:23:25,920
受到的指控是有伤风化的暴露，
on charges of indecent exposure...

2363
02:23:25,930 --> 02:23:28,150
窗口偷窥，作伪证，
window-peeping, perjury...

2364
02:23:28,160 --> 02:23:31,260
和扰乱治安。
and disorderly conduct.

2365
02:23:31,260 --> 02:23:34,060
这是你的真实记录吗？
Is this your true record?

2366
02:23:34,070 --> 02:23:35,930
那些玩意儿从没对过。
Them things are never right.

2367
02:23:35,940 --> 02:23:38,330
你是怎么透信息给控方的，
How did you get the ear of the prosecution...

2368
02:23:38,340 --> 02:23:41,740
说想告诉他们你和曼尼昂中尉的谈话？
in order to tell them about the 
conversation you had with Lt. Manion?

2369
02:23:41,740 --> 02:23:44,830
- 地方检察官把我们带到他办公室。
- 带谁到他办公室？
- The D.A. was taking us into his office.
- Taking who into his office?

2370
02:23:44,840 --> 02:23:48,260
- 我们监狱里的犯人。
- 一下子都去，还是一次一个？
- Us prisoners in the jail.
- All at once, or one at a time?

2371
02:23:48,260 --> 02:23:51,260
一次一个。他和那个律师…
One at a time. Him and that other lawyer...

2372
02:23:51,260 --> 02:23:55,280
把我们带到他办公室，
问我们有关曼尼昂中尉的问题。
took us to his office and asked us 
questions about Lt. Manion.

2373
02:23:55,290 --> 02:23:58,650
有没有人允诺你，如果你出庭作证，
将对你从轻发落？
Were you promised a lighter sentence
if you went on the witness stand?

2374
02:23:58,660 --> 02:24:01,850
- 法官大人，公诉方反对……
- 反对无效。回答问题。
- Your Honor, the people object to--
- Overruled. Answer the question.

2375
02:24:01,860 --> 02:24:05,450
- 没人允诺我任何事情。
- 你以为那会对你自己的麻烦有帮助，
- I wasn't promised anything.
- You thought it'd help your troubles...

2376
02:24:05,470 --> 02:24:07,900
要是捏造一个这样的故事
来取悦地方检察官。
if you dreamed up this story 
to please the D.A.

2377
02:24:07,900 --> 02:24:10,870
- 我没捏造什么。
- 你肯定那都是曼尼昂中尉说的？
- I didn't dream up nothin'.
- You're sure that's what Manion said?

2378
02:24:10,870 --> 02:24:14,060
- 是的，我肯定。
- 就像你对你的犯罪记录一样肯定？
- Yeah, I'm sure.
- As sure as you were about your record?

2379
02:24:14,070 --> 02:24:18,030
呃，那个我想我可能是有点搞错了。
Well, I guess I kind of goofed on that one.

2380
02:24:19,150 --> 02:24:21,740
法官大人，我不想再问这人什么问题了，
Your Honor, I don't feel I can dignify...

2381
02:24:21,750 --> 02:24:24,410
这让我感到丢脸。
this creature with any more questions.

2382
02:24:24,420 --> 02:24:26,950
把证人带走。
Take the witness away.

2383
02:24:26,990 --> 02:24:29,150
比格勒先生，你想和你的委托人商议一下吗？
Would you like a conference with your client?

2384
02:24:29,160 --> 02:24:32,380
我可以看出来上一个证人
完全出乎你们的意料。
I can see how the last witness 
was quite a surprise.

2385
02:24:32,390 --> 02:24:34,760
不用了，法官大人，我们不需要商议。
No, Your Honor. We don't need a conference.

2386
02:24:34,760 --> 02:24:37,720
我想现在再传曼尼昂中尉上证人席。
I'll recall Lt. Manion to the stand right now.

2387
02:24:45,570 --> 02:24:49,100
你听了这个米勒的证词。
Now, you've heard the testimony of this Miller.

2388
02:24:49,940 --> 02:24:52,810
- 有哪部分是事实吗？
- 没有。
- Is any part of it true?
- None.

2389
02:24:53,680 --> 02:24:58,010
中尉，你知道为什么他会跑到这儿来
编出个这样的故事吗？
Lieutenant, do you have any idea why he 
might come here with a tale like that?

2390
02:24:58,020 --> 02:25:00,320
不知道，先生。
No, sir.

2391
02:25:01,450 --> 02:25:03,960
你和这个人谈过话吗？
Have you ever talked with this man?

2392
02:25:03,960 --> 02:25:05,620
是的。
Yes.

2393
02:25:05,630 --> 02:25:07,820
你们谈了什么？
What did you talk about?

2394
02:25:09,500 --> 02:25:11,760
没什么要紧的事。
Nothing important.

2395
02:25:11,760 --> 02:25:15,430
肯定没有谈过我个人的生活或我的感觉。
Certainly, nothing about 
my personal life or my feelings.

2396
02:25:15,440 --> 02:25:17,590
我想知道的就这些。
That's all I wanted to know.

2397
02:25:17,600 --> 02:25:20,330
曼尼昂中尉，
Lt. Manion...

2398
02:25:20,340 --> 02:25:23,470
你和米勒之间有没有过…
have you ever had any sort of...

2399
02:25:23,480 --> 02:25:26,240
什么过节？
trouble with Miller?

2400
02:25:26,850 --> 02:25:29,680
我不知道。你什么意思？
有没有争吵之类的事情？
I don't know. What do you mean?
An argument? Something like that?

2401
02:25:29,680 --> 02:25:33,880
你有没有攻击――肢体上攻击过他？
Did you ever attack-- physically attack him?

2402
02:25:34,820 --> 02:25:37,390
你的律师不可能替你回答这个问题，中尉。
Your lawyer can't answer 
the question for you, Lieutenant.

2403
02:25:37,390 --> 02:25:42,120
- 你有没有肢体上攻击过米勒？
- 严格地说，那称不上是攻击。
- Did you ever physically attack Miller?
- I wouldn't call it an attack, exactly.

2404
02:25:42,130 --> 02:25:44,260
有一天我把他的头按到栏杆上过。
I pushed his head against the bars one day.

2405
02:25:44,260 --> 02:25:47,460
- 为什么？
- 因为他说了我妻子的坏话。
- Why?
- He said something ugly about my wife.

2406
02:25:47,470 --> 02:25:51,260
你还记得你按着他的头往栏杆上撞吗？
Do you remember pushing or bumping 
his head against the bars?

2407
02:25:51,260 --> 02:25:53,400
当然，我刚告诉过你。
Sure. I just told you.

2408
02:25:53,410 --> 02:25:55,940
那么这不算是“习惯性分裂反应”，嗯？
Then this was not dissociative reaction.

2409
02:25:55,940 --> 02:25:57,970
被告没有资格回答这个问题。
The defendant isn't qualified to answer that.

2410
02:25:57,980 --> 02:26:00,810
- 反对有效。
- 曼尼昂中尉，
- Sustained.
- Lt. Manion...

2411
02:26:00,810 --> 02:26:03,260
你对巴尼・奎尔所做的反应，
wasn't your action against Barney Quill 
much the same...

2412
02:26:03,260 --> 02:26:05,940
是不是和你对米勒，
和对那个你在鸡尾酒会上…
as your action against Miller 
and against the lieutenant...

2413
02:26:05,950 --> 02:26:08,280
打了的少尉，所做的反应相同呢？
that you struck at the cocktail party?

2414
02:26:08,290 --> 02:26:12,920
都是在盛怒之下产生了有意识的、
蓄意的伤害或杀戮的欲望。
All in the heat of anger with a willful, 
conscious desire to hurt or kill?

2415
02:26:12,930 --> 02:26:15,560
我不记得我对奎尔所做的反应了。
I don't remember my action against Quill.

2416
02:26:16,400 --> 02:26:20,230
你知道你妻子和巴尼・奎尔是相好
有多长时间了？
How long had you known that your wife 
was running around with Barney Quill?

2417
02:26:21,270 --> 02:26:24,260
我从不知道有这样的事情。
I never knew anything like that.

2418
02:26:24,260 --> 02:26:26,230
我信任我妻子。
I trust my wife.

2419
02:26:27,110 --> 02:26:29,830
我想你时不时地打她
那只是为了找点乐子。
I suppose you just beat her up 
occasionally for the fun of it.

2420
02:26:29,840 --> 02:26:33,260
没有道理允许问这样的问题。
Nothing has been established
to permit a question like that.

2421
02:26:33,260 --> 02:26:35,440
他总是在暗指什么却不明确观点。
He keeps implying things 
without getting to the point.

2422
02:26:35,450 --> 02:26:38,880
就让他直接问中尉，
他有没有殴打过他妻子？
Let him ask the lieutenant, 
did he ever beat his wife?

2423
02:26:38,890 --> 02:26:40,850
我要说反对有效。
I'll sustain the objection.

2424
02:26:40,850 --> 02:26:43,780
你能重新表述一下你的问题吗，丹瑟先生？
Would you like to rephrase 
your question, Mr. Dancer?

2425
02:26:45,090 --> 02:26:47,320
不用了。谢谢，法官大人。
No thank you, Your Honor.

2426
02:26:47,330 --> 02:26:49,330
我问完了。
I've finished.

2427
02:26:49,330 --> 02:26:52,690
那我来问好了。曼尼昂中尉，你有没有…
Then I'll ask him. Did you, Lt. Manion...

2428
02:26:52,700 --> 02:26:55,930
在发生枪击的那个晚上，或任何其它时候
殴打过你的妻子？
ever beat your wife on the night
of the shooting or any other time?

2429
02:26:55,940 --> 02:26:57,970
- 没有，先生。
- 在你心里有没有一丝的疑问，
- No, sir.
- Is there any doubt in your mind...

2430
02:26:57,970 --> 02:27:00,470
怀疑巴尼・奎尔强奸了你的妻子？
that Barney Quill raped Mrs. Manion?

2431
02:27:00,470 --> 02:27:02,470
- 没有，先生。
- 就这些。
- No, sir.
- That's all.

2432
02:27:02,480 --> 02:27:04,280
请退席，中尉。
Step down, Lieutenant.

2433
02:27:09,980 --> 02:27:12,940
- 大事不妙？
- 相当糟糕。
- We hurt?
- We're hurt bad.

2434
02:27:18,490 --> 02:27:22,360
法官大人，我知道时间已经很紧，
所以我不想请求休庭。
Your Honor, I know time is pressing.
I don't want to ask for a recess.

2435
02:27:22,360 --> 02:27:24,400
但是我想离开法庭一下，就一会儿。
I would like to leave the courtroom for a moment.

2436
02:27:24,400 --> 02:27:27,060
如果那很重要的话，我们可以给你一分钟。
If it's important, we can be at ease for a minute.

2437
02:27:27,070 --> 02:27:29,260
谢谢您，大人。
Thank you, sir.

2438
02:27:29,500 --> 02:27:32,070
这太不合规矩了，法官大人。
This is highly irregular, Your Honor.

2439
02:27:32,070 --> 02:27:35,770
没有理由据此整出个联邦大案来【小题大做】。
There's no reason to make a federal case out of it.

2440
02:27:46,490 --> 02:27:50,020
非常感谢，法官大人。
我们现在有了另一位反驳证人。
Thank you very much, Your Honor.
We now have another rebuttal witness.

2441
02:27:50,020 --> 02:27:52,420
辩方传玛丽・皮兰特出庭。
The defense calls Mary Pilant to the stand.

2442
02:27:52,430 --> 02:27:54,620
法官大人，我们必须抗议这整个安排。
We must protest this whole affair.

2443
02:27:54,630 --> 02:27:57,560
尊贵的辩方律师冲出去进行了秘密商议，
The noble defense attorney rushes out 
to a secret conference...

2444
02:27:57,560 --> 02:28:00,630
而现在却在最后一刻
戏剧性地把证人带下了过道。
and now the last-minute witness is being
brought dramatically down the aisle.

2445
02:28:00,630 --> 02:28:03,760
这整个事情很显然受到了操控，
目的是不正当地激起陪审团的兴趣。
The whole thing has obviously been
rigged to unduly excite the jury.

2446
02:28:03,770 --> 02:28:06,340
这是比格勒先生的又一个陈腐鄙俗的诡计。
It's another cornball trick.

2447
02:28:06,340 --> 02:28:09,700
法官大人，我不会怪丹瑟先生
有被占了便宜的感觉。
Your Honor, I don't blame Mr. Dancer 
for feeling put-upon.

2448
02:28:09,710 --> 02:28:12,780
我只是个卑微的地方律师，
想做的只是尽我所能，
I'm just a humble country lawyer 
trying to do the best I can...

2449
02:28:12,780 --> 02:28:16,280
全力对抗这位从大都市兰辛来的
才华横溢的检察官。
against this brilliant prosecutor 
from the big city of Lansing.

2450
02:28:16,280 --> 02:28:18,750
让证人宣誓。
Swear the witness.

2451
02:28:18,750 --> 02:28:22,650
请举起你的右手。你能不能
在上帝面前庄严宣誓，
Raise your right hand. Do you swear
the testimony you shall give...

2452
02:28:22,660 --> 02:28:26,560
你即将为本庭所作的证词将是事实，
完全是事实，除了事实没有别的？
shall be the truth, the whole truth, and
nothing but the truth, so help you God?

2453
02:28:26,560 --> 02:28:28,860
- 我宣誓。
- 请坐下。
- I do.
- Sit down, please.

2454
02:28:31,630 --> 02:28:34,720
- 你住在哪儿，皮兰特小姐？
- 雷鸣湾的“雷鸣湾旅店”。
- Where do you live, Miss Pilant?
- At Thunder Bay Inn in Thunder Bay.

2455
02:28:34,730 --> 02:28:38,100
- 你在那儿住了多长时间了？
- 两年了。
- And how long have you lived there?
- For two years.

2456
02:28:38,100 --> 02:28:41,170
- 你的职业是什么？
- 我管理这家旅店。
- And what's your profession?
- I manage the inn.

2457
02:28:41,170 --> 02:28:45,900
皮兰特小姐，“雷鸣湾旅店”的洗衣房是怎样运作的？
Now, Miss Pilant, how is the laundry 
handled at Thunder Bay Inn?

2458
02:28:45,910 --> 02:28:47,940
有个斜道将衣服滑入洗衣间。
It's chuted down to the laundry room.

2459
02:28:47,950 --> 02:28:50,740
二楼的滑道在什么位置？
Where is the location of that chute 
on the second floor?

2460
02:28:50,750 --> 02:28:54,380
- 在42号和43号房之间。
- 谁住在那两个房间？
- Between room 42 and 43.
- Who lives in those rooms?

2461
02:28:54,390 --> 02:28:58,150
我住42号，奎尔先生住43号。
I live in 42. Mr. Quill lived in 43.

2462
02:28:58,160 --> 02:29:00,730
如果奎尔先生从大厅出来，
Would Mr. Quill, coming up from the lobby...

2463
02:29:00,730 --> 02:29:04,930
走回他的房间，是不是必定经过那个滑道口？
have to pass by the mouth of that chute 
on the way to his room?

2464
02:29:04,930 --> 02:29:05,530
是的。
Yes.

2465
02:29:05,530 --> 02:29:09,260
那么当他经过时，是不是很容易
把什么东西丢入那个滑道？
Would it be very easy for him to drop 
something into that chute as he passed?

2466
02:29:09,260 --> 02:29:10,130
是的。
Yes.

2467
02:29:10,140 --> 02:29:14,100
你是否有的时候也到
下面的洗衣房去看看呢？
Have you ever had occasion to go 
down into the laundry at any time?

2468
02:29:14,110 --> 02:29:17,510
是的，我的工作之一就是
在衣服洗完烘干之后，
Yes. Part of my job is to sort 
various pieces of laundry...

2469
02:29:17,510 --> 02:29:20,100
将送洗的衣服分类整好。
as they come out of the wash-and-dry machine.

2470
02:29:20,110 --> 02:29:23,260
你能不能告诉法庭，
在奎尔先生被杀后的第二天，
Would you tell the court what you found 
among those pieces of laundry...

2471
02:29:23,260 --> 02:29:25,770
你在这些衣服里面发现了什么？
the day after Mr. Quill was killed?

2472
02:29:25,790 --> 02:29:28,120
我发现了一条女人的内裤。
I found a pair of women's panties.

2473
02:29:28,120 --> 02:29:31,190
- 你把内裤怎么样了？
- 我把它扔到了破衣箱里。
- And what did you do with them?
- I threw them in the rag bin.

2474
02:29:31,190 --> 02:29:34,620
你什么时候意识到这条内裤的重要性的？
When did you learn the significance 
of those panties?

2475
02:29:34,630 --> 02:29:37,660
这儿，今天上午，在法庭里。
Here. This morning, in the courtroom.

2476
02:29:37,660 --> 02:29:39,760
然后你就回家把它从破衣箱里取了出来？
And then you went home 
and got them out of the rag bin?

2477
02:29:39,760 --> 02:29:40,330
是的。
Yes.

2478
02:29:40,330 --> 02:29:42,300
你把它带来了吗？
Did you bring them with you?

2479
02:29:42,300 --> 02:29:43,410
是的。
Yes.

2480
02:29:45,510 --> 02:29:48,940
我提供这件女性内衣…
I offer this article of lingerie...

2481
02:29:48,940 --> 02:29:51,370
作为辩方的一号呈堂证物。
as Exhibit Number One for the defense.

2482
02:29:51,380 --> 02:29:55,710
它是白色的，边上有花边，
They're white, they have lace up the side...

2483
02:29:55,720 --> 02:29:58,080
被严重撕坏，
and they're badly torn...

2484
02:29:58,080 --> 02:30:01,920
像是被一双有力的大手扯烂的。
as if they've been ripped apart by powerful hands.

2485
02:30:01,920 --> 02:30:04,260
标签上印着――
The label reads...

2486
02:30:05,290 --> 02:30:07,990
“亚利桑那凤凰城时髦商店”。
"Smart Shop, Phoenix, Arizona."

2487
02:30:07,990 --> 02:30:11,430
如果没有反对，该物品将被接受为证物。
If there is no objection, the exhibit 
will be received in evidence.

2488
02:30:11,430 --> 02:30:14,620
- 我问完了，皮兰特小姐。
- 你曾和罗德威克先生交谈过…
- That's all, Miss Pilant.
- Do you ever talk to Mr. Lodwick...

2489
02:30:14,630 --> 02:30:16,670
巴尼・奎尔之死吗？
about the death of Barney Quill?

2490
02:30:16,670 --> 02:30:19,700
是的，在奎尔先生被杀后，他来过旅店几次。
He came to the hotel several times 
after Mr. Quill was killed.

2491
02:30:19,710 --> 02:30:23,100
你是否告诉过罗德威克先生你不相信
巴尼・奎尔强奸了曼尼昂夫人？
Did you tell Mr. Lodwick that you didn't 
believe Barney Quill raped Mrs. Manion?

2492
02:30:23,110 --> 02:30:27,310
- 是的，我是这样告诉他的。
- 皮兰特小姐，你和被告律师比格勒先生谈过吗？
- Yes, I told him that.
- Did you ever talk to Mr. Biegler?

2493
02:30:27,310 --> 02:30:27,910
是的。
Yes.

2494
02:30:27,910 --> 02:30:30,360
内容是否也和奎尔被杀有关？
Was this also in connection 
with the shooting of Quill?

2495
02:30:30,360 --> 02:30:30,710
是的。
Yes.

2496
02:30:30,720 --> 02:30:33,260
你是否告诉过他你不相信
巴尼・奎尔强奸了曼尼昂夫人？
Did you tell him you didn't believe 
Barney Quill had raped Mrs. Manion?

2497
02:30:33,260 --> 02:30:33,550
是的。
Yes.

2498
02:30:33,550 --> 02:30:35,680
- 你和他谈过几次？
- 两次。
- How many times did you talk to him?
- Twice.

2499
02:30:35,690 --> 02:30:37,980
- 最后一次是什么时候？
- 昨天晚上。
- When was the last time?
- Last night.

2500
02:30:37,990 --> 02:30:40,390
那么你现在改变主意啦？
你现在相信…
And have you now changed your mind?
Do you now believe...

2501
02:30:40,390 --> 02:30:42,760
巴尼・奎尔强奸过曼尼昂夫人？
Barney Quill raped Mrs. Manion?

2502
02:30:42,760 --> 02:30:44,920
我现在不知道，我想有可能吧。
I don't know now. I think he might have.

2503
02:30:44,930 --> 02:30:47,090
你什么时候改变的主意？昨天晚上？
When did you change your mind? Last night?

2504
02:30:47,100 --> 02:30:50,070
- 不，是在这儿，今天上午。
- 什么时候给你的裤子？
- No, it was here, this morning.
- When were you given the panties?

2505
02:30:50,070 --> 02:30:52,360
- 昨天晚上吗？
- 不，且慢！先且慢！
- Was that last night?
- Just wait a minute!

2506
02:30:52,370 --> 02:30:55,340
用适当的形式反对，比格勒先生。
Use the proper form of objection, Mr. Biegler.

2507
02:30:55,340 --> 02:30:59,430
转念一想，我不反对了。
我想让陪审团听听她的回答。
On second thought, I don't object.
I'd like the jury to hear her answer.

2508
02:30:59,450 --> 02:31:02,040
- 证人可以回答。
- 不。
- The witness may answer.
- No.

2509
02:31:02,050 --> 02:31:04,980
没人在昨天晚上或任何其他时候给过我内裤，
I was not given the panties last night 
or at any other time.

2510
02:31:04,980 --> 02:31:07,920
- 我自己发现的，就像我刚才说的那样。
- 你是事实上知道…
- I found them exactly as I said.
- Do you know for a fact...

2511
02:31:07,920 --> 02:31:10,890
巴尼・奎尔把那条内裤
丢进了滑道呢，还只是你的推测？
that Barney Quill dropped the panties
down the chute, or did you assume it?

2512
02:31:10,890 --> 02:31:13,420
- 我推测的。
- 你有没有想过有可能某个其他的人…
- I assumed it.
- Had you thought maybe someone else...

2513
02:31:13,430 --> 02:31:16,990
把内裤放那儿的，一个想让内裤
在洗衣房被发现的人？
might have put the panties there
who wanted them found in the laundry?

2514
02:31:17,000 --> 02:31:18,500
我还没那样想过。
I hadn't thought of that.

2515
02:31:18,500 --> 02:31:22,430
在比格勒先生的所谓
“无法抑制的冲动”的控制之下，
And in the grip of what Mr. Biegler 
might call irresistible impulse...

2516
02:31:22,440 --> 02:31:25,160
你气冲冲地拿着内裤跑到这儿，
目的是想拷问…
you rushed in here with the panties
because you wanted to crucify...

2517
02:31:25,170 --> 02:31:27,260
已故的巴尼・奎尔的人格，是不是这样？
the dead Barney Quill, isn't that true?

2518
02:31:27,260 --> 02:31:30,260
- 不，我想这是我的责任……
- 你的自尊心受到了伤害，是不是？
- No, I thought it was my duty--
- Your pride was hurt, wasn't it?

2519
02:31:30,260 --> 02:31:33,280
- 我不明白你在说什么。
- 法官大人，他想把证人搞糊涂了。
- I don't know what you mean.
- He's trying to confuse the witness.

2520
02:31:33,280 --> 02:31:35,850
让他问她能理解的问题。
Let him ask her a question she can understand.

2521
02:31:35,850 --> 02:31:39,940
是的，丹瑟先生，我自己也想知道你的用意所在。
Yes, Mr. Dancer. I myself would like 
to know what you're driving at.

2522
02:31:39,950 --> 02:31:43,390
皮兰特小姐，当你发现了那条内裤，
Miss Pilant, when you found the panties...

2523
02:31:43,390 --> 02:31:46,720
你的第一个念头是巴尼・奎尔
可能强奸了曼尼昂夫人呢，
was your first thought that Barney Quill 
might have raped Mrs. Manion...

2524
02:31:46,730 --> 02:31:50,730
还是他可能和曼尼昂夫人有了一腿？
or was it that he might have been
stepping out with Mrs. Manion?

2525
02:31:50,730 --> 02:31:52,890
他什么意思，我不知道他什么意思。
I don't know what he means.

2526
02:31:52,900 --> 02:31:57,560
丹瑟先生，我再一次要求你，
问证人直接的问题。
Mr. Dancer, once again I must ask you to 
put straight questions to the witness.

2527
02:31:57,570 --> 02:32:01,100
这个就是直接的问题，法官大人：
Here is a straight question, Your Honor.

2528
02:32:01,110 --> 02:32:03,870
皮兰特小姐，你是巴尼・奎尔的情人吗？
Miss Pilant, are you Barney Quill's mistress?

2529
02:32:03,880 --> 02:32:05,870
不！不，我不是！
No. No, I was not!

2530
02:32:05,880 --> 02:32:07,970
在雷鸣湾人人都知道你和奎尔住在一起。
It's common knowledge in Thunder Bay 
you were living with Quill.

2531
02:32:07,980 --> 02:32:12,050
- 这不是事实。巴尼・奎尔是……
- 是什么，皮兰特小姐？
- That's not true. Barney Quill was--
- Was what, Miss Pilant?

2532
02:32:12,050 --> 02:32:15,720
巴尼・奎尔是什么，皮兰特小姐？
Barney Quill was what, Miss Pilant?

2533
02:32:16,720 --> 02:32:19,680
巴尼・奎尔是我的父亲。
Barney Quill was my father.

2534
02:32:30,740 --> 02:32:32,960
没有问题了。
No more questions.

2535
02:32:32,970 --> 02:32:34,970
我没有问题。
That's all for me.

2536
02:32:34,970 --> 02:32:37,970
证人可以退下了。
The witness may step down.

2537
02:32:37,980 --> 02:32:40,670
现在休庭15分钟，随后，
We will recess for 15 minutes, after which...

2538
02:32:40,680 --> 02:32:43,080
我们将聆听双方的总结陈词。
we will hear the closing arguments.

2539
02:32:43,080 --> 02:32:47,540
如果有可能，我希望陪审团
在黄昏之前作出裁决。
If possible, I would like to charge 
the jury before nightfall.

2540
02:33:03,260 --> 02:33:05,570
你想他们会一直弄到深夜吗？
Think they're gonna stay out all night?

2541
02:33:20,590 --> 02:33:23,550
谁能不能说点什么？
Can't somebody say something?

2542
02:33:24,960 --> 02:33:27,550
你想让我说什么，梅达，亲爱的？
What do you want me to say, Maida, darling?

2543
02:33:27,560 --> 02:33:30,890
跟我说我们会赢。
Tell me we're gonna win.

2544
02:33:30,900 --> 02:33:34,930
我还指望着拿到中尉的期票呢。
I'm counting on getting that 
promissory note from the lieutenant.

2545
02:33:34,930 --> 02:33:39,260
我希望可以靠它先借点钱。
我需要一台新的打字机。
I hope I can borrow some money on it.
I need a new typewriter.

2546
02:33:39,260 --> 02:33:43,500
有一半时间，我的打字机
打不出“第”和“事”。
Half the time, the "p" and the "f" 
don't strike on mine.

2547
02:33:43,510 --> 02:33:46,260
“第一部分当事人”有时被打成…
"Party of the first part" sometimes comes out...

2548
02:33:46,260 --> 02:33:48,800
“一部分当人”。
"arty of the irst art."

2549
02:33:48,810 --> 02:33:51,640
根本没道理嘛，让人哭笑不得。
Doesn't make sense. It's embarrassing.

2550
02:33:51,650 --> 02:33:54,120
“一部分当人”？
"Arty of the irst art"?

2551
02:33:54,120 --> 02:33:56,350
我有点喜欢这个，
I kind of like that.

2552
02:33:56,360 --> 02:33:58,880
很有意味。
Has a ring to it.

2553
02:34:01,390 --> 02:34:04,490
十二个人走进个房间。
Twelve people go off into a room.

2554
02:34:05,600 --> 02:34:09,630
十二个不同的头脑，
十二种不同的心情，
Twelve different minds, 
twelve different hearts...

2555
02:34:09,640 --> 02:34:13,100
十二条不同的生活轨迹；
and twelve different walks of life.

2556
02:34:13,110 --> 02:34:17,110
十二双眼睛和耳朵，有不同的形状和大小。
Twelve sets of eyes, ears, shapes and sizes.

2557
02:34:17,110 --> 02:34:20,110
这十二个人，
And these twelve people...

2558
02:34:20,110 --> 02:34:23,310
被要求对另一个人作出判决，
are asked to judge another human being...

2559
02:34:23,320 --> 02:34:26,850
这个人也完全不同于他们，
就像他们之间互不相同。
as different from them 
as they are from each other.

2560
02:34:26,850 --> 02:34:30,510
而在他们判决时，
他们必须变成一个头脑――
And in their judgment, 
they must become of one mind.

2561
02:34:30,520 --> 02:34:33,350
一致同意。
Unanimous.

2562
02:34:33,360 --> 02:34:37,760
这是人类混乱不堪的心灵
所能做到的奇迹之一，
That's one of the miracles of man's 
disorganized soul that they can do it.

2563
02:34:38,800 --> 02:34:41,290
而且在大多数情况下，做得不错。
And most instances, do it right well.

2564
02:34:42,970 --> 02:34:46,140
上帝保佑陪审员们。
God bless juries.

2565
02:34:46,970 --> 02:34:50,030
我不知道要是我在陪审团里，我会怎么做。
I don't know what I'd do if I were on that jury.

2566
02:34:53,280 --> 02:34:55,580
我真的不知道。
I really don't know.

2567
02:34:56,720 --> 02:34:58,240
你呢？
Do you?

2568
02:35:02,690 --> 02:35:04,690
我喜欢那个，保利。
I loved that, Paulie.

2569
02:35:04,690 --> 02:35:08,690
我喜欢那什么“卑微的地方律师”之说，
I loved that "humble country lawyer" bit.

2570
02:35:08,690 --> 02:35:11,920
你让丹瑟【舞者】先生翩翩起舞了。
You had Mr. Dancer dancing.

2571
02:35:11,930 --> 02:35:13,930
我担心他会跳到最后。
I'm afraid he got in the last dance.

2572
02:35:13,930 --> 02:35:16,370
他的总结是我听过的最好的法庭总结陈词。
That's the best summary I've ever heard 
in a courtroom.

2573
02:35:16,370 --> 02:35:19,670
我还是更喜欢你的，保利。
I liked yours much better, Paulie.

2574
02:35:24,260 --> 02:35:27,140
你非得弹那玩意儿吗？
你不会弹《丹尼小子》…
Do you have to play that stuff?
Can't you play "Danny Boy"...

2575
02:35:27,150 --> 02:35:29,640
或《甜蜜的茵尼斯弗利岛》？
or "Sweet Isle of Innisfree"?

2576
02:35:43,330 --> 02:35:47,560
保罗・比格勒办公室。
好的，先生，这就过去。
Paul Biegler's office.
Yes, sir. Right away.

2577
02:35:47,570 --> 02:35:49,870
他们好了。
They're ready.

2578
02:35:59,260 --> 02:36:01,410
嗨，亲爱的。
Hey, sweetie.

2579
02:36:02,480 --> 02:36:03,760
接着走。
Go on.

2580
02:36:05,260 --> 02:36:07,440
- 陪审团已经进去了。
- 是啊，我听说了。
- The jury's coming in.
- Yeah, I heard.

2581
02:36:07,450 --> 02:36:10,520
你可以告诉我可爱的丈夫我在车里等他。
You can tell my loving husband 
I'll be waiting in the car.

2582
02:36:10,520 --> 02:36:13,720
- 你肯定他会出来？
- 噢，当然！
- You're sure he's gonna come out?
- Oh, sure!

2583
02:36:13,730 --> 02:36:17,390
他运气好，有的人运气就是好。
He's lucky. Some people have all the luck.

2584
02:36:17,400 --> 02:36:22,060
你可以告诉他我在等他把我踢到天国去。
You can tell him I'm waiting 
to get kicked to kingdom come.

2585
02:36:22,070 --> 02:36:24,130
噢！嘿，亲爱的，
Oh! Hey, sweetie...

2586
02:36:24,140 --> 02:36:27,000
我有件纪念品给你。
I have a souvenir for you.

2587
02:36:28,040 --> 02:36:30,130
呃，你最好还是自己留着。
You'd better keep that thing.

2588
02:36:30,140 --> 02:36:32,840
也许什么时候你又会用得着，谁知道呢。
You might need it again sometime. 
You never know.

2589
02:36:32,850 --> 02:36:35,070
是的，是不知道，对吗？
No, you don't, do you?

2590
02:36:35,080 --> 02:36:37,710
噢，我喜欢你，保利。
Oh, I like you, Paulie.

2591
02:36:44,060 --> 02:36:47,960
我提醒在场的各位不要打断判决过程，
I warn all those present not 
to interrupt the taking of the verdict.

2592
02:36:47,960 --> 02:36:50,530
一旦出现这样的迹象，我将中止判决，
I will stop the proceedings 
and clear the courtroom...

2593
02:36:50,530 --> 02:36:53,300
进行清场。
if there is any demonstration.

2594
02:37:01,840 --> 02:37:03,930
开始吧，书记官先生。
Proceed, Mr. Clerk.

2595
02:37:03,940 --> 02:37:06,600
陪审员们，你们是否已经就裁决取得一致意见？
Members of the jury, 
have you agreed upon a verdict...

2596
02:37:06,610 --> 02:37:10,110
- 如果是的话，谁是你们的代言人？
- 我们已经取得一致，我是陪审团主席。
- and if so, who will speak for you?
- We have. I'm the foreman.

2597
02:37:10,120 --> 02:37:12,420
被告起立。
The defendant will rise.

2598
02:37:14,850 --> 02:37:17,260
- 你们的裁决是什么？
- 我们认为被告…
- What is your verdict?
- We find the defendant...

2599
02:37:17,260 --> 02:37:20,090
无罪，理由是精神错乱。
not guilty by reason of insanity.

2600
02:37:25,360 --> 02:37:27,760
梅达给了你那张期票单，是吗？
Maida gave you that promissory note, didn't she?

2601
02:37:27,770 --> 02:37:30,730
就在这儿，就等我们快乐的委托人签字了。
Right here, ready to be signed by our happy client.

2602
02:37:31,840 --> 02:37:35,770
你知道，有一阵子我觉得透过威士忌酒瓶，
这世界看上去更加美好，
You know, I used to think the world 
looked better through a glass of whisky.

2603
02:37:35,770 --> 02:37:37,940
但其实不然。
It doesn't.

2604
02:37:37,940 --> 02:37:41,070
我想我会保持这样的状态，感觉不错。
I think I'll keep it this way. Looks nice.

2605
02:37:41,910 --> 02:37:45,260
嗯，通过这个案子，我有一个收获――
Well, I got one good thing out of this case--

2606
02:37:45,260 --> 02:37:49,280
一个新的法律伙伴，如果他也同意的话。
a new law partner, if it's all right with him.

2607
02:37:49,290 --> 02:37:53,150
把他的名字刻在你的招牌上，
他会感到非常自豪的。
He'd be mighty proud to have his name 
on a shingle with yours.

2608
02:38:22,960 --> 02:38:26,320
我猜你们是来找曼尼昂中尉的，
是吗，比格勒先生？
I guess you're looking for Lt. Manion, 
aren't you, Mr. Biegler?

2609
02:38:26,330 --> 02:38:28,720
他让我把这个条子转给你。
He gave me this note for you.

2610
02:38:29,900 --> 02:38:34,020
我真替曼尼昂夫人难过，她哭得厉害。
I felt real sorry for Mrs. Manion.
She was crying.

2611
02:38:34,030 --> 02:38:37,800
他们把这儿搞得一团糟，是不是？
嗯，我得忙我的去了。
Left a mess, didn't they?
Well, we'd better get busy here.

2612
02:38:37,800 --> 02:38:41,840
“亲爱的比格勒先生，
非常抱歉我的突然离去，
"Dear Mr. Biegler, 
so sorry that I had to leave suddenly.

2613
02:38:41,840 --> 02:38:44,870
因为我的‘无法抑制的冲动’症又犯了。
I was seized by an irresistible impulse.

2614
02:38:44,880 --> 02:38:47,540
弗雷德里克・曼尼昂。”
Frederick Manion."

2615
02:38:47,550 --> 02:38:50,570
这下我们究竟怎么去见梅达呢？
How in the world are we gonna face Maida?

2616
02:38:51,780 --> 02:38:55,880
杜松子酒。我就知道那家伙有什么地方不对劲。
Gin. I knew there was something wrong with that guy.

2617
02:38:55,890 --> 02:38:58,620
还从没见过一个喝杜松子酒的你可以信任的。
Never saw a gin drinker yet you could trust.

2618
02:38:59,730 --> 02:39:02,820
搭档，你说我们去见我们的
第一位委托人怎么样？
Partner, what do you say 
we go and see our first client?

2619
02:39:02,830 --> 02:39:05,020
- 那会是谁？
- 玛丽・皮兰特。
- Who might that be?
- Mary Pilant.

2620
02:39:05,030 --> 02:39:07,720
我们去帮她打理巴尼・奎尔的财产。
We're gonna administer Barney Quill's estate.

2621
02:39:07,730 --> 02:39:11,570
这就是我说的“善恶有报，人人难逃”。
Now, that's what I call poetic justice for everybody.

2622
02:39:23,440 --> 02:39:31,440
[ 中文翻译：疯狂弥天大幌 ]
[ translation: loco-whopper ]

2623
02:39:32,320 --> 02:39:35,600
[ 谢谢观看！]
[ thanks for watching! ]
